title: pecan crisps
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet with teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Preheat oven before baking.
This is one of my favorite recipes.
I make them all the time for our church.
Everyone loves them!

title: cheese and zucchini bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter (or spray) a 9 x 13 glass baking dish.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in heavy, large skillet over medium heat.
Cook onion and garlic until softened.
Add zucchini and cook until tender, about 10 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 cup Monterey Jack cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, 1/4 cup bread crumbs, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper. Transfer to baking dish. Sprinkle remaining Monterey Jack cheese over.
Combine eggs and cream; pour over zucchini. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Dot with remaining butter. Bake until golden brown, about 35 minutes. Can be made 1 day ahead.
Rewarm before serving.

title: hotchpotch(hutspol)
directions: Wash meat, boil in two cups water and salt.
Scrub and mince carrots.
Peel, wash and slice onions and add them to the meat together with peeled and cut potatoes and carrots.
Boil until done (about 30 minutes).
Remove meat from pan.
Mash all vegetables together, add butter and pepper to taste.
If too thick, add some milk (but a spoon must stand up in it).
Serve with sliced meat.
I make gravy out of leftover juice.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Tear 4 pieces of foil large enough to enclose hamburger patty and vegetables.
Place 1 patty on each piece of foil.
Add a slice of onion.
Place quartered potato on onion slice.
Add sliced carrots.
Top with 1 tablespoon butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put foil together.
Fold at top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Real good!

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix everything together.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until potatoes are done.

title: goulash
directions: Brown beef in pan; add tomato soup, water, onion and pepper. Simmer this mixture while preparing spaghetti according to directions on package.
Add spaghetti to meat mixture.
Simmer this about 15 minutes.

title: summer fresh fruit pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating at medium speed (4 minutes) after adding each egg.
Blend in flavoring.
Pour in cold pie crust.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Best to let set overnight.
Add fruit (your favorite) like strawberries to make pie look pretty.

title: heavenly grahams
directions: Mix
egg, sugar, butter and milk.
Cook until it begins to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in coconut, nuts and 1 cup graham cracker crumbs.
Line cookie sheet with graham crackers and spread mixture
over
crackers;
top with graham crackers. Combine powdered sugar,
cup
margarine,
vanilla
and
2 tablespoons milk.
Mix
until
smooth.
Spread
over
top
of graham crackers and chill for two hours and slice.

title: dave's gorp
directions: Mix and enjoy.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: honey-soy chicken
directions: Mix together first six ingredients.
Pound breasts until 1/2-inch thick.
Marinate for 4 to 6 hours or overnight in orange juice-soy sauce mixture.
Grill 10 minutes, turning once.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all, except cheese.
Pour 1/2 in large iron skillet that has been greased and heated.
Sprinkle 1/2 cheese over it, then add rest of batter.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake as corn bread in a 400° oven until brown.

title: spiced-up coffee
directions: Place coffee in coffee filter or filter basket.
Spoon flavoring over coffee.
Add water to coffeemaker and brew.
Serve immediately.
Great for a brunch.

title: layered garden pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Stir together macaroni, onions and 2 tablespoons of bacon in medium bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, cheese, sugar and garlic powder.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Pour juice off of pickles and slice.
Return to jar; add sugar, onion, celery seed and vinegar and shake real good.
Let set a couple days and eat.

title: marinade for venison
directions: Place ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Simmer covered for 1
hour.
Cool.
Pour over meat and marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: favorite oysters
directions: Put
your
oysters on half shell.
Put them on a cookie sheet. Put
bacon
on
top of each oyster.
Bake in 350° oven until oysters and bacon start
to
curl up.
Top with slice of cheese and cook until the cheese melts.

title: frugal gourmet's artichoke and curried eggs
directions: Peel and chop eggs.
Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Combine eggs and artichokes into a coarse spread.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, salt, pepper and curry powder.
(Go lightly on curry; this should not be hot.)
Refrigerate.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Put 1/2 of batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool cake 10 minutes.

title: pudding fudge
directions: Cook to soft ball stage.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour into buttered pan and cool.

title: pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large baking dish, place roast. Prepare soup mix with water as directed.
Add flour to mixture. Arrange vegetables around roast.
Pour soup mixture over all. Bake, covered, until roast is tender, 1 1/2 to 2 1/4 hours.

title: juanita's famous baked beans
directions: Start by 9 p.m.
Cook on low heat overnight.
Check by 6 a.m. May need a bit more water.
Be sure to add a handful of parsley flakes for good luck and good taste!

title: roasted garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and mash with enough whipping cream to make them fluffy. Add salt, pepper and butter. Roast garlic in a little butter until very dark. Put garlic with 1 stick butter in food processor. Mince. Add to potatoes.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Mix flour, powder, sugar and salt.
Add pineapple, egg and oleo.
Mix lightly with fork.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: barbecued pork ribs
directions: Place ribs in shallow roasting pan, meaty side up.
Sprinkle with 2 teaspoons liquid smoke.
Roast in hot oven at 450° for 30 minutes. Combine remaining ingredients except smoke and celery seed. Bring to boiling and pour over ribs.
Continue baking in moderate 350° oven for 1 hour or until tender. Baste ribs with sauce every 15 or 20 minutes.
Fifteen minutes before ribs are done, sprinkle with remaining liquid smoke and celery seed. Serves 4.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Beat together eggs and oil. Add to dry ingredients.
Add apples and nuts or raisins.
Pour into 9x13 pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease sheet with Crisco.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix until creamed on low speed.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop one tablespoon of dough 2 inches apart on sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes and remove from sheet.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Wash and bake potatoes 1 hour at 400° or until done.
Let cool.
Cut in half and scoop out pulp.
Melt butter over low heat. Add flour.
Stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Add potato pulp, salt, pepper, 2 tablespoons green onion, 1/2 cup bacon and 1 cup cheese. Cook until thoroughly heated.
Stir in sour cream.
Add extra milk for desired thickness.
Serve.
Sprinkle with remaining onions, cheese and bacon.
Yields 10 cups.

title: onion-garlic hot toddy
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender; add water and blend until smooth.
Pour in pot and boil until hot, stirring constantly. Serves 4.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add salt and flour; mix well and add nuts.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: raisin banana picnic cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat in bananas, shortening, milk, peel and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes, scraping bowl constantly. Add eggs; beat 2 minutes more, scraping bowl.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into wax lined (or greased and floured) 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until pick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 minutes; turn out onto rack to cool.
Frost.

title: peach jam
directions: Add 1 cup of sugar to peaches.
Bring to rolling boil.
Add rest of sugar.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Can.

title: eggs and chip dish
directions: Combine all but last 2 ingredients thoroughly but lightly, so as not to break the eggs. Place in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle cheese. Top with chips. Bake at 375° until heated through.

title: veg-all chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into prepared pie crust. Cover with top crust; crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust and brush with egg.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: You can add salt and pepper to taste, but I never do.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Arrange cucumbers in shallow dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Add vinegar to cover.
Let stand at least 30 minutes; drain.
Combine sour cream, sugar, dill and pepper.
Toss with cucumber slices. Chill at least an hour.

title: fruit cake
directions: Chop dates and pecans; mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle flour over ingredients.
Mix with hands.
Pour Eagle Brand milk in and continue to mix with hands.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
(Grease pan thoroughly and dust lightly with flour.)

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Place dressing ingredients in a blender and process on low until well mixed.

About an hour before serving, place dressing in a large bowl and then add cabbage 2 cups at a time, tossing after each addition of cabbage. If using red pepper flakes, add now. Cover the bowl and chill for 1 hour, tossing every now and then.

title: chocolate covered coconut mound balls
directions: *50% paraffin; 50% bees wax is fine.

title: salsa
directions: Chop all ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil, then simmer, uncovered, for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
May use canned tomatoes but must be drained.

title: apple chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Dredge in flour and fry over moderate heat in butter and oil, until brown all over.
Add Calvados and carefully ignite with a match.
(Usually quite safe; sometimes will surprise you!)

title: tomatoes stuffed with macaroni
directions: Cut a thin slice
from	stem
end of unpeeled tomatoes. Scoop out centers; leave	outer
wall.
Reserve centers.	Cook onion, green pepper and
celery
in
margarine
for
about
5 minutes. Add tomato centers and cook for 10 minutes.
Combine with macaroni.
Season to
taste
with
salt and pepper.
Fill tomatoes.
Bake in 325° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs and mix with mixer.
Add whipping cream and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Place in freezer and fill with sweet milk.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Mix all ingredients, except the chocolate chips and nuts on medium speed until well blended.
Add chips and nuts.
Bake until lightly browned.
Cool slightly before removing to a wire rack.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 350° oven until done. Insert toothpick or knife into center of cake to test for doneness. Toothpick or knife or come out clean when cake is done.

title: franks and potatoes
directions: In medium skillet, combine milk, soup, relish, vinegar, onion and pepper.
Cook
and
stir
until
boiling.
Stir
in potatoes and wieners, heat.	Serves 4 or 5.

title: weight watcher's soup
directions: *French green beans, Chinese vegetables, bean sprouts, green peppers, mushrooms, potatoes or onions.

title: three cheeses
directions: Cook and cool the shells per package directions.
Place shells in lightly-buttered 11 x 7-inch pan.
Pour cheeses over shells. Poke gently to scatter cheeses.
Put butter over cheeses.
Pour cream over all.
Bake at 400° to 450° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Very rich.
Great served at brunch with crisp salad and chilled red wine.

title: chicken and squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion for 3 to 5 minutes.
Let drain.
Mix chicken, chicken soup, shredded carrot, squash and onion together. Let simmer about 3 minutes.
Saute stuffing mix in butter.
Layer stuffing in bottom of dish.
Pour in squash mix; cover with stuffing mix.
Place in casserole dish and cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pimiento cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or golden brown.

title: kielbasa and sauerkraut
directions: Slice kielbasa into 1/2-inch or smaller slices.
Place in large frypan.
After draining and rinsing sauerkraut for 2 minutes, add it to pan along with the rest of ingredients.
Cook over medium heat for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Add Prego sauce and let simmer. Take lasagna noodles (uncooked) and spread cream cheese on both sides and cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 1/2 of cottage cheese and spread.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Add about 1/2 of sauce mixture.
Repeat so you have two layers.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 7 minutes.
Then add last 2 ingredients and beat.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add beaten eggs, jam and buttermilk; beat well.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add to mixture.
Add flavoring and nuts; stir to blend.
Pour into a greased pan and bake about 1 1/2 hours or until done, in a 325° oven.

title: jumping fruit salad
directions: Cut desired amounts of fruit; add sugar to fruit.
Cover bowl with lid or plastic wrap; jump.
Great recipe for someone with a little helper.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for 2 hours.
Add additional sour cream if needed.
Pour dip into a hollowed out round of rye or sourdough loaf.

title: sauerkraut and meat balls
directions: Soak rice for 3 to 4 hours; drain off water and add meat, garlic, egg, cream and seasonings.
Mix together and form into meat balls.
Set aside.
Drain large can of sauerkraut.
Save water. Cook sauerkraut 1 hour.
Brown chopped onion and paprika in oil or butter.
Add 1 tablespoon of flour.
Add sauerkraut water to make sour gravy.
Layer sauerkraut and meat balls.
Pour gravy over and cook over medium heat until meat balls are done.
If you want to add potatoes to this recipe, the raw potatoes should be layered with the sauerkraut and meat balls and then pour gravy over all.

title: freezer strawberry jam
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar thoroughly.
Set aside for 10 minutes.
Stir Sure-Jell with water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir mixtures together until completely dissolved.
Pour in plastic containers.
Cover.
Let stand 24 hours.
Freeze.

title: layered antipasto salad
directions: Reserve 2 banana peppers.
Slice remaining peppers in half and remove stems.
Layer cucumbers, olives, tomatoes and peppers in a 3-quart bowl; pour 1/4 cup dressing over layers.
Top with lettuce, half of pepperoni, artichoke hearts, half of cheese strips, mushrooms, remaining pepperoni and cheese strips.
Pour remaining dressing over salad; chill.
Garnish with reserved peppers.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: grandma's chocolate pudding
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add water and milk; stir until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook until thick, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and salt.
Cool to room temperature, stirring several times.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix until smooth. Serve with your favorite vegetables.

title: e z baked chicken breasts
directions: You will need 1 medium cooking bag.

title: vegetable-beef soup
directions: Combine meat, tomato juice, onion, seasonings, and 8 cups water in soup kettle.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add vegetables, except cabbage, and simmer covered about 1 additional hour, adding cabbage last 30 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Drain chiles, pimentos, olives, and jalapenos.
Combine all ingredients except flour tortillas and cheddar cheese in blender. Spread mixture on tortilla shells. Sprinkle with cheddar cheese. Roll each tortilla shell.
Refrigerate until firm.
When ready to serve, slice into 2 inch sections.
Store any unused portions in refrigerator. These keep well.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with eggs (one at a time).
Add lemon juice, vanilla and salt.
Bake in a greased and floured
Bundt pan at 300° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: green noodle casserole
directions: Mix mushroom liquid, chicken broth, soup and cheese.
Heat to melt cheese.
Cook package of green spinach noodles in broth until tender.
Mix all together; season to taste.
Put in buttered casserole.
Add sliced pimento on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Freezes well.
Serves 20.

title: pretzel salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, combine soft margarine, sugar and pretzels.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes and cool.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, saut onion and green pepper in butter until tender. Add tomatoes, mushrooms, olives and oregano. Add ground beef if desired. Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes. Place half of the spaghetti in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with half of the vegetable mixture. Sprinkle with 1 cup of Cheddar cheese. Repeat layers.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Cool jello mixture.
Mash bananas.
Stir in the pineapple and thawed strawberries.
Add the blended fruits to the jello.
Put 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place in refrigerator until firm.
Spread sour cream over jello.
Add the rest of the mixture. Refrigerate.

title: nippy deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in halves lengthwise; remove yolks.
Mash yolks. Stir in mayonnaise, mustard, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Fill egg halves with mixture; chill.
Sprinkle with paprika before serving.
Cut olives in halves and top each egg.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach, drain and cool.
Combine other ingredients with spinach.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: shellfish cioppino
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil for 5 minutes.
Add parsley, tomato puree, tomato sauce, sherry, spices and water.
Simmer (covered) for 1 hour.
Remove garlic.
Add fish and shellfish. Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes more.
Top with steamed clams.
Serve over pasta.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix
ingredients together.
Place in 12 stemmed sherbet glasses.
Put
your favorite sauce or whipped cream on top.
A cherry may be used for decoration.

title: sugar-free strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed on box, minus 1/4 cup water, until thickened.
Thaw strawberries and crush them.
Add the Equal and let sit for a while.
Add the strawberries with the juice, pineapple, cream cheese and pecans.
Let set until firm.

title: dip a la shrimp
directions: Heat all ingredients in a double boiler or microwave.
Serve hot in chafing dish with toast points or crackers.

title: pineapple-strawberry jam
directions: Heat pineapple	and strawberries along with lemon juice and sugar.
Bring
to
a full rolling boil; cook, stirring for one minute.
Remove
from
heat
and
stir in Certo.
Stir and cool 10 minutes.
Put
into
margarine
cups.
Makes
about 5. Cover and place in refrigerator.
Not necessary to seal.
Will keep for 2 to 3 months, unsealed.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine chocolate chips, condensed milk and butter in a 2-quart glass bowl.
Microwave at Medium (50%) power for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring at 1 1/2 minute intervals.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into an 8-inch dish.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Yields 2 pounds.

title: onion soup
directions: Cut up onions and brown in butter until soft; add beef consomme and 2 cans of water.
Boil, then add lemon juice and simmer.
Boil hard and add the cheese.

title: beef noodle soup(yields 16 cups)
directions: Brown beef in oil in large soup pot.
Add water, celery, onion, tomatoes, pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil and then reduce heat to simmer.
Cook, covered, until meat is tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in mixed vegetables, bouillon cubes and noodles.
Bring to a boil and cook, uncovered, about 6 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip until smooth.
Add pineapple, apricot baby food and dry Jell-O into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with pecans.
Chill at least 3 hours before serving.

title: oatmeal pie(mock pecans)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spread potatoes in long baking dish.
Mix half of butter, soup, salt, cheese and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes and cover with remainder of butter and cornflakes.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: potato latkes
directions: Peel onions and potatoes.
Slice both.
Drain in a colander, then spread them onto a baking sheet or pan.
Add ingredients into a mixing bowl; stir together egg, flour and pepper only with spices.

title: cocoa vanilla frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute chicken and vegetables in butter and oil 5 minutes in a large soup pot; add spices.
Mix flour with a little water to make a paste.
Stir flour paste into chicken along with remaining ingredients. Simmer 1 1/2 hours. Pour hot soup over tortilla chips and top with grated cheese.
Guacamole and sour cream can also be added. Enjoy!

title: excellent cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix in blender or beat with electric beater for 5 to 10 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.
It keeps very well.

title: clams casino dip
directions: Brown onions and green peppers in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix with reserved juices.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Best served hot.

title: mud pie
directions: Crush oreos and mix with melted margarine.
Press mixture into a 9 inch pie plate.
Soften ice cream and fill pie shell. Refreeze.
When serving, top with
Kool Whip, chocolate syrup, walnuts, sprinkles, etc.

title: oreo cookies refrigerator cake
directions: Crush cookies and reserve 1/2 cup.
Mix cookies and margarine. Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate for one hour.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Mix soups and heat.
Add butter and water.
Mix half soup mixture with rice and put in bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Top with chicken breasts and cover with rest of soup mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and almonds.
Bake uncovered at 250° for 3 hours.
Perfect for Sunday lunch.
Put it on at 9:30 when you leave for Sunday School.
It's ready when you get home from church at 12:30.
May be made ahead and refrigerated.

title: chicken with rice(peru)
directions: Heat the oil and fry the chicken pieces.
In this same oil, fry the onion, garlic, salt, pepper, cumin and coriander and when it is cooked, add the red pepper strips.
Add the water and beer.
When it comes to a boil, add the rice and cover with lid.
Let it cook for 17 minutes and add the green peas.

title: janet's slaw
directions: Feed all through "Salad Shooter" with fine shredder head (or food processor, or grate by hand).
Mix with dressing ingredients. Refrigerate.
Stir before serving.

title: spicy sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef in a large skillet; pour off fat.
Add beans, barbecue sauce and peppers; cook, stirring frequently, until bubbly hot.
Makes 6 servings.
Serve over warmed hamburger buns.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook pasta to desired tenderness.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Add oil and spice mixture.
Add onion and cucumber. Refrigerate overnight.

title: champagne dessert
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar, bananas, pineapple, frozen strawberries and Cool Whip.
Add
nuts.
Freeze overnight.
Take out 1/2 hour before serving.

title: homemade irish cream liqueur
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients until smooth.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator for up to one month.
Stir before serving.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix thoroughly and put in tightly covered container.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to each cup of tea.
May be served iced.

title: strawberry delight
directions: For crust:
Crumble and smash graham crackers; put into mixing bowl.
Melt butter and add to graham crackers; mix well. Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch ungreased cake pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Soften cream cheese.
Put into large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and milk.
Mix on high speed until smooth.
Spread on top of crust and chill.
Clean and slice strawberries and mix together with glaze.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Chill for about 1/2 hour.
Spread Cool Whip on top and chill one hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Use the liquid the chicken is cooked in.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Combine butter, shortening and sugar.
Add 7-Up and mix.
Add flour, extract and eggs.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: lemon glazed persimmon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix pulp and soda.
In a large bowl lightly beat egg.
Stir in sugar, oil and pulp.
Mix dry ingredients separately and then add to wet ingredients.
Add nuts and dates.
Spread in greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and spread on glaze.

title: spicy black-eyed peas
directions: Wash
and sort
peas.
Set
aside.
Brown
sausage
and bacon pieces; drain.
Add
8 cups of water and peas;
bring to a boil. Skim off
foam
from
top.
Then add rest of ingredients, except the 3 cups of water.
Simmer 1 hour, then add the 3 cups of water and simmer another 30 minutes.
Remove the bay leaf and serve hot over rice or with cornbread.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with fork (no foam).
Add Karo syrup, sugar, nuts and vanilla.
Mix lightly.
Pour into shell.
Put in cold oven. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: date balls
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in pan and heat, stirring until mixture thickens. Take from heat and cool. Add the pecans and Rice Krispies.
Mix well and make into small balls. Roll in very fine coconut.

title: raw vegetable salad
directions: Break cauliflower into small flowerets.
Add carrots, celery and olives.
In blender, add rest of ingredients.
Blend until celery leaves are finely chopped.
Pour over vegetables.
Toss well and chill several hours.

title: miracle fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk in a large pan.
Stir and boil slowly for about 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Blend well.
Pour in a greased pan.
Let cool before cutting into squares.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: lebkuchen
directions: Cream
shortening, eggs and sugar together.
Add molasses
and sour cream and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients. Add
enough flour
to
make a stiff dough.
Refrigerate dough overnight.
Roll out dough on a floured board, 1/4-inch thick. Cut
dough
in pieces
(squares).	Place
on
greased
cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Marinate carrots in all other ingredients overnight.
Will keep 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: mom's antipasto
directions: Heat these ingredients but do not boil.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay crescent rolls out in a deep casserole dish.
Press to form a crust like pizza dough.
Bake according to instructions. Mix together sour cream, cream cheese and party dip mix.
Spread mixture over rolls.
Cut vegetables up into small bite size pieces and place over cheese mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese and enjoy.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Parboil until tender.
Cut in halves and scoop out meat.
Set aside and saute onion, garlic and celery and cook until tender. Mash pulp with ham, cheese, bread crumbs and mixture in skillet. Fill shells and cover with more bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until crumbs are browned.

title: fruit salad
directions: *All of peach juice and a little of the other juices.

title: carrot and corn meal spice cake
directions: Grease 12-cup Bundt pan.
Coat pan with nuts.
In mixing bowl, combine sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in combined flour, corn meal, baking powder, salt and spices.
Add carrots and raisins; mix well.
Pour into pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan immediately.
Cool 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: jeffrey's chicken breasts
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts lightly on all sides with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
In a large frying pan, heat together butter and oil.
Add chicken and brown lightly on one side; turn.
Add mushrooms and shallots and continue cooking until breasts are lightly browned on both sides.
Pour on wine; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes just until chicken is tender and juicy.
Remove chicken to a warm serving plate and keep warm.
Bring liquid in pan to boiling, stirring until reduced by half.
Mix in cream, cheese and paprika.
Cook over moderate heat until cheese melts and sauce is slightly thickened.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli chowder
directions: Cook onion and broccoli in salted water until tender.
Do not drain.
Stir in milk and soup.
Heat well.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Cool slightly.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in bowl; set aside.
Mix eggs, oil, bananas and vanilla in bowl.
Mix well; add dry mix and mix well. Add nuts and pour in bread loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Variation:
May
substitute
1 teaspoon grated onion or onion powder and use only 1 tablespoon butter.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
For best flavor let stand in the refrigerator one day.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: zucchini loaf
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and oil and mix.
Add zucchini and mix. Sift dry ingredients together; add to first mixture.
Mix well. Add vanilla; mix.
Fold in raisins.
Pour into 2 large pans (greased).
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until done.
Check like it was a cake.

title: chicken hash
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Remove from stove and blend in flour so there are no lumps.
Return to medium heat, add milk and stir constantly until thickened.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Add chicken and stir in well.

title: shrimp with feta over linguine
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon margarine in a heavy saucepan.
Add onion and parsley and saute until onion is tender.
Add tomatoes, oregano and pepper.
Increase heat and simmer gently until reduced, mashing tomatoes and stirring occasionally for 20 minutes.
Stir in wine and sherry.
Cook 2 minutes.
In a separate pan, melt 1 tablespoon margarine.
Add garlic.
Cook 30 seconds; don't let it brown.
Add shrimp and cook until shrimp just turns pink.
Bring the sauce to a boil.
Add the shrimp mixture and 2/3 of the Feta.
Mix until heated through.
Add the black olives. Mix well.
Serve with linguine and crusty French bread.
Top serving platter with reserved Feta.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: marinated beans
directions: Marinate beans in Italian dressing for several hours or overnight.
Bunch up approximately 6 beans in a half slice of bacon.
Continue until all beans are used up.
Place in baking dish with cut side of bacon down.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° until bacon is done.

title: mother's spicy crumb cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar, and then cut in butter as if making pie crust.
Take out 1/2 cup of the crumbs to sprinkle on top of the cake.
To the remaining mixture add the sour milk with baking soda dissolved in it.
Add spices and egg (and raisins if desired). Pour into a 13 x 9 inch greased pan.
Sprinkle crumbs on top. Bake at 325 degrees for 40 - 50 minutes.
To sour fresh milk, curdle a cup of milk by adding a tsp. of vinegar to it.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Combine dip, cottage cheese, half shredded cheese, parsley and salt.
Add potatoes, toss gently to coat.
Put in baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with remaining shredded cheese.
Bake 3 to 4 minutes more or until cheese melts.

title: party punch
directions: *Or use 1 quart strong tea.

title: shredded wheat bread
directions: Pour milk over shredded wheat biscuits and cool to lukewarm. Add softened yeast, salt, shortening and molasses.
Add approximately 1/2 of the flour.
Beat well.
Add enough more flour to make a soft dough.
Prepare as any other yeast bread.
Place in greased bread pans.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 375° and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: hot, creamy beef dip
directions: Beat cream cheese with sour cream until fluffy.
Add beef, onion and seasonings.
Turn into shallow baking dish; top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Stir ingredients in skillet over low heat about 5 minutes.
Let the mixture continue to cook, adding walnuts and Rice Krinkles or a substitute.
Roll in powdered sugar or powdered coconut.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: lemon-raspberry cake
directions: Grease 3 (9-inch) round cake pans; line with wax paper. Grease and flour wax paper.
Set pans aside.

title: philadelphia devil's food cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and shortening. Add well beaten eggs and beat mixture well. Stir flour and measure, then sift again with cocoa, soda, baking powder and salt.
Combine hot coffee and buttermilk. Add alternately with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla. Pour into three 8-inch pans.
Bake in moderate oven at 350°. Frost with fluffy cooked white frosting.

title: corn pudding
directions: Heat butter and milk until butter is melted.
Stir in corn and eggs.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: pork chop abracadabra(crock-pot)
directions: Brown the pork chops well and season lightly with salt and pepper.
Place in Crock-Pot and cook on Low 7-9 hours.
Heat and use any ONE of the above for sauce.
Pour over the pork chops and serve.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a Pyrex dish (9 x 13 1/2 x 2-inch). Lay raw pork chops on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If necessary, place under broiler a few minutes to fully brown chops on top.

title: mushroom brown rice stuffing
directions: In large saucepot, bring water and 1 teaspoon salt to boiling. Gradually stir in rice.
Cover; cook on low heat for 45 minutes, or until liquid is absorbed.
In large skillet, melt butter.
Add onion, celery and mushrooms; saute until soft.
Stir in 2 teaspoons salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Add to cooked brown rice.
Add whole bran cereal.
Sprinkle with milk; toss until moistened.
Stuff lightly into turkey.
Makes enough for 10 to 12-pound turkey.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix vanilla wafer crumbs and soft margarine.
Spread in bottom of 3-quart baking dish.
Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese or margarine.
Beat with mixer until light and fluffy.
Spread over crumb mixture and chill 1 hour.
Slice bananas round and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Layer bananas, then pineapple, then Cool Whip. Garnish top with pecans and cherries.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake in 9 or 8-inch pans.	Cool.
Make pudding and put in	icebox.
When cool enough to start layering in trifle bowl, put
one
layer of cake.
Drizzle with Kahlua.
Put 1/2 pudding, 1/2 Cool Whip and 1/2 Heath bars.
Place second cake layer	and repeat.
Much
better
if made day before serving. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate smoothies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add the vanilla and flour.
Pour one-third of the mixture into a small bowl and set aside.
Add the melted chocolate to the large bowl and mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Gently pour contents of small bowl on top of chocolate layer and top with nuts and chips.
Press in lightly.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut shelled eggs in halves, lengthwise or crosswise. Carefully remove yolks.
Mash yolks, then add remaining ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Refill whites with this mixture. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place cooked broccoli in Pyrex dish.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, margarine, egg and onion; pour over broccoli. Sprinkle top with cheese.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sauteed fresh mushrooms
directions: Rinse and pat dry and halve or slice mushrooms.
Set aside. Melt butter in a large electric skillet.
Add onion and saute for 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms and saute for 5 minutes.
Stir in parsley, lemon juice, salt and pepper.

title: spice nuts
directions: Combine sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon, cream of tartar in saucepan; add water. Bring to boil. Cook at 240° on candy thermometer, or until a little syrup dropped in cold water forms firm ball. Add vanilla and walnuts. Stir until nuts are thoroughly coated. Turn out onto wax paper or greased cookie sheet. With 2 forks separate nuts. Cool. Makes 3 cups. Recipe is from Good Housekeeping Cook Book, modified by me.

title: potato casserole
directions: Saut onion and celery in 1 stick butter until translucent. Mix potatoes, soup and sour cream and pour into baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Top cheese with cornflakes.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hr.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Fry hamburger.
Drain.
Salt to taste, if desired.
Add water, tomatoes, bay leaves, basil and soup base.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Add vegetables except green beans.
Cook until just tender.
Add green beans about last 20 minutes of cooking time. Serve.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix together vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cool.
Drain vegetables.
Add to the cooled liquid mixture. Allow to marinate overnight.
Will keep for a long period.
The longer it marinates, the better it tastes.

title: favorite corn dogs
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, onion, sugar and mustard; stir well. Combine milk and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, stirring well.
Set aside.
Wipe each frankfurter dry and insert a wooden stick into one end.
Dip frankfurter in batter.
Fry in deep, hot oil at 375° for 2 to 3 minutes or until brown, turning once.
Drain well on paper towels.
Repeat with remaining frankfurters.

title: easy oven baked beans
directions: Cook 4 slices of bacon until crisp.
Reserve 3 tablespoons of bacon grease.
In skillet, with bacon grease, add onion, pork and beans, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and ketchup. Pour beans into casserole dish; sprinkle bacon on top.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Peel and slice thin the vegetables.
Cover with cold water. Add 2 tablespoons salt and soak overnight.
Drain nearly all water off.
Mix sugar, vinegar, 1 teaspoon salt and celery salt.
Add to pickles and refrigerate.
Keeps for weeks.

title: tater wedges
directions: Bake 25 minutes on 375°.
Turn over, bake until brown.

title: lemonade tea
directions: Bring 2 cups of water to a boil; add tea bags.
Steep for 6 minutes.
Pour into
1 gallon container.
Add sugar and lemonade.
Fill with water; mix well.

title: quick banana pudding
directions: Whisk first four ingredients for a few minutes (mix well). In bowl, layer as follows:
cookies, bananas, pudding, etc. Finish with cookies.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix pudding, cake mix, eggs, oil and water.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour 1/2 cake mixture into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Put 1/2 sugar mixture.
Pour rest of cake mixture. Put rest of sugar mixture.
Cut through cake with knife.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake(from 1975 edition)
directions: Beat margarine and cream cheese until smooth.
Beat in sugar and vanilla; add eggs, then flour and baking powder.
Flour and grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: 5 cup fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit well.
Stir in sour cream.
Add coconut, marshmallows and pineapple.
Carefully stir in oranges last. Refrigerate.
Let stand overnight.

title: sugar cake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and butter until blended. Add eggs and beat.
In separate bowl, measure flour and baking powder.
In a cup, measure buttermilk and add baking soda; stir. Alternately add flour/baking powder mixture and buttermilk mixture to creamed sugar mixture until well blended in one bowl.
Then add vanilla for flavor.

title: "mississippi mud" cake
directions: Mix wet ingredients.
Add flour and cocoa.
Blend well.
Add nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes in greased and floured cake pan.
Remove from oven and while hot pour on 1 jar marshmallow cream; spread.
Let cool and frost.

title: french coconut pie
directions: *Works better if your pie crust is frozen when putting ingredients in for baking.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Mix flour, sugar, eggs and thin with the pineapple juice.
Cook until thick.
Mix with the crushed pineapples.
Top with the marshmallows and sprinkle with nuts.
Chill.

title: sausage stars
directions: Blot sausage dry with paper towels and combine with cheeses, salad dressing, olives and red pepper.
Lightly grease muffin tin and press 1 wrapper in each cup.
Spray lightly with vegetable oil. Bake wonton wrappers for 5 minutes until browning around edges or bubbles up.
Remove wrappers from tin and place on baking sheet. Fill with sausage mixture.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes at 350° until bubbly or melted filling.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in saucepan (low heat) until thawed.
Add everything but rice.
Heat good until cheese and margarine melt. Add rice.
Place in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not mix.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: blueberry surprise
directions: Mix jello and water, stirring well.
Let cool and add pie filling and pineapple.
Let gel overnight or until firm.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over top.
Garnish with pecans.

title: irish potato soup
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Place in pot and cover with water. Add salt, onion, celery and carrot.
Boil until tender.
Mix enough dry milk into liquid to complete filling the pot as full as you wish.
Mix cornstarch with water; add to pot to thicken as desired.
Let come to simmer and turn off.
Add margarine and pepper.
Sprinkle on top of hot mixture the coffee creamer and stir into soup.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix confectioner's sugar, cream cheese, pineapple and approximately 1/3 c. cool whip. Blend well. Spoon into pie shell. Top with sliced bananas, then strawberries, then remaining cool whip. Sprinkle pecans on top. Chill for 2 - 3 hours. Slice and serve.

title: italian chicken
directions: Put chicken in a bowl with fitted cover.
Pour Italian dressing over chicken.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Take chicken out of dressing; put in frying pan.
Fry slow until done.

title: belini
directions: Grate potatoes and onion.
Drain off extra liquid.
Add flour, egg, salt and pepper; mix well.
Heat small amount of Crisco oil in frying pan.
Place a tablespoon of mixture into pan, forming a circle, and fry until brown on both sides.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients, cut in shortening with pastry blender. Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to dry ingredients with buttermilk; mix well.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick; cut with round biscuit cutter.
Dip in melted butter; fold in half.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Use what you need, put the rest in refrigerator.
These will keep in fridge or may be frozen.
No need to thaw out, just place from freezer to oven.
Place 3 to 4 tablespoons butter in pan for biscuits.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken
breasts; cut meat from bones. Cut into 1-inch cubes.
Sprinkle
with
salt
and pepper.
Add oil
to wok,
pouring it around sides.
Preheat to 325°.
Add chicken cubes.
Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes or until chicken turns white. Make
well in center.
Add onions, mushrooms, pimiento and ginger.
Stir-fry
minute.
Make
well in center.
Add broth and snow peas.
Bring to boil.
Cook 1 minute.
Combine cornstarch and
water;
add
to center of wok.
Bring to boil without stirring, about 1 minute.
Cook an additional 1 minute or
until thickened, stirring rest of ingredients with sauce. Serve
with Plum Sauce or Hot Sweet Mustard Sauce.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: chattanooga cheese spread
directions: Combine Cheddar cheese and softened cream cheese; mix well until very well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes approximately 5 cups.

title: spinach onion quiche
directions: Saute onion slowly in butter.
Cook spinach according to package; drain thoroughly.
Combine onion, spinach and Swiss cheese.
Beat eggs.
Blend in milk and seasonings.
Combine with spinach mixture.
Bake pie shell.
Pour in egg and vegetable mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: avocado butter
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Mold into log and refrigerate.

title: sweet and sour hot dogs
directions: Mix mustard, jelly and butter over heat and let come to a slight boil.
Put in hot dogs and cook until they look done, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: monkey meal
directions: Peel bananas.
Spread peanut butter in the bun and put in a banana.
Cut the "monkey meal" in half and serve.

title: frozen lime parfait
directions: Beat egg yolks with condensed milk to blend.
Add juice; beat until smooth.
Pour into 4 to 5 champagne flutes.
Wrap with film and freeze.
Thaw slightly before serving.
Top with whipped cream.
Garnish with lime slice.

title: jack county fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in sheet cake baking pan.
If using frozen fruit, cook slowly for 30 minutes with 1 cup sugar.
After cooking, you should have 1/2 to 1 cup juice.
Do not drain.
Pour fruit and juice over butter in pan.
Mix sugar, flour, salt, baking powder and milk to make batter.
Pour over fruit.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until slightly brown on top and cobbler mixture is firm.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, oil, eggs, salt, soda, cinnamon, allspice, buttermilk, cooked and diced prunes and vanilla until they are well blended.
Add pecan pieces.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: venison and tomato sauce
directions: Trim fat from meat, cube and rinse under water.
In frying pan, heat oil, add meat and brown completely.
Remove meat and set aside.
Slice onion into small pieces and add to frying pan. Saute, add meat.
Add seasoning to taste.
Start with the suggested amount and add more for desired taste. Pour in enough tomato sauce to cover completely.
Add the bay leaf, cover and simmer several hours, adding water to keep from drying out.
Serve with rice.

title: feta cheese foldovers
directions: On floured pastry cloth with stockinet covered rolling pin, roll pastry into a 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Cut into twelve 3-inch squares.
Place a mounded tablespoon of filling in center of each square.
Moisten edges with water; fold pastry over filling to form a triangle and press edges together firmly with a fork to seal.
Brush tops lightly with egg mixture.
Cover and chill until ready to bake or bake immediately on an ungreased baking sheet in preheated 375° oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Makes 12.

title: super nacho
directions: In a large skillet cook meat until brown.
Drain.
Add seasoning mix and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until meat is cooked and flavors have blended.
Set aside.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix crumbs, ketchup and water; mix really good.
Add ground beef and mix well with your hands.
Shape in cast-iron skillet and top with half can of undiluted tomato soup, then dilute the remaining soup and pour around the loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients; use 1/3 cup of mixture to each cup of boiling water.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook sliced carrots until tender in lightly salted water. Marinate overnight in the remaining ingredients.

title: crabmeat au gratin #2
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until wilted.
Blend in flour. Pour in milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Add egg yolks, salt and peppers.
Cook 5 minutes.
Put crabmeat in a mixing bowl and pour sauce over crabmeat.
Mix well and transfer to lightly greased casserole.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Baked at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Add water and mix, about 1 tablespoon to 6 ounces.
Enjoy.

title: liver pate
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with 1 teaspoon parsley.

title: banana split salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and milk.
Beat well.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill until serving time.
Makes a large amount.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Lightly cook and drain broccoli. Saute onion in margarine until transparent. Combine broccoli, onion, eggs, cottage cheese, salt, corn bread mix and cheese. Pour into lightly greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until golden brown. Cut into squares.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: In large bowl, combine butter, sugar, vanilla and salt.
On low speed of mixer for about 1 minute, blend well.
Then add flour gradually on low speed until combined.
Stir in nuts.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place balls about 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until firm.
While cookies are warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool and reroll in sugar again.

title: parkway-type hot dog sauce
directions: Mix ground beef and water together and boil 15 minutes.
Add the other ingredients and cook for 15 minutes.

title: haroseth dessert
directions: Combine the ingredients and either serve immediately or chill for use later.

title: tangy meat balls
directions: Mix meat with salt and pepper, egg and cream.
Add just enough flour to hold mixture together.
Make walnut size meat balls. Melt butter in skillet and brown meat balls, turning carefully. When meat balls are browned, add chili sauce and grape jelly. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve warm in sauce.

title: bran bread
directions: Mix.
Let rise before making into loaves.
Let rise again. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 loaves.
This recipe also makes nice rolls.

title: party time beans
directions: In a slow cooker, combine the first 10 ingredients; mix well. Add the beans and peas; mix well. Cover and cook on low for 5-7 hours or until onion and peppers are tender. Remove bay leaves.

title: karen's low-fat lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne noodles according to package directions and set aside in cool water to prevent sticking.

title: chocolate cake(from the files of viola clark williams)
directions: Try 375° for 30 minutes.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Beat eggs, mix in both milks, add vanilla. Fold in whipping cream and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: oriental vegetable casserole
directions: Cook green beans until tender.
Drain and toss lightly with the rest of ingredients, except onion rings.
Turn into a 10-inch shallow casserole dish.
Put onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: potato-broccoli-meat casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain.
Blend flour, nutmeg and paprika in margarine.
Slowly add milk and stir until bubbly. Remove from heat.
Add cheeses to sauce and stir until melted. Stir in hash browns.
Turn half of mixture into greased baking dish.
Top with broccoli and meat.
Spoon remainder of mixture over broccoli and meat.
Cover; bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat across grain into 1/2-inch strips, 1 1/2 inches long. Melt butter in skillet.
Add mushrooms and onion and cook until onion is tender.
Remove from skillet.
In same skillet, cook meat until light brown.
Reserving 1/3 cup of broth, stir in remaining broth, the catsup, garlic and salt.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes. Blend reserved broth and flour; stir into meat mixture.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Reduce heat.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat and serve over noodles.

title: stroganoff
directions: While noodles are cooking, melt margarine in large skillet at low heat.

title: peanut dream pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and syrup. Sprinkle coconut and nuts in pie shell. Add syrup mixture. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: plum pudding
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Add raisins and citron. Separate eggs and beat separately.
To egg yolks, add the next 3 ingredients, then mix with dry ingredients.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Put into greased cans or bowls; fill 1/2 to 2/3 full. Cover each bowl tightly with lid or foil.
Place bowl on a rack in roasting pan.
Fill pan halfway up sides of bowls with hot water. Cover pan with roaster lid or aluminum foil.
Put into oven at 300° and leave for 3 hours.
Do not disturb.
Makes two bowls.

title: breakfast quickie
directions: Grease 9 x 9 pan. Grate Cheddar cheese and sprinkle in pan. Cook sausage; drain and sprinkle on top. Beat eggs with Bisquick and milk. Pour over all in pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Could add green chilies and canned French fried onion rings.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Warm soup, water and Cheez Whiz; mix well.
Mix with rice, broccoli and onion.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° until browned.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown and floats.
Drain on paper towels.

title: skiers french toast
directions: Melt together margarine, sugar and syrup.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice bread into 12 to 16 slices, cutting off crust, if desired.
Layer on top of syrup.
Mix eggs, milk and vanilla and pour over bread.
Make the night before and refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal, raisin, chocolate chip cookies
directions: Plump up raisins in water for 3 minutes in the microwave. Grind oatmeal in a blender or food processor.
Cream brown sugar, vanilla, eggs and oleo.
Mix soda into buttermilk and add, mixing well.
Sift baking powder with flour.
Mix in and add oatmeal, mixing thoroughly.
Add chocolate morsels and mix.
Drop.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add and beat well eggs and milk.
Add flour, cornmeal and lemon rind, then pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients into a smooth batter.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°.
Cool.
Break cake into pieces on serving plate.
Top with can of drained fruit, sliced bananas and whipped cream.
Garnish with nuts.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Blend ingredients.
Pour into greased pan.
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans; add soup and mix.
Top with onions and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: peppermint angel cake(with fat-free chocolate sauce)
directions: Prepare cake mix.
Gently fold in candies.
Pour into an ungreased tube pan evenly.
Gently cut through the batter with a knife.
Bake according to directions.
Immediately invert the pan and cool completely.
Using a narrow spatula, loosen the sides of the cake.
Remove from pan.
Slice and spoon chocolate sauce over. Sprinkle with additional candies.
Serves 12.
Calories: 228. Fat: 0.

title: pineapple frosting
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thick with juice of pineapple. Add pecans, coconut and pineapple.
Cook until thick. Spread on cooled cake layers.

title: black cherry congealed salad
directions: Bring pineapple and cherry juice to boil.
Pour over jello to dissolve.
Add other ingredients to congeal.

title: white pizza
directions: Mix together parsley, Ricotta cheese, garlic powder and Parmesan cheese.
Set aside.
Brush olive oil on pizza shell and sprinkle with chopped garlic.
Spread cheese mixture on top of shell.
Add broccoli florets (no stems) on top.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake pizza in 350° oven until cheese is melted and shell is golden brown.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Chop and mix all ingredients. Sprinkle with brown sugar to taste. Sprinkle with garlic powder, salt and onion powder to taste.
Chill, drain and serve.

title: cowboy spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef and season with chili powder and chopped onion; drain well.
Add soups and tomato sauce.
Blend together well.
Mix with spaghetti that has been cooked according to directions on the box.
Put in a casserole dish and top with cheddar cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 300 degrees until cheese is melted and slightly brown.

title: chili
directions: Fry hamburg with salt, pepper and garlic salt until lightly browned.
Pour off extra fat.
In a kettle pot, put Ragu sauce. Add chili seasoning plus Sloppy Joe seasoning and sugar.
Heat, stirring often.
Whet hot and well mixed, add kidney beans.
Add hamburg and simmer a while.

title: oyster crax snacks
directions: Combine in a bowl and stir real good.
Put oyster crax in a grocery sack and pour ingredients over.
Shake real good until oyster crax are well covered.
Ready to eat.

title: meatball stroganoff
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, egg, bread, salt, and pepper.
Makes about 16 meatballs.
Brown in skillet, pour off fat.
Blend in soup, sour cream, water.
Cover, simmer 10 minutes.
Stir now and then.
Serve over noodles.
(3 to 4 servings.)

title: chicken divan
directions: Simmer chicken breasts until tender.
Cut into pieces.
Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish with frozen broccoli.
Cover with cut up chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and spread evenly; top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Toss dressing; mix with melted butter.
Spread on top of baking dish.
Bake until heated through in a 375° oven for 50 minutes or until hot in center.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix altogether; bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together first 2 ingredients.
Spread 1/2 in bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: cabbage and rice bake
directions: Put cabbage in buttered casserole.
Cook hamburg and onion until brown.
Add rice, tomato soup and water.
Pour over cabbage and cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: "chocolate cheese cake to die for"
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and sugar; stir in butter.
Press on the bottom and 2-inches up the sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: super nachos
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain.
Add salt and Tabasco.
Spread beans in shallow baking dish.
Top with meat, chilies and cheese and drizzle with taco sauce.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Top with diced olives and sour cream.
Serve with Doritos chips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Roll in nuts and chill.

title: dabble cake
directions: Butter sides and bottom of 11 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour into pan the cherry pie filling; rinse can with about 1/2 cup water. Pour over cherry pie filling crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix over cherries and pineapple.
Cut up margarine and place on top cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour until mixture is size of peas.
Mix egg, water and vinegar together. Stir into flour until it forms a soft ball. Makes 4 crusts.

title: potato and tomato pie
directions: Preheat oven to hot (400°).
Boil potatoes and mash them until very smooth.
Mix them with the flour and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Press the potato mixture in 1/2-inch layer in bottom of oiled shallow baking dish.
Spoon half the oil over the potatoes.
Arrange the tomatoes over the oil.
Top with cheeses and sprinkle with oregano and remaining oil.
Bake for 25 minutes, until the surface is lightly browned.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat in margarine and add water.	Cook until meat is tender and add
vegetables.
Cook about 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add salt.

title: low-fat rice pilaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large microwavable bowl; cover with Saran Wrap.
Microwave on Full power for 20 minutes.
Stir and serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks light.
Add water.
Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt together and add to liquid.
Cook until thick, stirring. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and oleo.
Stir for about 5 minutes. Pour in baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites with 6 tablespoons sugar.
Place on pie filling (cooled).
Bake 10 minutes.

title: baked beef stew
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Spoon into greased 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cocoa; stir into creamed mixture alternately with water.
Stir in the sauerkraut.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Use chocolate frosting.

title: crawfish etouffee(club member: jason harvey)
directions: Melt butter; add onions and cook for 15 minutes. Add all other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: easy mock cabbage rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground chuck and onion soup mix. Mix other ingredients together and add to meat mixture.
Bake in roaster or pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Stir a couple of times during cooking.

title: wine punch
directions: Mix ingredients together and serve chilled.

title: black bean salad
directions: Add 1 to 2 Tbsp water to corn and cook a few minutes.
Drain and rinse beans.
Chop onion and red pepper. Wash, seed and mince jalapeno.
Wash, dry and chop cilantro. Drain corn and combine with beans, onion, pepper, jalapeno, cilantro and lime juice. Season with salt and pepper.
Serve with Mexican food or for a picnic.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with waxed paper.
Preheat oven to 350°. Melt margarine (1 minute in microwave in a glass measuring cup) and let cool.
Mix pumpkin, evaporated milk, sugar, eggs and cinnamon. Pour into waxed paper-lined pan.
Sprinkle dry yellow cake mix over the top.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over cake mix; pat into place. Spoon melted margarine evenly over dry mix and nuts.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: sugar-free fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Drain fruit cocktail.
Cook 2 cups pineapple juice and vanilla pudding until clear.
Cool.
Mix fruit and pudding together.
Refrigerate.

title: smothered liver
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Dip liver in flour. Brown liver at high heat, then set aside.
Brown remaining flour in skillet, then add onions and cook until the onions are clear. Add water and liver and cook, covered, about 10 to 20 minutes. Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: easy caramel popcorn
directions: Microwave popcorn accordingly.
Peel caramels and place in microwave-safe container.
Add 1 tablespoon water.
Microwave on High for 30 seconds to 1 minute, stirring every 15 seconds to prevent scorching.
Pour popcorn out on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Drizzle melted caramel all over popcorn.
Let cool slightly and toss.
Serve in parchment paper cones.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients in glass jar.
Shake until mixed well. Store tightly covered.
For a cup of tea, use 1 teaspoon of mix to 3/4 cup water.

title: annie's corn casserole(serves 12)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased (spray with Pam) 9 x 12-inch dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until done. (Can be made ahead of time and frozen.)

title: crab meat hors d'oeuvres
directions: Blend until smooth.
Spoon into a shallow dish.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: crab meltaways
directions: Slice muffins in half, then cut each half into fourths and arrange on cookie sheet.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread on muffins.
Freeze at least 30 minutes even if you plan to use same day.
May be kept for weeks in freezer.
Broil them until they puff up and are bubbly and golden brown.

title: jelly roll
directions: Line jelly roll pan with waxed paper.
Preheat oven to 400°. Sift together flour mixture.
Beat eggs and vanilla in large bowl until eggs are lemon color.
Gradually add flour mixture and water.
Beat until well blended.
Pour in already prepared pan and bake 15-18 minutes.
Turn out at once on a clean damp towel already floured with powdered sugar.
Spread jelly and roll quickly.

title: high rise apple pancake
directions: Combine eggs, flour, milk and salt. Beat until smooth.
Heat oven-proof 10-inch skillet in a 450° oven until very hot. Coat skillet with margarine.
Immediately pour in batter. Bake on lowest rack of oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°. Continue baking 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Fill and serve immediately.

title: boiled custard
directions: Place eggs in top of double boiler; beat well.
Add sugar gradually; stir in milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring frequently until mixture coats spoon.
Add butter; cool.
Stir in vanilla.
Add orange peel.
Chill overnight.
Remove peel before serving.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Cook
chicken,	large fryer, and debone; chop.	Mix all ingredients,
except
stuffing
mix, butter and rolls.
Unroll crescent rolls.
Put
triangles together to make 4 squares. Put chicken
mixture in center; pull up corner.
Pinch together.
Dip in	melted	butter.
Roll
in stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: "mean beans"
directions: In a large casserole dish, combine beans, pie filling, sausage, molasses and sauces. Mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: spanish franks
directions: Mix in order given. Simmer 30 minutes. Add franks, cut in thirds. Simmer 30 minutes more.

title: hamburger-mac bake
directions: Mix together in 2 qt. casserole. Cover and bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until macaroni is done. Toss together crumbs and butter or margarine; sprinkle atop casserole, if desired. Bake, uncovered, 10 minutes more. Makes 4-6 servings. * This has been the most popular in our family.
We often triple or quadruple the recipe for family gatherings or church potlucks.

title: franks 'n noodles
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter; saute vegetables.
Add catsup, chili sauce, lemon juice and soy sauce, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add frankfurters and simmer 5 additional minutes. Meanwhile, cook noodles according to package directions; drain. Return noodles to saucepan; stir in cottage cheese.
Alternate 2 layers each of noodles and sauce in a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a greased pan in 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: heartburn salad
directions: Dice onions, tomatoes and cucumbers in large bowl.
Add salt and black pepper.
Let set 30 minutes in refrigerator to cool before serving.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour 1/2 of batter in heated iron skillet.
Cover with 1/2 of cheese.
Top with rest of batter; cover with rest of cheese.
Bake at
375° for about 45 minutes.

title: beef tips with rice
directions: Cut beef into small pieces; roll in flour. Slowly brown on all sides. Add water and cook on medium to low heat until beef is tender. Add mushroom onion soup and simmer 30 minutes. Serve over cooked rice.

title: salsa
directions: Scald, peel and crush tomatoes.
Combine tomatoes with rest of ingredients in large pan.
Bring to hard boil.
Boil for one hour, stirring often.
Pour into pint jars.
I process mine in a water bath for 10 minutes. Yields 2 to 3 pints.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine above ingredients. Serve with crackers for dipping.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Place 1/2 cup chicken broth in a Dutch oven and heat.
Add celery and green onions, cooking over medium heat until tender. Add remaining chicken broth and heat thoroughly.
Add mashed potato flakes to thicken.
Add skim milk and baked potatoes. Continue to heat, stirring constantly but do not allow to boil. Add crumbled bacon bits.
Ladle into bowls and top each with 1/4 cup shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Serves 6.

title: southwestern spoon bread
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together all ingredients except last two. Pour batter into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with chilies and cheese.
Pour remaining batter over all.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or just until set.
Serve warm with a spoon. Good with enchiladas.

title: norwegian cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar well.
Beat in egg and almond and coconut flavorings.
Gradually blend in flour and baking powder which have been sifted together.
Fill cookie press. Form cookies in a round circle on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: c k's house dressing
directions: Fry the bacon pieces in a medium size skillet until crisp. Drain on paper towels and reserve the fat in the skillet.
Saute the bread slowly in the hot bacon fat until crisp and browned. Make the salad dressing.
Combine the salad greens, bacon, croutons and Blue cheese in a salad bowl.
Add the dressing; toss and serve immediately.
Makes 6 portions.

title: sausage medley
directions: Fix in a 10 or 12-inch skillet.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix the sugar, flour and cinnamon by hand.
Put remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Stir until it bubbles.
Add to mixture. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well by hand.
Pour into a 16 x 11-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Be sure to grease pan with oil or Crisco.
Start icing before cake is done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter to soften. Add sugar gradually and cream until fluffy. Add syrup and salt; beat well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 50 minutes.
Pie is done when knife inserted comes out clean.
This is a lighter pecan pie. If you want a richer pecan pie, use 1 cup sugar instead of 1/4 cup sugar.

title: cranberry and apple casserole
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice over apples.
Mix with cranberries and sugar.
Pour into large baking dish.
Cut margarine with two knives and add brown sugar, flour and oatmeal.
Sprinkle on top of apple-cranberry mixture and bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: roasted stuffed loin of pork
directions: Have oven to 450°. Prepare the stuffing mix according to package instructions in a bowl. Place roast, fat side up, on a clean surface. With a sharp knife, cut along length of pork loin without cutting all the way through. Open up pork like a book. Spoon stuffing down center of pork; close pork over stuffing. Tie up loin with kitchen twine, spacing twine about every 1 1/2-inches. Rub pork with 1 tablespoon olive oil. Stir together the flour, salt and pepper in a small bowl. Rub the seasoned flour mixture evenly over the pork loin. Toss together sweet potato chunks and the remaining 2 tablespoons olive oil in a roasting pan. Spread out evenly over bottom of pan. Place the tied pork loin, fat side up, on top of potatoes in the roasting pan. Roast in a 450° oven for about 10 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350°. Continue to roast 55 to 60 minutes or until instant-read thermometer inserted into pork but not in stuffing, registers 150° to 155° and potatoes are fork-tender. Let the pork rest for about 15 minutes. Temperature of pork should increase to 160°. Keep the sweet potatoes warm. Remove the twine from the pork loin before slicing. Serve with potatoes. Makes about 12 servings.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix pudding as directed on package and add Cool Whip.
Layer graham crackers in the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Top with pudding/Cool Whip mixture.
Repeat layers, finishing with a layer of mixture.
Top with blueberry pie filling and chill.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done; drain juice and let cool slightly. Dice onion and mix in mixing bowl with tuna, mayonnaise and macaroni.
Let chill and it's ready to serve.

title: easy bars
directions: Place 1 package of chocolate chip dough on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, vanilla, cream cheese and eggs.
Spread on top of dough.
Place other package chocolate chip dough on top. Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: dannon fruit and yogurt cream pie
directions: Arrange fruit in crust.
In small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over water.
Let stand one minute to soften.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is completely dissolved.
In food processor or blender, process cottage cheese and Dannon yogurt on high speed until smooth.
Add sugar and vanilla extract.
Process until well blended.
Gradually add gelatin mixture, blending well.
Pour over fruit in crust.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Garnish with additional fruit just before serving, if you like.
Yield: 8 servings.
Contains 190 calories, 3 g fat and less than 5 mg cholesterol.

title: ham, cheese and potato casserole
directions: Combine ham, potatoes and pimento in a 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Make cheese sauce by heating half and half and adding cheese until creamy. Stir constantly.
Pour over ham mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until desired consistency.

title: all-bran brown bread
directions: Combine all ingredients;
turn in 1 well-greased coffee can with plastic cover.
Steam for 3 hours in kettle.

title: no mix cookie
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Spread evenly in pan. Sprinkle crumbs, chocolate bits, nuts and coconut evenly in pan. Dribble the can of condensed milk over the mixture. Bake 350°F. for 25 minutes or until mixture begins to brown. Cool and cut in squares.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla until very fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients to blend and then stir into batter, blending well.
Stir in chocolate chips, nuts and chocolate bar.
Roll in large balls (use heaping teaspoonful) and place 3 inches apart on shiny cookie sheets.
Bake on upper rack of oven for 10 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Cookies may not look done, take out anyway.
Cool on racks.
Store in airtight container.

title: 1, 2, 3, 4 cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine together well.
Add well beaten yolks; mix well and sift dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk to creamed butter and sugar; add flavoring. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in layers at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate overnight.

title: mama's chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco together.
Add one egg at a time, blending well after each egg before adding another one.
Add sugar a little at a time, allowing mixture to smooth each time.
Add milk and vanilla slowly while mixing slowly.
Add flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder while mixing slowly.
Place in cold oven and set oven temperature at 335° and bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Put all ingredients into a 9 inch pie pan.
Mix with a fork until well blended and pat into pan.
Push the pastry up the sides and form a nice edge with your thumb and finger.
Prick the crust with a fork to prevent bubbling of the pastry during baking. If using with a no-bake pie, bake crust first	for 12 minutes at 400°.
This is truly the easiest pie crust you will ever make. Mix it right in the pie plate: no bowl and no rolling!	It is very flaky, and you can use this whenever you are are making a single pie crust.

title: baked steak dinner
directions: Place meat
in	roasting
pan;	sprinkle
with salt and pepper.
Cut vegetables in slices on top of meat.
Heat tomato sauce, lemon juice,
bay
leaf and cloves; bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Bake at 400° for 10
minutes;
reduce
heat to 325° and bake for 1 1/4 hours.
Can
also
be
layered
in	a crock-pot;
cook on low, until meat is well done.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Place soup, margarine, celery, onion and cheese in saucepan and heat long enough to melt cheese and margarine.
Mix and add rice and broccoli.
Pour all into well-greased casserole and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tuna pate
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with crackers.

title: hot dog pizza
directions: Spread ketchup on English muffin halves.
Arrange hot dog in circles.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until the cheese melts.

title: avocado dip
directions: Cut avocados in half lengthwise.
Pry out pits with point of knife.
Peel back skin and spoon out the flesh.
Mash avocados with fork, then blend in all other ingredients.
Put in blender, if you wish.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Add lemon extract and 7-Up.
Mix well.
Cook in well-greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: stuffed fish(le poisson farcie)
directions: Bake fish in a deep baking dish in hot oven, covered with foil, for 30 minutes at 425°.

title: vegetable casserole(servings:  12)
directions: In skillet, saute bacon and onion; drain.
In 10 x 14-inch buttered casserole dish, mix all ingredients, except chow mein noodles.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour.
Remove and sprinkle with chow mein noodles.
Return to oven for 5 or 10 more minutes.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish, smooth out pineapple to edges.
Add blueberries, then sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar over top. Sprinkle dry cake mix over top and chopped nuts next.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over these.
Melt butter in small pan; pour over mixture.
Bake for 12 minutes.
With large spoon, cut through cake with crisscross strokes to allow juices to come through.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes more.

title: garbanzos with dumplings
directions: Simmer onion in butter; sprinkle in flour and blend.
Add enough liquid from beans to stir smooth.
Add to beans.
Bring to a boil.
Add basil, Accent and salt to taste.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sour cream, oregano, garlic powder and pepper.
Spread in a 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Spread pizza sauce over top.
Sprinkle with pepperoni, onion and green peppers. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Top with cheese; bake 5 minutes more.
Serve warm with cut-up vegetables or crackers.

title: deacon's de-lite chili
directions: Brown ground round and pork with onions, salt and pepper. Brown round steak cubes with onions, bell peppers, salt and pepper.
Drain all grease.
Add meat to chili pot.
Mix all other ingredients.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours on low heat.
For best results, cool overnight in refrigerator and reheat before serving.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
