May alter the amount of sugar depending on the sweetness desired.
Pour into a casserole dish. Bake at 400° until mixture is solid and slightly brown.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the Crisco, white and brown sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Fold in well beaten egg and beat entire mixture.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes in preheated oven at 375°.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix together well and put in buttered mold. Cover tightly. Put in freezer until ready to use. Set out several hours ahead of serving. Serve with crackers.

title: slushie (drink)
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in freezer, about 2 days prior to serving.
Serve in tall glass, 1/2 glass of mixture and 1/2 glass of 7-Up.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar. Add eggs and buttermilk/soda.
Stir in flour, about 1/2 cup at a time.
Mix thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly. Cook in tube pan for 3 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: kitty litter cake
directions: Prepare cake mixes and bake according to directions.
Prepare pudding mix and chill until ready to assemble.
Crumble white cookies in small batches in blender.
They tend to stick, so scrape often.
Set aside all but about 1/4 cup.
To the 1/4 cup of cookie crumbs, add a few drops of green food coloring and mix using a fork.
(This makes the cat box filler look like it has chlorophyll in it.) When the cakes are cooled to room temperature, crumble into a large bowl.
Toss with half of the remaining cookie crumbs and chilled pudding.
Gently combine. Line a new cat box (obviously).
Put mixture into the litter box. Put 3 unwrapped Tootsie Rolls in a microwave-safe dish and heat until soft and pliable.
Shape ends so they are no longer blunt, curving slightly.
Repeat with 3 more Tootsie Rolls and bury in mixture in the litter box.
Sprinkle the green cookie crumbs over top.
Heat the remaining Tootsie Rolls 3 at a time.
Place on top and sprinkle with cookie crumbs.
Serve with a new, clean scooper. Makes 24 servings.

title: cajun white beans and shrimp
directions: Rinse, peel, devein and butterfly the shrimp and set them aside.
Place shrimp heads and shells on a pizza pan, drizzle on about 4 tablespoons of margarine and bake in a preheated 450° oven until toasty (about 15 minutes).
Add the heads, shells and accumulated juices to a stock-pot containing about 10 cups of water.
Bring to a rapid boil then reduce heat to simmer and cook for about an hour until about 8 cups of stock remain.
Discard the shells and heads.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan, place 4 slices of bread, broken into pieces.
Brown the sausage; cut into pieces and place over bread.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese over top.
Beat the eggs into milk.
Add mustard, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over bread and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: pineapple pork pies
directions: Prepare pastry; divide into 6 portions.
On floured surface, roll each portion into a 7-inch circle.
Fit each circle into a 5-inch tart pan; press out all bubbles.
Do not prick.
Flute edges.
Cook pork and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender; drain.
Add soup, mushrooms, seasonings and mix well. Spoon into tart shells; top each shell with a pineapple ring; sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes or until pastry is golden brown.
Garnish with bacon curls if desired.

title: chili sauce
directions: Cook; boil until thick.

title: simple hawaiian sandwich
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly butter one side of the bread slices.
Place bread on cookie sheet butter side up.
Lay ham on butter side (as much as you wish).
Place a slice of pineapple on the ham, then place a slice of cheese on the pineapple.
Bake until cheese forms a bubble over pineapple center and browns slightly.
Serve open-faced with barbecue sauce.

title: chocolate lovelight chiffon
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually add 1/2 cup sugar and beat until stiff.
Sift remainder of sugar, flour, soda and salt into another bowl.
Add oil and half of milk; beat 1 minute.
Add rest of milk, egg yolks and melted chocolate; beat 1 minute.
Fold in egg whites and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix water, sugar, Kool-Aid, lemonade and orange juice in gallon container.
Let set overnight.
Make ice ring and put in punch bowl.
Pour punch mixture on top of ice, then ginger ale. Makes about 20 to 30 nice size cups.

title: "make ahead" mexican salad
directions: Tear lettuce in bite size; chop tomatoes and onions. Layer ingredients as listed in a deep glass bowl, except corn chips. Push each layer down in bowl and cover with aluminum foil. Make salad day before to be served. When ready to serve, put corn chips on top.

title: mango salsa
directions: Cut up all ingredients and put in a bowl and squeeze ingredients. Add lime juice and stir mixture. Goes great with fish.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, oleo, salt and pepper until done.
Cook, then mash.
Mix eggs, milk, crackers and cheese.
Add to squash.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick and easy lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Stir in onion soup mix, tomato sauce and water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until thick.
Cook noodles according to directions on box.
Drain and let stand in cold water for easier separation.
In 5 x 9-inch loaf dish, alternate layers of noodles, meat sauce and cheese, ending with cheese layer.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bean soup
directions: This can be made in a crock-pot or on the stove.
Wash beans, mix all ingredients together.
Cook about 2 hours or until the beans are soft.
Add cabbage after one hour of cooking time.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening for crusts.
Add ice water as needed for right consistency.
Roll out dough to 1/8-inch thickness and cut into 5-inch circles or pinch off enough dough and roll each circle out separately.
Add filling to half of dough circle, keeping it 1/2-inch from edge.
Brush edge of pastry with water. Fold over and press edge with fork to seal.
Prick top half of pie with fork.
Heat 3 cups shortening to 360°.
Fry pies on each side for 2 or 3 minutes or until golden brown.

title: snappy bites
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing well.
Pinch off small pieces of dough and shape into balls (about 3/4 inch).
Place on baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 8 dozen.
Freezes well.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo and shortening; mix in brown sugar, eggs, sugar and vanilla. Sift and mix in the flour, baking powder and baking soda. Mix in oats, chocolate chips, pecans, Rice Krispies and coconut. Use 1/4 measuring cup per cookie (or ice cream scoop). Put on an ungreased cookie sheet, 6 to a sheet. Cook 12 minutes at 350° or until light brown. Let cool 5 minutes before removing from sheet. Rinse the cookie sheet in cold water after each cooking. Makes 30 to 40 cookies.

title: trifle dessert
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to directions; cool.
Prepare chocolate and vanilla mousse and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Mix the sugar and cinnamon together for a cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Take each quarter of the biscuits and shake real good into cinnamon-sugar mixture, covering them.
Place each quarter into 8-inch round pie pan (sides touching).
Melt butter and pour over the biscuits, then spread nuts evenly over the top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix.
When finished and still warm, poke holes in it and pour the remaining ingredients over the cake.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: tuna ball
directions: Cream mayonnaise and cream cheese together.
Add lemon juice, garlic powder, onion powder and 1/2 cup of nuts.
Mix well.
Add tuna and then make into a ball.
Roll in nuts.

title: butternut cake(aunt tera's)
directions: Cream the oleo and cream cheese.
Add the sugar, a little bit at a time.
Prepare 1 box Duncan Hines butter golden cake mix adding 1 tablespoon butternut flavoring and follow box directions. Spread the cream cheese mixture between layers and on top and sides.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine the first five ingredients.
Add milk, eggs and butter.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: fresh apple-pear cobbler
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a medium saucepan, stirring well.
Add water, stirring well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Gently stir in pears, apples and raisins.
Spoon mixture into an 8-inch square baking dish that has been coated with cooking spray.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Brown pork, onion and garlic lightly.
Add all ingredients except macaroni, salt and pepper.
Add 2 quarts hot water. Cover and simmer (not boil) 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add macaroni, salt and pepper.
Let simmer 30 minutes.
Serve sprinkled with Parmesan cheese and hot chunks buttered French bread.

title: warm crab dip
directions: Melt cream cheese over low heat.
Add 1 1/2 cups grated cheese; mix.
Add 1/4 cup wine, garlic powder and peppers to taste; mix well.
Add crab meat.
Mix.
Place mixture in Pyrex pie plate.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated cheese, then red pepper. Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: veg-all treasure salad
directions: Combine Veg-All with remaining ingredients and toss lightly. Chill.
Serve on bed of crisp lettuce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fast pot roast
directions: Wipe roast off.
Place in foil lined pan.
Sprinkle canned soup on top.
Sprinkle soup mix on top of that.
Wrap in foil and seal ends.
Bake in 350° oven for about 3 hours.
Stir drippings from pan and you have a great roast with gravy.

title: aunt hazel's summer squash casserole
directions: In a saucepan or skillet, cover squash and onion with salted water. Boil for 5 minutes and drain. Combine soup and sour cream. Stir in carrots. Fold in squash and onion mixture. Combine stuffing mix and butter. Spread 1/2 of stuffing mixture on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Spoon the vegetable mixture on top. Spread the remaining stuffing mixture over the vegetables. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: candied apples
directions: Core apples (do not peel).
May halve or quarter.
Place in baking dish with peeling side up.
Pour enough sugar on top to cover apples.
Pour syrup on top of sugar.
Slice pats of butter on top.
Cook on top of stove or in oven until syrup bubbles and begins to candy (low heat).
May take 30 minutes to 1 hour.
No need to cover.

title: "fannie's" delight
directions: Mix jello, salt and boiling water.
Chill slightly.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Re-chill.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Layer on top the remaining ingredients.
Bake for 4 hours in slow oven (250°).

title: white cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown onion and bacon. Add ground meat. Add all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Stir occasionally.

title: another chocolate chip cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream butter; add sugars, egg, vanilla and water.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda together and mix in. Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop onto baking sheet with teaspoon.
Bake 45 minutes or until brown and firm.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.
(Dough can be made in advance and refrigerated until needed.)

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Mix well.
Sift flour 3 times with salt.
Add alternately with sour cream to which soda has been added.
Fold in egg whites which have been beaten to stiff peaks.
Add vanilla and lemon extracts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: granola pudding
directions: Mix or layer.
Refrigerate overnight.
Heat at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with APPLE CREAM.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Combine pineapple and 2/3 cup sugar.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Add lemon gelatin and cream cheese; stir until mixture is combined. Let cool.
Fold in apple, nuts, celery and whipped topping.
Pour into 9-inch square pan.
Chill.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze all liquid out of spinach. Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: fudge footballs
directions: Combine and stir until well blended.
Push lengthwise from spoon, forming footballs.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes. Cool before removing.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix together and pour over 1 bag oyster crackers.
Stir well. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 225°.
Store in airtight container.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Cook
macaroni	in salt water.	Drain and coat with oil (use plenty of oil, at least 1/2 cup; this keeps the macaroni at a better consistency).

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine
all ingredients in bowl, then add eggs, vanilla, milk, oil and water.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked sweet potatoes with apples
directions: Core, peel and slice apples and fry in butter until light brown.
Slice the potatoes.
Arrange the potatoes and apples in alternate layers in a buttered baking dish.
Add the salt.
Pour the syrup over this and dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: jinny wood's baked beans
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Put in a large casserole dish or a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 450°, foil covered, then remove foil and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: roger's bean soup
directions: Use a 6-quart pot.
Place beans, ham hock, salt and pepper in pot and add plenty of water.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add diced vegetables and tomatoes and fill pot with water to 6 quarts; stir well.
Simmer, stirring once during the next hour.
Let stand a couple of hours before stirring.
Reheat. Makes 6 quarts, enough for 4 hungry eaters or a dozen dieting women.
Serve with tossed salad and garlic bread.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and
salt.
Add
sour
cream to creamed butter mixture. Turn to low speed and add flour mixture.
Mix until smooth.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Make day before serving.
Serve with your favorite vegetables.

title: mejay's banana cream pie(choudrant, louisiana)
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour in saucepan.
Gradually add milk. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Take off heat and pour part of mixture into egg yolks.
Pour all back into hot mixture.
Return to heat and cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Let cool.
Layer in pie shell, mixture and sliced bananas.
Top with whipping cream.
If you like banana cream pie, this is wonderful!

title: spareribs with orange honey glaze
directions: Cut spareribs into pieces.
Sprinkle with pepper and salt. Place into baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Meanwhile, mix all other ingredients together.
Pour mixture over ribs.
Lower oven to 350°.
Bake until ribs are juicy and tender.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: In 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole, layer green beans, noodles and chicken pieces.
Mix chicken soup, chicken stock and pimientos. Cover casserole.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: *If frozen, cook 6 minutes with 1/4 cup water in microwave.

title: three-ingredient chili(serves 4)
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Heat until bubbly.
Serve over bed of rice (brown tastes best).
One gram of fat per serving!!

title: diet oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sweetener and egg.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients, applesauce, oatmeal and raisins.
Mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until done.

title: sweet smoked salmon
directions: You will need hickory chips.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix 1 egg, cake mix and oil until crumbly, save 1 cup of crumbs
for later.
Press the remainder in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake
at
350° for 15 minutes.
Beat cheese, sugar, lemon juice and
egg
until
smooth;
pour
over the baked layer while hot. Sprinkle the cup of crumbs over the cheese mixture and bake for 15 more minutes.

title: south of the border cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dissolve bouillon in water.
Set aside.

title: cream puffs
directions: Melt butter in boiling water.
Stir flour all at one time into water and butter mixture, stirring constantly over low heat, until mixture leaves sides of pan in smooth compact mass.
Remove from heat; beat in unbeaten eggs, one a time.
Continue beating until mixture forms a thick dough.
Drop by tablespoon on greased baking sheet 1 1/2 inches apart, piling dough high.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 20 minutes, then reduce heat to moderate (350°) for 20 minutes longer.
Remove from baking sheet and cool.
Cut top 3/4 way down and fill.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: winter punch
directions: Heat and let simmer for about 30 minutes, allow red hots to melt.
Serves 20 to 24.

title: uncle milton's hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add chopped onion, then remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon into deep, hot grease where fish are cooking.
Drain on paper towels.

title: butterscotch snacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in double boiler.
Add cornflakes and peanuts.
Stir thoroughly.
Spoon onto cookie sheet covered with wax paper.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.

title: blue cheese salad dressing
directions: Heat ingredients except Blue cheese and bacon.
Remove from stove, remove cloves.
Add cheese and bacon.
Great on fresh spinach.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid with water and sugar.
Add orange and pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Garnish with cherries and pineapple chunks or make an ice ring with them using some of the punch or water.
Makes 6 gallons.

title: kim's cinnamon sugar rolls
directions: In a small bowl, evenly mix the sugar and cinnamon.
Separate each roll and cover with melted butter.
Cover the buttered roll with the cinnamon and sugar.
Bake as directed on package of refrigerator rolls.

title: kahlua
directions: Dissolve coffee in hot water.
Add sugar and cool.
Cut vanilla bean in quarters.
Put 2 pieces in each of two glass bottles.
Pour 1 cup vodka in each bottle.
Add half coffee mix to each bottle.
Seal 30 days.

title: crab imperial
directions: Beat egg.
Add mayonnaise, salt, Worcestershire sauce and wine.
Fold in crab meat and green pepper.
Place in casserole and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until set.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef and drain. Saute onion in shortening. Combine all ingredients in pot and cook slow for 3 1/2 hours.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt, butter and milk.
Boil for 6 minutes. Remove from heat and add chocolate chips, German chocolate, Marshmallow Creme and nuts.
Beat until all chocolate is melted. Pour into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Let stand a few hours before cutting.
Store in a tin box with waxed paper between layers.

title: flour dredge for chicken, fish and pork chops
directions: Sift all together.
Keep in tightly fitted container.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and cut apples (enough to cover the bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan).
Add cinnamon and sugar to apples (to taste). Combine dry ingredients, add 1 egg and half of the oil.
Cover the apples with crumb mixture and the rest of the foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 55 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake cookie dough in 11 x 14-inch pan until golden brown.
Mix the cream cheese with sugar.
Spread over cooled cookie dough. Top with fruit.
Ready to eat.
Keep in fridge.

title: cornbread salad(good in warm weather)
directions: Crumble 1 to 1 1/2 cups cornbread in big salad bowl.
Combine tomatoes, green peppers, onions, pickles and bacon.
Spoon half of this mixture over cornbread.
Stir mayonnaise and pickle juice and spread half over vegetable and bacon mixture.
Layer remaining mixtures, ending with cornbread.
Chill 3 hours.

title: oven broiled salmon
directions: Heat broiler; melt butter in small saucepan.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.

title: tangy pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Drain and run cool water over pasta.
Add next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Add cheese and salad dressing.
Chill until served.

title: cough syrup remedy
directions: Take 1 lemon; slice it thin.
Add the flax seed and water. Simmer, do not boil, for 4 hours.
Strain while hot.
Add the honey.
If there is less than a pint, add sufficient water to make a pint.
Take 1 tablespoon 4 times a day and a dose after each severe fit of coughing.

title: egg white topping
directions: Beat egg whites for 10 to 15 minutes until very stiff.
Add sugar and then vanilla.

title: buttered shrimp(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, melt butter and add onion and garlic. Microwave on High for 5 minutes or until onion is tender.
Add Worcestershire sauce, salt, hot sauce and shrimp.
Stir to mix. Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir. Cook on High for 3 minutes or until shrimp are pink.
Add parsley and onion tops after cooking.
Taste to adjust seasonings.

title: steak or what
directions: Press ground beef to 1-inch or so in a small square pan. Slice onion and put on top of beef. Place cooked, sliced potatoes on top of onions.
Drain peas and put on top.
Pour both cans of soup on top. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Chill in refrigerator until syrupy, then add fruit and 1 cup 7-Up. Refrigerate until set.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: amish pork chops
directions: Mix together and pour over pork chops.
Bake about 2 hours at 350°; turn occasionally.

title: linda's rice dish casserole
directions: Bring water to boil and add butter and rice.
Cover and reduce heat to lowest setting and steam cook for 20 minutes.
While this is cooking, slice or dice onion and peppers and put in large skillet with very small amount of water; cover to steam tender. Add hamburger to skillet and add the beef cube (crushed).
Stir until hamburger is brown, then drain.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, margarine, milk, cocoa and salt to a boil. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
With a teaspoon, drop balls onto waxed paper; chill.

title: hot chili dip
directions: Melt cheese slightly in microwave.
Add chili and cook until heated through, stirring often.
Serve with corn chips.

title: mother's caramel candy
directions: Combine sugar, cream, syrup, salt and butter.
Stir while cooking over medium heat.
When mixture starts to boil, add soda and stop stirring.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Cool 5 minutes. Beat until it holds its shape.
Pour into buttered pan or drip on wax paper.
Also makes excellent cake icing.

title: secret pal maple fudge
directions: Cook in saucepan, stirring constantly, to 240°-243°.
Remove from heat.
(Can put in butter after taking it off the stove.)
Beat until thick.
(It thickens fast toward the end and if beaten too long can be difficult to get out of the saucepan.)
Pour into an 8x8 inch greased pan.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Add tomato soup, hot ketchup, salt and dash of pepper.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Serves approximately 6.

title: no peek stew
directions: Put meat on bottom of Dutch oven. Add veggies.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over all.
Put top on pan and cook 4 hours at 250°.
Don't peek!

title: corn relish
directions: To prepare corn, boil 5 minutes. Cut from cob. Combine with remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes. Bring to boiling. Pack, boiling hot, into sterilized Ball jars, leaving 1/8-inch headspace. Adjust caps. Yield: About 6 pints.

title: prune conserve
directions: Place all above ingredients in crock or glass container.
Let stand 5 to 7 days before serving, then refrigerate.
Portion not used within 30 to 40 days should be put in containers and frozen. Serve on pancakes, waffles or French toast.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, green pepper and carrots with salt; let stand 1 hour.
Mix vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute; cool.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Put in covered containers and freeze.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cheddar, ham and broccoli bake
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions. Set aside.
In a large skillet, melt butter and saute ham, broccoli and onions until onions are translucent.
Butter a 2-quart dish.
Combine the noodles, creamy onion soup, milk, cheese packet, and the sauteed ham, broccoli and onions.
Mix well.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle the Monterey Jack cheese on top and return to oven for an additional 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: family pie
directions: Mix together smoothly with complete faith in God.
Add two tablespoons wisdom, one teaspoon good nature for flavor, then sprinkle generously with thoughtfulness.
Makes a wonderful family pie.
Will serve any size family.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine lettuce, tomato, cheese, cooked hamburger and crushed Doritos in bowl.
Mix in dressing and salsa sauce 1 hour before serving.

title: souperior italian meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine all ingredients. Put in a loaf pan.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven at 325°.
Combine ingredients, starting with eggs.
Add oil, then alternate small amounts of water and mixes until all is used.
Add poppy seed.
Pour into two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans that have been greased, and the bottoms lined with brown paper and greased again.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel apples; chop and set aside.
Pour oil in a large mixing bowl; add eggs and sugar.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla. Carefully add apples and nuts.
Grease 10-inch tube pan, which has been lined with wax paper.
Pour in batter and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix pineapple with jello.
(Do not add water.)
Add cottage cheese.
Fold in Dream Whip and chill.

title: candy
directions: Cream butter; add salt, sugar and syrup.
Flavor with desired flavoring and color.
Shape into small size balls.
Dip with chocolate and paraffin (6 to 8 ounces chocolate to 1/2 bar paraffin).

title: chicken-cashew casserole(a catchy combination of cashew nuts and chow mein noodles)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).
Lightly butter a 2-quart casserole.
In a medium bowl, combine cream of mushroom soup, Chicken Broth or water, onion and celery.
Stir to blend.
Add Chicken Mix, chow mein noodles and cashew nuts.
Pour into prepared casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Cook celery and onion in margarine until golden around edge. Cook bread cubes until golden brown with oleo.
Add seasoning.
Add crumbled cornbread to this.
Add beaten eggs to stock and pour over all.
Use more stock if too dry.
Lastly, add eggs that have been chopped.
Bake on 400° until golden brown around edges.
(This is very good.)

title: orange nut bread
directions: Squeeze juice from orange in 1 cup measuring cup.
Add boiling water to make 1 cup.
Force orange rind and raisins through food chopper, use coarse blade.
Add diluted orange juice; stir in shortening, vanilla and egg.
Add flour, sifted with salt, baking powder, soda and sugar.
Beat well; stir in nuts.
Bake in greased, 1 pound loaf pan in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Cool in pan before slicing.

title: salsa dip
directions: Microwave in a 1 1/2-quart bowl on High for 5 minutes (or until heated), stirring after 3 minutes.
Serve hot with chips.

title: three pepper quesadillas
directions: Cook and stir peppers, onions and cumin in butter in large skillet until tender-crisp, about 4 minutes.
Drain; reserve butter.
Mix cream cheese and Cheddar cheese until well blended. Spoon 2 tablespoons cheese mixture unto each tortilla; top with scant 1/3 cup pepper mixture.
Fold tortilla in half; place on cookie sheet.
Brush with reserved butter. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Cut each tortilla into thirds.
Serve warm with salsa.

title: hank's swedish pastry
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients like pie crust; divide into 2 strips.
Pat thin on cookie sheet.
In large pan, boil water and oleo.
Add flour.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, and flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Ice when cool.

title: cheese chowder
directions: In Dutch oven, cook vegetables until tender in butter and water.
Add chicken broth; mix milk and flour.
Add cheese. Simmer.

title: onion cake
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; discard drippings and cook onions in butter until tender.
Cool.
In bowl, combine flour, salt, sour cream and eggs.
Stir in bacon and onions.
Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Separate crescent roll dough into 4 parts.
Pat dough in pan an inch on sides, also.
Pinch edge together to seal.
Pour mixture into pan over dough.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until the topping is set and crust is golden brown.
Cool slightly before cutting into small squares.

title: orange icing
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add juice and rind of orange and beat until creamy consistency for spreading is reached.

title: 7-up salad
directions: In a deep bowl, dissolve Jell-O with hot water. Add cream cheese. Stir until dissolved and creamy. Add sugar and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients. Chill well or overnight.
This is a very firm Jell-O.

title: stuffed squash(green peppers, small eggplant)
directions: Cut stems and scoop out seeds of squash.
Wash.
Mix the washed rice, lamb and spices together.
Stuff squash with mixture, but do not pack too tightly.
Arrange in saucepan.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Add enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium low and cook for 25 minutes.

title: pasta sauce raphael
directions: My mom cooks it. She cooks it the way she likes to.
She cooks it back and froth.
She cleans up and she cooks everything and then she vacuums!

title: meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients.
Form into balls.
Arrange in baking dish.
You may freeze or prepare meatballs from this point.

title: cracklin' corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together 3 times.
Mix in everything else in order.
Heat a 9-inch iron skillet in a 375° oven with the bacon grease in it.
Pour batter in the piping hot skillet.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
If using a long (9 x 17-inch) iron skillet, make 3 recipes to fill it.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, margarine, sugar and vanilla well with mixer.
Add 1 cup coconut.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cover top with marshmallows and brown in oven.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Beat all the ingredients until smooth.
Add zucchini and mix together, then pour into tube pan.
Bake 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: chewy cookies
directions: Mix together well brown sugar, shortening, vanilla, salt and eggs, then add flour sifted with baking powder.
This makes a very stiff dough.
Spread on a greased cookie sheet.
Press chopped nuts into it.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
They will seem slightly underdone but should be golden when cool.
Cut into strips before they cool.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Put all ingredients except butter into a large mixing bowl. Melt butter and pour over other ingredients
in bowl.
Mix well. Shape into small balls or any shape desired.

title: stuffing
directions: Mix together all ingredients, adding water and butter last. Fill both cavities of turkey 2/3 full.
This makes a lot!
You can use the small bag of stuffing and cut all ingredients in half.

title: mocha drink mix
directions: Mix 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan except vanilla and soda.
Boil and stir constantly until thick.
Let set 5 minutes without stirring. Add vanilla and stir well.
Stir in soda.
Pop popcorn (6 quarts). Pour mixture into popcorn.
Add peanuts; stir.
Bake for 1 hour at 250° in large pan.

title: brunswick stew *
directions: Cover hen with water and simmer until meat begins to fall off. Remove from broth and cut or shred meat.
Save broth (approximately 1/2 gallon) to use for cooking vegetables.
Fresh or frozen vegetables may be used. When vegetables are tender, add chicken and other ingredients. Corn should be added toward end of cooking time since it tends to stick.
Simmer chicken and vegetables about 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Add handful macaroni during last 15 minutes for thickness.
Serves 8 to 12 people.
Stew may be frozen.

title: bit of cinnamon cake
directions: Melt butter or oleo, cocoa and milk and bring to a fast boil, stirring constantly. Pour into a bowl with powdered sugar and add nuts and vanilla. Mix thoroughly and pour on the hot cake.

title: spaghetti sauce and meatballs
directions: Brown garlic and salt pork being careful not to burn it or your sauce is ruined before your start.
Blend paste and water. Add to salt pork. Add tomatoes. Grate the Romano cheese, adding to sauce 1/3 cup. Simmer slowly for 4 hours.

title: cooked sauce for potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in saucepan over medium heat.
Stir constantly until sauce comes to a boil.
Makes about 1 pint.

title: linguini and scallops
directions: Steam scallops and season with salt, pepper and garlic salt. Prepare noodles; make sure that they are no longer than 4 inches each.
(It makes stirring in the cheese quite difficult if they are too long.)
Add cheese to noodles and stir until melted.
Add milk as a thinner.
Add scallops last.

title: hawaiian supreme cake
directions: Sift cake mix and pudding together; add eggs, one at a time. Add oil, then 7-Up.
Mix together and pour into three 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked clam dip
directions: In frying pan over low flame, melt 1 stick margarine.
Stir in 1 small, minced onion until onion is tender.
Stir in Tabasco sauce, pepper, garlic powder, oregano, and lemon juice.
Heat to simmer.
Add bread crumbs; stir in.
Add Mozzarella until melted. Serve warm with crackers or tortilla chips.
Can be made ahead and reheated in microwave.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces on a greased cookie sheet, salt and pepper if desired.
Spoon 1 to 1 1/2 tablespoons of salsa over chicken.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes, remove pan from oven and place strips of Mozzarella cheese over cooked chicken and allow to melt.

title: pecans in the microwave
directions: Melt butter, cinnamon and brown sugar 1 minute on High in microwave.
Add 4 cups of pecans.
Stir to mix.
Microwave on High 2 1/2 minutes.
Put on cookie sheet to cool.

title: 90 minute dinner rolls
directions: Mix 3/4 cup flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Heat milk, water and margarine at 120° to 130°.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer.
Add 1/4 cup flour and beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir enough additional flour to make soft dough.
On floured board, knead 2 to 3 minutes.
Shape into balls.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen rolls.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in the Crisco; set aside.
Beat the egg and vinegar or lemon juice in a cup, then fill rest of cup with water.
Mix together; mix with fork until mixture is consistent.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
(Will keep for a month.)

title: greek rice pudding
directions: Heat milk on top of stove.
When milk is hot, add rice and boil slowly until rice is tender and pudding is thickened.
Add sugar and vanilla and heat until sugar is dissolved.
Remove pan from heat.
Beat eggs and stir a little of the hot rice mixture into them.
Pour this into rice mixture and replace pan on heat and stir until creamy.
Remove from heat and pour into a bowl or individual dishes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and allow to cool.
Pudding may be eaten warm as well as cold.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Saute beef and onion in margarine until beef is done and onion is clear.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Mix in milk, eggs and Worcestershire sauce together.
Add 1 cup cheese.
Combine with beef mixture.
Pour into pastry shell.
Sprinkle 1 cup cheese over top.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mom's salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Shape into patties. Put in hot skillet with 1/8-inch cooking oil.
Brown and turn. Brown other side.

title: pineapple yam bake(no fat)
directions: Mash yams until smooth.
Preheat oven to 400°. Mix drained pineapple and 3 tablespoons of syrup into yams.
Spoon into a 9-inch round or 8-inch square, nonstick baking pan.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon of syrup and beat until stiff.
Spread with spatula using a swirling motion on top of yam mixture.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: roasted balsamic onions
directions: Peel 4 large onions.
Leave root end on.
Cut into 6 sections; do not cut all the way through. Put in greased baking dish.
Cover with vinegar, olive oil, thyme, basil salt and pepper mixture.
Cover, bake 450° for 25 minutes.
Uncover, bake for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: crab dip plate(very simple recipe)
directions: On a large plate, layer the cream cheese and crab meat.

title: orange gelatin dessert
directions: Make jello according to instruction on box (using 2 cups less water than required). When jello is particularly jelled, place juice from pineapple into blender along with the cream cheese. Blend just long enough to get the lumps out about 6 seconds. Then pour cream cheese, pineapple and cool whip into jello mixture and mix well. Together with spoon. Pour into desired dish or mold. Chill for at least 12 hours.

title: pineapple lemon pie
directions: In saucepan, mix Jell-O, pineapple and sugar. Heat until Jell-O melts and just begins to bubble; let cool. Beat evaporated milk and lemon juice until stiff. Fold into Jell-O mixture, then pour into baked pie shell. Chill until set firm.

title: ground beef gravy
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until all redness is gone from beef. Drain off fat.
Add 2 cups water and beef cubes.
Bring to boil, then lower heat.
Make thickener by mixing together 1/4 cup water and cornstarch in a cup.
Mix until smooth.
Add this slowly to ground beef, stirring constantly until desired consistency.
Add Gravy Master (optional), salt and pepper.
Simmer on low heat about 3 minutes.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Peel banana and cut into chunks.
Place banana, milk, vanilla, honey, and ice into blender or food processor.
Blend until mixture looks smooth, about 4 minutes.
Stir with a wooden spoon to check that all ingredients are thoroughly mixed.
Serve in tall glasses.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain on paper towels.
Saute onion and garlic until soft in pan drippings.
Sprinkle chili powder into pan and cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, breaking up with spoon, and kidney beans.
Stir in ground beef; simmer, un1overed, for 15 minutes.

title: sloppy joe pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°. In large nonstick skillet, brown beef; drain off fat. Put back in skillet and add barbecue sauce and onions; heat thoroughly. Put onto pizza crust and sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes until cheese is melted. Also leftover beef (shredded) can be substituted for ground beef and bell pepper and vegetables may be added if desired. Very versatile dish.

title: avocado dip
directions: Combine avocado, 3 tablespoons picante sauce and lemon juice. Stir well. Add tomatoes and stir in. Spread in bottom of shallow dish.
Top with olives and sour cream all over top. Spoon picante sauce over top of that and then add cheese. Serve with chips.

title: frozen cucumber relish
directions: Wash and cut cucumbers thin.
Dice rest of vegetables.
Pour vinegar, sugar and salt over vegetable mixture; let set awhile. Stir several times.
When juice is drawn (4 hours or overnight), package and freeze.
To thaw, thaw in refrigerator.
Cucumbers will be crisp when thawed.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon and spice; mix well. Add pumpkin; stir for thorough mixing.
Add eggs.
Beat lightly with rotary beater or fork.
Gradually add in evaporated milk and milk.
Place pie shell on oven rack.
Pour in mixture.
Cover edge of dough with foil.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375°.
Remove edge foil and continue baking for 25 minutes, or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
May be topped with whipped cream.

title: almond pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add flour and eggs (begin and end with flour).
Add flavorings and bake in a buttered and lightly sugared Bundt pan for 55 minutes at 325°.
Yield:
1 Bundt cake.

title: catherine's shipwreck
directions: Arrange ingredients in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish in layers, beginning with meat and topping with tomatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add tomato soup and 1 soup can of water. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350° or 2 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Grease and flour cake pan.
Combine first 9 ingredients and boil for 3 minutes.
Cool.
When cool, add 1 teaspoon baking powder sifted with 2 cups flour.
Last, add 1 teaspoon soda dissolved in a small amount of hot water.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted in cake. "Does nicely in a tube pan."

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased 6 x 10-inch dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together with fork until crumbly and sprinkle over apples.
Melt and cool 1/3 cup shortening and pour over top. Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: crunchy parmesan chicken
directions: Combine onions, cheese, bread crumbs and seasonings, mixing well.
Combine egg and milk.
Dip chicken pieces in egg mixture; coat well with crumb mixture.
Place in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish; spoon margarine over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until golden brown.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan and boil hard for 1 minute. Cool and spread on bars or cake.

title: indonesian coconut slices
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add flour and soda.
Then add coconut and extract.
Form into rolls 1 1/2 inches wide.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate.
Then place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes, just until lightly browned.
Do not overbake!

title: caramel pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add 1 cup sugar, cornstarch, milk, salt and vanilla.
Heat to almost boiling, then add 3/4 cup sugar which has been caramelized.
Beat egg whites, adding 6 tablespoons sugar. Place mixture in baked pie crust, then add meringue.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter together.
Mix in powdered sugar until mixture can be made into balls, but not sticky.
Chill.
Form into balls; store in refrigerator.

title: chicken broccoli bread
directions: Combine chicken, broccoli, cheese, mayo and dill. Roll out crescent rolls. Slice sides, then put mixture in center. Take up sides and braid down center. Brush top with egg white and sprinkle almonds on top. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: tea time tassies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill 1 hour.
Roll dough out and cut with 2 1/2-inch cutter to fit in miniature muffin pans.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugars and eggs and beat well.
Sift flour and add gradually to mixture.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Fold in nuts and apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Mix and spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: ruth miller's macaroni salad
directions: Mix together with 1 pint Miracle Whip, 1 cup sugar and 2 to 3 tablespoons vinegar.

title: cake-pie crunch
directions: Empty pie filling into 9x13 pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pie filling.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over cake mix.
Pour melted butter or margarine over top.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Saute onion in oil; set aside.
Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain and set aside.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix dry corn bread mix with 4 eggs.
Combine cottage cheese, broccoli, onion and melted margarine with corn bread mix; stir well.
Pour into pan in which margarine was melted.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: turkey ala king
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Blend in soup and milk.
Heat slowly, stirring often.
Add cheese and mustard.
Serve on toast, patti shells, rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: broiled banana split
directions: Place 1/2 split banana in each of 4 flameproof dishes. Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and fine apple, then nuts.
Dot with margarine.
Broil 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream, ice cream or yogurt.
Serves 4.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well. Pour mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: noodle bake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn vegetable medley
directions: In saucepan, heat soup and milk to boiling, stirring often. Stir in vegetables.
Return to boiling.
Cover; cook over low heat for 20 minutes, or until vegetables are tender, stirring often. Stir in cheese.
Heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: maple nut ice cream
directions: At room temperature, beat eggs slightly.
Mix white sugar and flour and add to eggs.
Scald 2 quarts half and half (DO NOT BOIL), then add small amount scalded half and half to sugar, flour, egg mixture - VERY SLOWLY.
Take this and add back into scalded half and half.
Heat, stirring constantly until almost coats wooden spoon.
MUST USE WOODEN SPOON.
Remove from heat.
Add immediately 2 1/4 cups light brown sugar to half and half mixture.
Add 2 quarts half and half to stop cooking process.
Cool in refrigerator.
Place in ice cream freezer and crank until mixture begins to freeze.
Add remaining ingredients to partially frozen ice cream and crank until frozen.

title: muffin jewels
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
With fork, cut shortening to form fine particles. Add milk and eggs.
Mix just until evenly blended.
Spread batter evenly into muffin pan and put any kind of jam on top (1 teaspoon).
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: divinity candy
directions: Combine pudding mix, margarine and water in a saucepan.
Bring just to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in sugar, blending well.
Add nuts.
Pour into oiled pan (8 x 4-inch loaf pan).
Chill, then cut into squares.

title: plunk-in-cake
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and cinnamon and pecans.
When it begins to boil pour over cut frozen rolls.
Stir together then put in greased Bundt pan.
(Follow directions on rolls to cook.)

title: cloud nine salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except jello.
Sprinkle jello over the top and stir together thoroughly.
Chill before serving.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Spray 8 x 8-inch pan with Pam.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions; can substitute some of water called for in cake mix with pineapple juice.
Pour batter in pan.
Mix pineapple and lemon pie filling.
Drop spoonfuls of pineapple lemon mixture over top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° until tests done.
Good, good, good!

title: hot apple cider
directions: Place spices in basket of percolator and dissolve brown sugar in apple juice in percolator and let perk.

title: lemon velvet cake
directions: Mix cake and dry Jell-O together.
Add water and mix.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time; add cooking oil last and mix.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked pork chops and apple-walnut stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare stuffing per package instructions.
Add apple slices and walnuts.
Place chops in baking dish.
In a bowl, mix dry soup mix and water.
Pour over chops. Cover and bake 45 minutes.
Uncover. Top each pork chop with scoop of stuffing. Cover and bake 15 minutes more.
Serve with your favorite "colorful" vegetable.

title: norwegian sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla together until fluffy. Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture. Make walnut size balls and dip in granulated sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together except nuts, form into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Combine flour, mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard, salt, cayenne and water in top part of double boiler.
Mix in eggs and cook, over simmering water, until thickened. Put in refrigerator until cold. Fold into whipped evaporated milk.
Mix with remaining ingredients and chill.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and vanilla together.
Add egg and milk; stir.
Add dry ingredients.
Divide dough in half.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
On lightly floured surface roll to 1/8 inch thickness.
Cut out and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°. For drop sugar cookie, omit 1/2 cup flour.

title: sugar-free cheese pie
directions: Beat together first 3 ingredients.
Fold in pudding mix. Spoon into pie shell.
Chill and serve.

title: corn pudding
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oleo for 5 minutes.
Add all ingredients to muffin mix.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in casserole at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecue baked potato
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer potatoes, flour, onions and half of the cheese.
Combine last four ingredients over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Stir gently and sprinkle remaining cheese and bacon.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Mix all together at high speed until smooth.

title: pickle surprise
directions: Drain juice off pickles and cut pickles into chunks.
Put remaining ingredients over pickles and put back in jar.
Cover with lid and put in refrigerator and let set a few days.
Turn the jar over once in a while to mix juice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on box. Add all ingredients except paprika and cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased, shallow 3-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Freezes well. When frozen, remove from freezer at least 4 hours before heating. Serve with mixed green salad and hot rolls or corn bread.
Yields 12 servings.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool before frosting.

title: steak pizzaiola
directions: Take chuck steak and cut into pieces to fit in saucepan.
Mix tomatoes with garlic, oregano, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour a little tomato mixture on the bottom of pan.
Place steak and rest of tomato sauce in pan.
Cover and cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, over low heat, until steak is tender.
Serve over macaroni.

title: one-dish taco supper
directions: Line a greased 9x13 pan evenly with biscuits; press to flatten biscuits and seal together, bringing biscuits 1 in. up sides of dish.
Bake at 375 degrees for 5-6 minutes or until lightly browned.
Set aside.
Brown beef in a large skillet; stir in seasoning mix and water.
Spread beef mixture over biscuits; sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes or until biscuits are golden.
If desired, spread sour cream over cheese; sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Cut into squares and serve immediately.
Yield: 6-8 servings.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Spray shallow glass dish with Pam.
Cover dish with enchilada sauce.
Roll or stack tortillas with grated cheese and onions covered with enchilada sauce.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with lettuce and tomato on top.
Add hot salsa to taste.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Do not add any salt to this!

title: chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Pour hot water over chocolate and butter.
Let cool and add vanilla; stir.
Sift flour, salt, sugar and soda.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Bake in greased and floured pans at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: montgomery inn beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine onion and bacon in skillet and saute until onion is transparent, then remove from stove.
Combine beans, mustard, brown sugar and barbecue sauce in a large mixing bowl, then mix all of this together thoroughly.
Add onion and bacon to the ingredients in mixing bowl and mix thoroughly.
Put all of this into an uncovered baking dish in oven and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: pecan dainties
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Stir flour and pecans into batter mixture.
Chill dough, then shape into marble-size balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 to 17 minutes, until firm, but
not brown.
Roll gently in confectioners sugar.
Cool, then roll in sugar again.
Makes 50.

title: apple nut coffee cake
directions: Combine.
Sprinkle nut mixture evenly over batter before baking.

title: salmon pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta following directions on package.
Drain and chill. In a large bowl, combine pasta, red pepper, celery, squash, onion and salmon. Add dressing. Toss until mixed.
Chill salad. Garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix together caramels and 1/3 cup of evaporated milk.
Melt over low heat on stove in saucepan, stirring occasionally.
Mix together the cake mix, margarine and 1/3 cup evaporated milk; press half of this mixture into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes, then take 1 cup chocolate chips and spread on top of baked cake.
Spread caramel mixture on top. Take the other half of the cake mixture and drop by spoonfuls on top of caramel layer.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Bake at 500° until corn pops.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Heat drippings in small iron skillet over low (300°) heat. Sprinkle flour over drippings and brown.
Add stewed tomatoes with liquid.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook slowly for 3 to 5 minutes. Serve over hot buttermilk biscuits or rice.

title: zucchini-corn bake(this is an original recipe, developed july 1988)
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in margarine in large skillet with lid, slowly.
Cook corn in margarine with just enough water to obtain doneness, until water evaporates.
Combine in shallow baking dish; sprinkle with French fried onions and Parmesan cheese.
Preheat oven to 400° and bake quickly, about 5 minutes, watch to see that onion topping is not too done (burned!).
Serve as a main dish or side dish with chicken, etc.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: good morning casserole
directions: Beat eggs well; add milk, salt, pepper, mustard and Picante sauce.
To this mixture, add crumbled toast and sausage.
Place in 8 1/2 x 13 pan; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45-55 minutes.

title: green chili-cheese rice
directions: In saucepan, bring water to boil.
Add rice, salt and butter. Turn heat to low; cover and cook 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Add sour cream, cheese and chilies (to taste) to rice; mix thoroughly. Pour into lightly greased casserole.
Sprinkle paprika on top. Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts and all is bubbly and hot, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: oatmeal caramelites
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine flour, oats, brown sugar, soda, salt and melted butter.
Blend at low speed to form crumbs.
Press 1/2 of mixture into bottom of 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with chips and nuts; blend topping with flour and pour over chips and nuts to cover. Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Continue baking for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Chill.

title: daffodil cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in center of flour mixture and add the following in order: oil, egg yolks, orange juice and vanilla. Beat with spoon until smooth.
Beat separately the egg whites and cream of tartar. Beat until very, very stiff.
Pour egg yolk mixture gradually over whipped whites. Fold with spatula just until blended. Do not stir. Pour into 3 ungreased 8-inch round pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: southern sweet potato cake
directions: Flour and grease tube pan.
In large bowl, cream sugar, 1 cup margarine and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each egg.
Cut up yams.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add flour, cinnamon, soda and nutmeg; mix well. By hand, fold in nuts, raisins and well-drained pineapple.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes or until done.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Cook frozen broccoli; put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil chicken breast until done; lay on top of broccoli.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and mayonnaise together and spread over chicken.
Grate sharp Cheddar cheese; put on top, then add bread crumbs.

title: my chili
directions: Fry hamburg, crumbled.
Drain and place in slow cooker. Slightly fry onions and green pepper.
Add to hamburg.
Add remaining ingredients in slow cooker.
Cook for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: eggs with cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter in a small saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, salt and pepper; stir until well blended.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened and smooth.
Add mustard and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Arrange two halves on each slice of toast.
Top with cheese sauce.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Serves 2.

title: never-fail microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together the sugar, syrup, peanuts and salt, mixing well.
Microwave at High for 6 to 9 minutes until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla and stir well. Microwave at High 1 to 2 minutes more.
Peanuts will be light brown and syrup will be very hot.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour into lightly buttered cookie sheet. Let cool 30 to 60 minutes. When cool, break into small pieces.

title: breakfast bars
directions: Place in medium bowl the first 5 ingredients. Pour buttermilk, eggs and margarine over dry ingredients.
Beat very lightly on low to mix.
Fold in nuts, figs and currants briefly with rubber spatula.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
These freeze well and are loaded with fiber.

title: molded salad
directions: Boil sugar and pineapple 3 minutes; dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, then stir in pineapple until it slightly congeals, then add cheese, nuts and a few maraschino cherries for color if desired. Add topping last and refrigerate.

title: low-fat chicken and pasta with spicy italian vegetable sauce
directions: Heat a large, nonstick skillet or one coated with cooking spray.
Add chicken.
Sprinkle with black pepper and paprika and stir-fry over medium-high heat until chicken is cooked through, about 5 minutes.
If chicken starts to stick, add a little of the tomato juice.
Remove chicken to a plate.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Combine raisins, water, jelly, orange peel and orange juice in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, ground allspice and salt.
Stir into orange mixture.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Serve warm with cooked ham.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: black bean soup
directions: Make a dark roux (1/4 cup flour and 1/4 cup oil).
When dark, add finely chopped red pepper, celery, carrot, onion and mushrooms.
Cook until just done, then add black beans, bouillon cubes, dark stock, tomatoes, garlic, salt and Cajun seasoning to taste.

title: one dish meal
directions: Insert steamer in large pan or pot.
Fill pan or pot to bottom of steamer with water.
Add carrots, potatoes, onions, celery, cabbage and corn.
When water boils, reduce heat and cook, covered, until carrots and potatoes are tender.
Remove to platter and sprinkle with Molly McButter or salt and pepper.
If sausage is used, place on top of vegetables to cook.
Serves two.

title: christmas salad
directions: Make jello as directed on box. Let congeal to soft stage.
Mix rest of ingredients. Pour in mold and congeal.

title: quick cheesy pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in bottom of Pyrex dish.
Cover with sliced potatoes.
Mix 2 cans soup and pour over potatoes.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until pork chops are tender.

title: creole cabbage or cajun slaw
directions: Melt beef bouillon cubes in just enough boiling water to cover, then set aside to cool.
Shred cabbage (as for slaw).
Toss in minced garlic (also minced onion if you like).
Add basil and thyme (I use about 1 tablespoon each but you can use less to start and add to taste).
Pour in the bouillon and apple cider vinegar or red wine vinegar (again, it is your choice) and toss it all together.
Enjoy!

title: batter white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
In large bowl add 1/2 flour (3 1/4 cups), sugar and shortening.
Blend on low speed; 2 minutes on high speed.
Mix remaining flour by hand.
Cover and let rise until double (45 minutes).
Stir batter, beating hard 1/2 minute.
Spread into 2 greased loaf pans.
(Batter will be sticky.)
Let rise 20 minutes or until double.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Rub butter on hot loaves.

title: refrigerator potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes in boiling salt water.
Drain and mash. Add other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: cinnamon pull aparts
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Place nuts in bottom.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Arrange in pan.
Melt butter and brown sugar.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Put butter, brown sugar and crushed pineapple in bottom of baking dish.
Mix next 7 ingredients together.
Add beaten egg whites.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: b. j.'s punch
directions: Add a bunch of ice cubes and ginger ale to fill the punch bowl.

title: tasty blue cheese salad dressing
directions: Blend first four ingredients together.
Then add the cottage cheese and remaining yogurt.
Blend well until smooth.

title: kielbasa bites
directions: Mix together chili sauce, jelly, spices, wine, mustard and soy sauce in a saucepan until mixture can be smoothly blended.
Add kielbasa and heat until kielbasa is hot.
Serve with toothpicks. Re-heated leftovers even taste better.

title: savory spinach squares
directions: Beat eggs and add all remaining ingredients.
Place in well-greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice and water until done.
Arrange in bottom of casserole dish.
Arrange on top chicken breasts and broccoli. Pour broth and soup over.
Bake for 1/2 hour covered at 350°. Bake for 1/2 hour more uncovered.
Last 15 minutes, sprinkle Durkee onions.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Mix well. Add spices, soda, baking powder and flour.
Add nuts and raisins; stir well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.
May be iced or un-iced.

title: english tea cake
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Drop from teaspoon onto a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at
350° for 25-30 minutes.
Let cool.
Cover with frosting (recipe to follow).

title: graham cracker pecan bars
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Spread mixture on graham crackers and bake at 300° for 10 minutes.

title: golden goo bars
directions: In a bowl, mix together cake mix, 2 eggs and butter.
Mix well.
Spread in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
In second bowl, mix together 2 eggs, cream cheese and sugar.
Spread over first layer.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: monkey bread(alaska pluckin' bread)
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Roll each piece in mixture of 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/3 cup sugar.
Grease Bundt pan with Crisco.
Place nuts in bottom of pan, then layers of the biscuits.

title: emma's green beans
directions: Put in deep kettle.
Add enough water to barely cover beans. Bring to boil.
Cook slow until beans are tender.
Drain water off beans and add about 1 cup of meat grease.
Let cook down slowly. Add more salt if needed.

title: cocoa(makes 1 gallon)
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients until smooth; add hot milk and vanilla.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Gradually beat in sugar until mixture is light and fluffy.
Beat yolks until thick and lemon colored (about 7 to 8 minutes).
Beat into creamed mixture.
Stir in brandy.
Beat whites until stiff.
Sift flour with mace and add alternately with egg whites to butter sugar mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into 2 buttered, wax paper lined 9 x 5 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done. Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Loosen sides of cake from pans; turn out onto cake rack and cool thoroughly.
Makes 2 cakes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all together and bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Pat the butter on top.

title: smothered okra, potatoes and onions
directions: Mix the okra, potatoes and onion in big bowl; salt and pepper. Pour flour over all and coat completely.
Heat 3 tablespoons oil in heavy skillet until hot.
Pour in the vegetables.
Turn fire down immediately and cover.
Check often and turn with spatula, adding a little more oil as needed.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all ingredients together and mix.
Chill.
Different flavors of jello
may
be
used to suit the occasion:
red for Christmas, etc.

title: potato zucchini omelet
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper in bowl.
Heat 3 tablespoons of the oil in a large skillet with ovenproof handle. Add onion and potatoes.
Cook, stirring constantly until potatoes are almost tender, about 3 minutes. Stir into egg mixture.
Wipe skillet clean.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Blend mayonnaise, egg white and 3 to 4 tablespoons crumbs in a bowl.
Add crab and fold gently.
Using wet fingers, divide mixture into 8 equal portions; shape into patties.
Coat with remaining crumbs (1/2 cup).
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: millionaire candy
directions: Melt chips and wax; stir in nuts.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper covered trays.
Chill.
Makes a small batch.

title: broccoli and chicken pasta
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Stir in broccoli, mushrooms, onion and red pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Add chicken and broth.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Place butter in pan to melt in oven.
Mix 2 cups flour and powdered sugar in butter.
Pat down and bake 30 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms; take out stems and set aside.
Mix cheese, clams (drain clams well) and oyster sauce.
Stuff mushroom with clam mixture.
Put in pan with sides.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: toffee
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line an 11 x 14-inch cookie sheet with saltines.
Melt margarine and sugar together; cook until mixture comes to a full boil (about 3 minutes).
Pour evenly over crackers.
Bake for 5 minutes or until brown sugar topping is bubbly.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over top. When chips have melted, spread evenly.
Sprinkle nuts over chocolate.
When cool, cut or break into pieces.

title: tri-color pasta salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Toss thoroughly; add salt and pepper to taste.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Toss again before serving.

title: classic butterscotch chip cookies
directions: Bake at 375°.
Yields 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: banana drop cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; beat in eggs.
Dissolve baking soda in sour milk.
Add alternately with flour and baking soda sifted together.
Stir in vanilla, nuts and bananas.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 or more minutes.
Don't overbake them.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: grandma's applesauce cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add raisins, chopped walnuts, melted butter and applesauce.
Blend well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Note: Do not salt anything.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.

title: crab soup
directions: Heat to boil.
Add 4 tablespoons sherry.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; then reduce heat to 350° and bake another 40 to 45 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Combine sugar and eggs.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately; beat well after each addition.
Add soda, cinnamon, salt and pulp; mix well.
Melt butter in bottom of an 8-inch square pan.
Add batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken. Debone and save broth. Saute onion in margarine. Mix dressing mix and onion-butter mix.
Use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Layer dressing mix, chicken and cream of chicken soup diluted with 1 can broth.
Layer of dressing mix, chicken and cream of mushroom soup diluted with 1 can broth. Top casserole with remaining dressing crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pancit(panseat)
directions: Using a large skillet or frying pan, lightly saute in a small amount of oil the onion and garlic.
Add the pork and shrimp.
Add cabbage, carrots, soy sauce and 1 cup of water.
Turn heat to medium and simmer for about 5 minutes.
Stir and simmer until carrots are cooked.
Place noodles on top of mixture and spoon vegetables and broth over noodles.
You might have to add a little more water if the noodles have not wilted.
Cover and allow to steam for about 2 minutes.
Turn out on a platter and garnish with lemon wedges.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain all water from spinach (squeeze).
Add sour cream, mayonnaise, onions and vegetable mix.
Mix well and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Cut out center of loaf and stuff with dip.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Wash and drain chicken.
Brown onions lightly in the fat.
Add paprika and the chicken.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cover and cook slowly for about an hour.
Pour the cream over the chicken and let rest for 1 minute.
Serve with freshly boiled soft noodles.

title: chocolate truffle cake
directions: Preheat oven
Grease bottom of 8-inch spring-form pan.
Melt
chocolate
and
butter in double boiler.
Add flour, sugar and water.
Stir well.
Add yolks, one at a time, beat well after
each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Fold into chocolate mixture.
Turn into the pan. Bake 15
minutes only!
Cake
will
look very uncooked in the center.
Let cool completely, then chill or freeze.
Cut cold, then let sit about 15 minutes.

title: spicy brown chicken
directions: Clean chicken.
Lay out on a table and coat with the following: salt, pepper, paprika and onion flakes.
Place into a deep dish pan.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour.
Take pan out of the oven and turn over into a new pan.
Place back into oven at 450° for another hour.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell until lightly brown.
Wash and clean strawberries.
Mix strawberries with glaze.
Pour mixture into cooled pie shell.
Refrigerate.
Serve with whipped topping, if desired.

title: s'mores
directions: Place 2 squares of candy bar and 1 large marshmallow on graham cracker square.
Place on napkin or paper plate.
Microwave on High 15 seconds for one, longer if making more than that.
Top with another graham cracker.

title: soft molasses gingerbread
directions: Melt shortening.
Mix in sugar, molasses and eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to mixture.
Add 1 cup boiling water last.
Bake in an 8 x 11-inch pan for 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry cheese pizza dessert
directions: On a lightly floured pizza pan, lay crusts in a position so they will cover all of pan.
Flute the edges and prick crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and beaten eggs. Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into partially baked crust.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Spread pie filling over cheese layer. Chill and top with dots of whipped cream.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cajun cake
directions: Drain
pineapple,
reserving
1/2 cup juice.
Set aside. Cream 1/2 cup softened butter;
gradually add 1 1/2 cups sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating
well
after
each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with reserved juice,
beginning
and
ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until
blended
after
each
addition.
Stir in crushed pineapple.
Pour batter
into
a
greased
and
floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350°
for 50 to 55 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in
center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes;
remove from
pan
and
place
on
serving
plate. Combine 1/4 cup
butter,
sugar,
evaporated
milk, coconut and pecans in a small saucepan.
Bring
to
a boil; reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon on top of warm cake. Cool.
Sprinkle with toasted coconut and garnish with pineapple slices and leaves if desired.
Yields 1 (10-inch) cake.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger.
Separately, brown green pepper.
To pepper, add tomato sauce, tomato soup and onion.
To hamburger, add cheese and chili powder.
Combine all and simmer.
Serve hot.
Serve with your favorite tortilla chips.

title: fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Spray a 9-inch square baking pan with cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine next 6 ingredients.
In medium bowl, stir sugar and water until sugar is almost dissolved.
Add egg whites and corn syrup.
Stir until blended.
Gradually add to dry ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
If desired, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 16 servings.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar gradually, beating until light.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in honey.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in nuts and fruits.
Fold in beaten egg whites.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Melt margarine in skillet. Cook onion and garlic until tender. Stir in green chilies, sour cream and soup; mix well. Reserve 3/4 cup sauce; set aside. Stir in chicken and 1/2 cup cheese to remaining sauce in skillet. Warm tortillas according to package directions. Fill tortillas with chicken mixture; roll up and place seam side down in ungreased 9 x 13 baking dish. In small bowl, combine reserved sauce and milk; spoon over rolled tortillas. Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly. Makes 8 to 10 enchiladas.

title: skillet sausage and cabbage
directions: Saute sausage in large heavy skillet over medium heat until brown; drain on paper towels.
Add onion and bell pepper to skillet and saute 2-3 minutes, add cabbage and cook about 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add remaining ingredients, reduce heat and cook until cabbage is tender.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 375° about 40 minutes.

title: margy's kisses
directions: Beat eggs until soft peaks form.
Slowly add sugar, beating constantly until it's a thick and glassy mixture that holds its shape.
Fold in nuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from sheets at once.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper until wilted.
Add cream cheese and crabmeat, stirring until cheese melts (cheese may be lumpy).
Add soups; mix well and add rice.
Pour into a casserole dish and top with bread crumbs and Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate orange cake
directions: Combine cake mix in large bowl with other dry ingredients.
Add unbeaten eggs, water, orange juice, oil and orange flavoring.
Beat for 5 minutes using spatula to push batter down sides of bowl. Pour two-thirds of batter into well-greased Bundt pan.
Add the chocolate syrup to the remaining batter (1/3rd).
Mix well and pour over the batter in Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated oven of 350° for 1 hour and test with toothpick.
May need another 10 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before inverting on a board dusted with xxxx sugar or make a thin frosting of xxxx sugar and orange/lemon juice and drizzles over cake and down sides.

title: no fat roux
directions: Heat black iron skillet with flour; stir constantly with a wire whisk about 25 minutes, or until the flour gets to a light brown color.
Remove from heat; continue to give it a stir from time to time until it is completely cooled down.
When cool, sift it into a container and store covered until needed.
Will keep for 2 to 3 months.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Mix together and spread over crust; chill well and cut into squares.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Cream
shortening
and	sugar
until
fluffy.
Add
egg yolks, one
at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition. Stir dry ingredients
together 3 times.
Add alternately with milk and vanilla
to
creamed
mixture, beating until smooth, after each addition.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) pans.
Bake 25 minutes in 325° oven.

title: sour cream and onion chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Skin chicken and place in baking dish. Quarter potatoes and place around chicken, as well as the mushrooms. Top each piece of chicken with a generous tablespoon of butter. Sprinkle entire baking dish with 1 envelope of dry onion soup mix (may need more than one package if cooking for a large number of people). Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes. Turn oven down to 250° and cook another 2 hours.

title: tacos
directions: Saute onion and pepper in small amount of oil.
Add meat and brown.
Add ketchup, chili powder, A.1 sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to taste, Texas Pete and garlic.
Simmer slowly. In small saucepan, heat oil until very hot.
Then drop in one tortilla at a time.
As soon as it hits the bottom, fold in half with a fork and remove.
Drain on paper towel.
Line all fried tortillas into baking pan.
Fill each with some meat mixture and top with cheese.
Put in oven long enough to melt cheese.
Top with cut up lettuce and tomatoes.
Use Texas Pete and ketchup on top.

title: mexican wedding balls
