directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, salt
and cream well.
Add flour and nuts.
Shape into balls.	Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350 degrees for 12-15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: bacon and tomato dip
directions: Cook, drain and crumble bacon.
Peel, seed and chop tomato. Finely chop green pepper and onion.
Stir all ingredients together.
Cover and chill.
Serve with vegetables.

title: deep-fried fish
directions: Heat enough oil to cover fish at least 1-inch to a temperature of about 375°.
Meanwhile, dip fish in a mix of cornmeal and seasoned flour; then in the egg and then again in the meal-flour mixture.
Fry for 3 to 6 minutes or until browned.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Use 2 or 3 teaspoons in a cup of boiling water.

title: fudge
directions: Butter 2 (9 x 12-inch) pans.
Grease top rim of pot that you boil sugar and milk in.
Bring sugar and Pet milk to a full boil. Boil 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
In a large bowl, combine top 5 ingredients.
Pour sugar and milk over first ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 (9 x 12-inch) pans and cool.
Cut and serve.

title: appleless apple pie
directions: Boil the water with sugar and cream of tartar.
When water comes to a boil, remove from heat.
Put in crackers.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Add cinnamon and butter.
Bake 25 minutes at 425°.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Take first 3 ingredients and cut into small pieces.
Mix together.
Thaw peas and spread over mix.
Then spread whole jar of Hellmann's over peas.
Crumble bacon over Hellmann's.
Sprinkle both packs of Zesty Italian over bacon, then cover with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and keep in refrigerator for several hours before serving.
Mix well when served.

title: turkey or chicken dressing
directions: Mix all; put into greased pan.
Cook at 300° for 1/2 hour.

title: wesson oil cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 375° until brown, about 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: royal apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add remainder of ingredients. Mix all together.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake in cold oven at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: spaghetti for 100
directions: Saute sliced mushrooms and onions until transparent.
Brown meat with garlic.
Add additional ingredients, including spaghetti which has been cooked according to package directions.
(I use a bit more beef and a bit less spaghetti.)

title: corn bread cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in 9-inch square pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Very easy and very good.

title: alabama pecan pie
directions: Sprinkle pecans on bottom of pie shell.
Combine other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake 40 minutes or until filling is firm.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup sugar and salt in double boiler.
Add scalded milk.
Stir well.
Cook over direct heat until smooth and thick.
Beat egg yolks.
Add a little of the hot mixture into them, then add to hot mixture.
Cook over boiling water about 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla. Beat egg whites.
Add the 6 tablespoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Add 1/3 to cooled filling and 1/2 cup coconut. Top with remaining meringue.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 12 minutes.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Generously grease Bundt pan.
Melt bars and syrup.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, salt, soda and buttermilk until well blended.
Add bars and syrup.
Mix well. Bake at 325° for 1 hour in Bundt pan.

title: cranberry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream together butter, shortening and sugar.
Add other ingredients. Press 1/2 of mixture into pan.
Spread over this the whole cranberry sauce (or other jelly, jam, filling).
Press remainder of crumbs mixture on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix and pour into 2 (9-inch) pie pans.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach dip (fat-free)
directions: Drain spinach well; get most of the water out.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Add spinach; mix well.
Chill overnight for best results.
Serve with cut-up veggies.
Mix well before serving.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: In a large saucepan, cook zucchini in boiling salted water for 10 minutes or until fork-tender.
Drain and cool slightly.

title: broccoli parmesan
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes or until bright green and completely thawed.
Do not overcook.
Drain and arrange in a shallow 12 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Saute onion in margarine until tender; blend in flour and seasonings, except paprika.
Add milk and soup; cook until thickened.
Add 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese; stir until melted.
Pour sauce over broccoli.
Sprinkle with paprika and remaining cheese.
Scatter onion rings over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: red cocktail sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill well.
Makes about 1/2 cup or enough for 4 to 6 servings.
Excellent for shrimp dip.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, soup, onion, cheese, melted butter, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper.
Pour in baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
I use bread in box or a small amount of Pepperidge Farm dressing for topping.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti as package directs.
Break it into small pieces before dropping it in the boiling water. In deep frying pan, brown onions and pepper in butter.
Add hamburger and brown.
Add mushroom and tomato soup.
Add 6 ounces of cheese.
Mix all of the ingredients with spaghetti.
Put in casserole dish.
Garnish with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until cheese melts.

title: toasted mushroom canapes("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a skillet.
Saute the mushrooms and onions 5 minutes.
Blend flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring 1 minute.
Gradually stir in sour cream and cook, stirring until thickened.
Cool.
Make sandwiches of the bread and mushroom mixture.
Cut into quarters and saute in the remaining butter until browned on both sides.
Makes 24.
May be frozen.
Heat on a cookie sheet in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: beef-n-noodles
directions: Brown meat slowly in hot fat in Dutch oven or heavy kettle. Sprinkle with sugar and continue browning until all meat is well-seared.
Dust lightly with flour and continue browning.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then cover and lower to simmer.
Simmer for approximately 2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Debone and set aside.
Combine canned soups and milk over low heat until boiling.
Place deboned chicken into mixture of soup.
Cook over low heat.
On a cookie sheet take 1 tortilla at a time, put 1 ladle of soup mix into tortilla and roll.
Continue until finished with tortillas.
Pour remaining soup mixture over tortillas on cookie sheet and shred cheese over the top.
Bake until cheese is melted.
Serve with sour cream, tomatoes and shredded lettuce.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Make into loaf.
Mix mustard, water and brown sugar; pour over meat loaf.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bran muffins(or blueberry)
directions: Soak cereal in water.

title: dad's spicy apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange apples in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish or pan.
Cover with crab apples and raisins.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Layer over top of apples and press lightly.
Bake approximately 30 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: depression soap
directions: Dissolve the lye in water and pour the mixture into one gallon of milk.
The mixture is then poured into the other gallon of milk without stirring.
Let the mixture stand 24 hours during which it will harden, then allow cakes to stand until well cured.

title: white chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients, stirring until blended.
Press into bottom and 1-inch up the side of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Melt chocolate in top of double boiler.
Let cool slightly.

title: hot and creamy shrimp dip
directions: Microwave Directions:
Place cream cheese in bowl.
Microwave 30 seconds to 1 minute
on Medium or until cheese is softened. Stir in soup and onions.
Microwave 2 minutes on Medium or until dip is hot.
Stir once halfway through cooking time.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: little red hen's easy bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast cake in warm water.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased bowl and let rise until dough doubles (about 1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Punch dough down and put in greased 9-inch pie dish.
Let rise until double.
Melt butter and pour over dough before baking.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: snappy turtles
directions: In small bowl, combine 1 cup frosting, crumbs, corn syrup and vanilla at low speed; beat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Set aside.

title: southern cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening and 2 cups sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour cream.
Mix well.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.

title: peanut butter delights
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to a full boil.
Take off heat and add peanut butter and corn flakes.
Mix well and drop spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Place tray in fridge until peanut butter mix hardens.

title: mom's perfect pie crust
directions: Place flour and salt into bowl.
Cut in shortening thoroughly. Sprinkle in cold water, one tablespoon at a time, mixing until all flour is moistened and dough almost cleans side of bowl.
Shape into flattened round.
Roll out on a floured, cloth-covered board. Recipe may also be used to prepare "Electric Mixer Pastry."

title: pumpkin rich pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and spices.
Add egg.
Mix well.
Stir in pumpkin; add milk.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into chilled pastry shell.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 45 minutes on shelf just below center of oven.
To check for doneness, insert knife in center.
If it comes out clean, it is done.

title: cocoa cookies
directions: Cream flour, cocoa, sugar, lard, salt, and soda.
Beat the eggs and add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by tsp. into crushed peanuts.
Roll till coated.
Put on cookie sheet and bake.

title: crab pie
directions: Prepare pie crust.
Layer the crab meat (pat it dry), Swiss cheese and onion.
Beat eggs slightly.
Beat in half and half and seasonings.
Pour over ingredients in pie crust.
Cook uncovered in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 300° oven and cook uncovered about 30 minutes or until knife test is clean.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: With a fork, mix together first 4 ingredients.
In a separate dish, beat remaining ingredients.
Combine the two mixtures, stirring with a fork, until all moist.
Then mold dough into balls.
Chill at least 15 minutes before rolling out.
Makes 5 crusts.
Lasts one week or freeze.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions until tender but firm in salted water or in a vegetable steamer.
Drain.
Add grated carrots.
Melt butter. Pour over stuffing mixture. Place 1/2 of stuffing mixture in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Combine squash mixture, sour cream, salt, pepper and soup.
Pour into casserole.
Top with remaining crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 1 hour until crumbs are brown.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Blend together sugar, eggs, oleo, pineapple, vanilla, salt, and soda. Add flour and mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.

title: oyster nibbles
directions: Put oyster crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat oil then add dill weed, lemon pepper and dressing mix.
Stir until all oil is absorbed.
Heat in oven at 200° for 10 minutes, stir well.
Cook another 10 minutes.

title: spinach quiche
directions: *You may substitute broccoli for spinach.

title: peppy cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except vegetables; beat well.
Chill until serving time.
Serve with vegetables.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups dip.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Process all the ingredients in the blender until smooth. Spray a nonstick skillet with cooking spray. Add the batter and cook over medium heat until both sides are lightly browned. You can also make smaller pancakes. Top with any low-sugar or sugar free syrup. This has 32 grams carbohydrate.

title: curry chicken and rice
directions: Cut chicken up in small pieces and dice onion and pepper.
In large pan, heat oil and saute chicken, onion and pepper.
Add curry and several dashes of red pepper.
After all slightly sauteed, add tomatoes and 2 cups water, then add hominy.
Bring to boil, then simmer about 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: incredible noodle pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Parboil noodles for 5 minutes.
Drain. Melt butter over noodles and cover well.
Mix sugar and eggs with electric mixer.
Add cheese, sour cream and milk.
Fold in apples, peaches, vanilla, marmalade and raisins.
Add to the noodles.
Mix well.
Pour into a large glass baking dish.
Fill dish 3/4 full, allowing space for pudding to rise.
Lightly sprinkle crushed cornflakes on top.
Dot with butter and cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be frozen and reheated for later.

title: gravy-baked pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
In 10-inch skillet, brown pork chops in 1 tablespoon hot shortening.
Pour off drippings.
Put in baking dish.
Pour around the chops a mixture of soup, evaporated milk and water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until chops are done.
Stir gravy well.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tea cakes(100 year old recipe)
directions: Note:
Don't use spoon, mix with hands.

title: monkey bread
directions: Remove biscuits from cans and cut each one into quarters; roll pieces in the granulated sugar and cinnamon.
Place pecans, some of the remaining cinnamon-sugar and 2 tablespoons margarine, cut into pieces in the bottom of a greased Bundt cake pan.
Arrange cut biscuits on top of the pecans.
Sprinkle any remaining cinnamon-sugar over top.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix sugar
and	oil.
Add
eggs
at a time.	Combine salt, soda
and
flour.
Add a small amount at a time to sugar mixture; mix
well.	Add vanilla.
Add apples, nuts and coconut;
mix well. Pour into floured and greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour or until cake tests done.

title: raisin pie
directions: Place the raisins in a saucepot with water to cover; stew until tender; drain.
Add the cream, sugar, mixed with the flour, and cook for 5 minutes.
Beat the egg yolks, stir in a little of the hot mixture, then add all together and cook until thickened; cool. Add the nuts (optional).
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and brown lightly in a moderate oven.

title: bantry brown bread
directions: In large bowl, combine all-purpose and whole wheat flour, baking powder, baking soda, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening and buttermilk.
Turn out on a lightly floured board and knead for 10 minutes.
Shape into a 7-inch round loaf.
Cut a cross on top of dough with a sharp knife.
Bake at 375° in a preheated oven for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 tablespoon water in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Brush top of bread with sugar syrup and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: owel's chili
directions: Brown together ground beef, onion and garlic.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
This recipe can be doubled or tripled.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil in electric mixer.
Beat at high speed for 1 minute; add eggs, one at a time, beating each for 1 minute.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add to mixture.
Fold in vanilla, apples and nuts.
(Juice thins as it cooks.)
Grease and flour large Bundt or angel food pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 15 minutes before removing.
Can be frozen for several months.

title: puppy chow
directions: In saucepan, melt butter, chocolate chips and peanut butter. In large bowl, empty Crispix cereal.
Pour peanut butter mixture over Crispix and mix well.
Put powdered sugar in large paper grocery sack.
Put coated Crispix into bag; close the bag tightly and shake until Crispix is well coated.
After mixture is well coated, lay flat on cookie sheet to dry.

title: chunk pickles
directions: Wash unpeeled cucumbers; cut into 1-inch chunks.
Dissolve salt in water; pour over cucumbers.
Cover; let stand at room temperature for 5 hours.
Prepare jars and water both as directed. Drain cucumbers; rinse thoroughly and place in large kettle. Heat remaining ingredients to boiling, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cucumbers; heat to boiling.
Fill jars; process and cool and store as directed.

title: rich 'n' creamy brownie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine brownie mix, contents of fudge packet from mix, eggs, water and oil in large bowl.
Stir with spoon until well blended, about 50 strokes.
Stir in pecans, spread evenly in pan.

title: chocolate peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugars together.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and eggs; mix well.
Add cocoa; mix well. Add flour and soda; mix well.
Fold in chips and peanut butter cups.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool for 1 or 2 minutes on sheet before removing or they will fall apart.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: mini quiche
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook sausage and drain.
Mix Bisquick and margarine.
Add boiling water.
Stir until soft dough forms. Divide dough between 12 regular muffin cups (greased) or 24 small. Press on bottom and up side of each cup.
Divide sausage evenly among cups.
Beat egg and half and half; stir in onions and salt. Spoon about 1 tablespoon into each cup.
Sprinkle cheese over tops.
Bake about 25 minutes.

title: spicy beans
directions: Mix ingredients into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Stir and serve.
Makes 12 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: I cook this in a heavy aluminum pan.
Bring butter, sugar and Karo to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes, then add soda.
It gets foamy. Pour over corn; stir until well coated.
Break apart and store in an airtight container.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, onion, crackers, pepper, salt, 1/2 cup tomato sauce and egg whites.
Form a loaf.
Mix remaining tomato sauce, vinegar, mustard and brown sugar.
Pour over meat loaf.
Pour 2/3 cup water around edge of loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: david wade's prune cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat the eggs 1 minute.
Add eggs to dry ingredients; mix with remaining ingredients.
Beat cake batter for 3 minutes.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Place into preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Mix eggs and sugar, beat well. Add oil, beat and add remaining ingredients. Pour into 15 X 10 pan. Batter is thin. Bake 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Grease cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oriental cole slaw
directions: Brown almonds and sesame seed.
Mix onions, pepper, oil, sugar, vinegar and seasoning packet.
Pour over cabbage and noodles.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute meat and onion in skillet with Crisco until meat changes color.
In casserole, place 1/2 of cabbage (chopped), then put 1/2 of meat on top of cabbage.
Add remaining cabbage, then rest of meat.
Pour tomato soup on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco twist salad
directions: Cook spirals; drain well; rinse with cold water.
Brown meat; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning, mix well and cool.
Combine cooled spirals, onion, cheese, olives, beef, and lettuce.
Mix well. Just before serving, stir in dressing; add tomatoes and chips. Toss lightly.
Top with spicy taco sauce if desired.

title: caviar pie
directions: Combine eggs with mayonnaise; spread over bottom of well-greased 8-inch spring-form pan.
Sprinkle with onion.
Blend softened cream cheese until well blended and smooth.
Spread carefully over onion with wet spatula.
Cover and chill 3 hours or overnight.
Before serving, top with caviar, spreading to edge of pan.
Garnish with lemon wedges and parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together
the first 4 ingredients.	Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix real well.
Put in 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground meat with celery, green pepper and onion.
Mix with cooked macaroni and cheese, adding cheese last.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: egg custard
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, flour and baking powder and mix thoroughly.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup milk and beat until smooth. Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into an unbaked 8-inch pie shell or custard cups.
Bake at 275° until top is golden and custard is set.

title: salted pumpkin seeds
directions: Clean out pumpkin for carving; clean the seeds from the flesh and soak for 2 hours in salt water.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together and toss with the pumpkin seeds.
Place seeds on a cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 1 hour, turning every 15 minutes.
After pumpkin is carved and lights turned low, admire your work of art while munching on those delicious pumpkin seeds. Happy Halloween!!

title: low-fat lemon poppy seed cake(heart healthy)
directions: Baking Temperature:
Baking Time:
25 to 35 minutes for 9 x 13-inch pan; 35 to 40 minutes for Bundt pan.

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart baking dish at 350°.
Mix flour, sugar and milk in a bowl.
Pour into hot margarine in baking dish, then pour in fruit with juice.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Heat up the butter until creamy.
Add sugar and vanilla; mix.
Then beat in one egg at a time.
Next add flour, baking powder, chopped nuts and chocolate chips.
Finally add the milk.
Mix until smooth and creamy.
Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake approximately 35 minutes.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Deep fry rice sticks and drain on paper towels.
Mix lettuce, chicken, sesame seed, almonds, onions and rice sticks.
Mix sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper in shaker.
Pour over salad before serving.
Store salad ingredients in airtight container until ready to use.

title: pearl's ground beef casserole
directions: Fry beef and onion until lightly browned; drain and season. Spread a layer of beef, onion and parsley in casserole.
Cover with rice and cheese; top with tomatoes.
Repeat layers.
Simmer at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: party rolls
directions: Melt oleo and add other ingredients.
Turn rolls out of aluminum pan onto cutting board.
Slice in half with serrated knife.
Spread oleo mixture on both sides (lightly).
Put ham and cheese and replace top.
Cut out in individual rolls and replace in pan.
Cover with aluminum foil and put back in plastic bag. Freeze until ready to use.
Heat, covered, in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into pieces; toss with oil.
Mix remaining ingredients, except sauce, in plastic bag.
Shake chicken in plastic bag.
Shake off excess crumbs.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Use a large pan (this boils high in the pan).
Combine sugar and milk (no salt is needed for the salt is in the peanut butter). Boil until soft ball forms in cold water.
Stir often.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter, eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add vanilla wafers (crushed) and milk and beat well.
Add coconut and pecans.
Fold in or stir by hand.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Will be light brown on top.

title: microwave ground beef casserole
directions: Cook beef
and
onion on High for 4 minutes; add spices and pepper,
corn and tomato sauce.
Cover and cook 4 minutes. Stir in rice
and
cover
and
cook 6 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and cook uncovered for 1 minute.

title: date cake
directions: Cut in thirds 1 pound dates; add to this
1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Cream together the sugar, shortening, salt and egg.
Add the flour, soda and vanilla.
Mix in the dates and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: whistle stop cornbread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add
oil
and
milk and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and beat.
Add more milk, if necessary, to get the consistency of
pancake
batter.
Can
make fried cornbread or bake in iron skillet or muffins at 450° until brown.

title: dump salad
directions: Do not add water to jello.
Drain all fruit.
Dump all ingredients into bowl and mix well.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Don't use light Cool Whip as it falls.
Try varying fruits if use use different flavors of jello.

title: potato casserole(serves 12)
directions: Thaw potatoes thoroughly and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix next 6 ingredients together and pour over potatoes.
Put crushed flakes on top and dribble butter over it.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or a little more.

title: heart healthy beef stir-fry
directions: Trim excess fat from meat; cut meat in 1/4-inch thick strips. Cut carrots and broccoli stems into 1/2-inch slices and separate broccoli flowerets.
Combine water, soy sauce, cornstarch and sugar.
Heat 1/2 oil in work or skillet over medium heat.
Add broccoli stems, flowerets and carrots.
Stir-fry until hot but crisp, 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove vegetables and add remaining oil to wok or skillet.
Add beef strips, not more than 1/3 at a time; stir-fry 4 to 5 minutes or until meat is light brown.
Add soy sauce mixture.
Cook until thickened and clear, stirring continuously.
Add vegetables, garlic powder and thoroughly stir. Serve immediately over hot rice if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: linda's jalapeno cheese dip
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Crush tomatoes.
Add peppers and tomatoes to cooked onions.
(Green chili peppers may be used if fresh jalapeno peppers are not available.)
Shred or slice cheese in 1/2-inch slices.
Add to mixture.
Cook on medium heat on top of stove or microwave on High for 10 to 13 minutes, stirring once or twice, until cheese melts and mixture is smooth.
Serve with nacho chips.
Keeps well in covered dish in the refrigerator.

title: the best brownies
directions: Blend butter, sugar
and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs and beat well with a spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually
add
to
egg	mixture
until well blended. Stir in nuts.
Spread
in
greased pan and bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from edges of pan.
Frost if desired.	Cut into squares.

title: blueberry streusel muffins
directions: Combine 1/3 cup sugar and 1/4 cup butter in a small mixing bowl, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add egg, beating well. Combine 2 1/3 cups flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, stirring well after each addition. Stir in vanilla and fold in blueberries.
Spoon batter into greased muffin cups, filling 2/3 full.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, 1/3 cup flour and cinnamon.
Cut in 1/4 cup butter until mixture resembles crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of muffin batter.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: meatless zucchini mexicana #1
directions: Chop zucchini in large pieces.
Put in wok or skillet to toss and stir-fry.
Add tomatoes, onion and chili.
Add chili powder and toss and cook together over low heat.
When crisp-tender, add corn.
Heat and serve.

title: special k bars
directions: Measure cereal into large buttered bowl.
Combine sugar and syrup in a small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until it boils. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and mix until well blended.
Pour over cereal and mix together until cereal is coated.
Press mixture into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let stand in cool place.
Melt chips over low heat.
Mix well and spread over bars.

title: chile chicken
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix all ingredients except cheese into a large pot and warm slightly.
Pour mixture into casserole dish, cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
After 1 hour, add cheese and remove foil if it seems too soupy.
Let rest 5 to 10 minutes before serving. Serves 10 to 12.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Heat oil in large skillet; saute beef and onion until browned, adding salt to taste, pepper and garlic powder.
Drain off excess fat and place in square casserole.
Bring water, milk, margarine and 1 teaspoon of salt to a boil.
Stir in Potato Buds until thoroughly moistened and potatoes are fluffy.
Spread corn Niblets over beef mixture, then spread potatoes over corn.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 6 servings.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Put sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa in pan.
Bring to a boil. Cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and quickly add oatmeal, peanut butter, vanilla and nuts.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Let stand until cool.

title: honey pork oriental
directions: Cut pork in 1-inch squares.
Brown in oil.
Stir frequently for 15 minutes.
Combine gravy with water, honey, soy sauce, vinegar, ginger and garlic.
Salt and add to skillet. Cover and cook 20 minutes.
(Can do this much ahead.)
Add carrots; cook 10 minutes.
Add onion and pepper; cook 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: russian sauerkraut
directions: Place sauerkraut in bottom of baking dish.
Add celery, tomatoes and margarine.
Add bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bacon is crisp.
This can be microwaved in 10 minutes at 7 power.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and milk.
Cook over medium heat until soft-ball stage.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and margarine.	Beat until it starts to thicken.
Pour into greased flat pan.
Cool and cut.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Combine broth, soy sauce and mushroom soup; pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve over hot rice.

title: rice custard pudding
directions: Boil water and add rice.
Cover and boil rice until most of water is absorbed (over low heat or double boiler).
Stir occasionally while rice is boiling.

title: orange ball cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly except coconut.
Form into moth ball bite-size pieces.
Roll in coconut flakes.
Chill.
Do not bake.

title: brown rice waldorf salad
directions: Mix together.
Good served with grilled chicken breast.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburg, drain. In large pot, add all the ingredients. May add more or less chili powder according to taste. Cook slowly, 1-2 hours. Or all day in a crockpot.
Serve with Pillsbury Cornbread Sticks. Enjoy!

title: rachel's apple crunch
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Pour in apples and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Add dry cake mix, saving 1 cup.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Bake at 350 degrees until brown.
Very good served with ice cream!

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13 oven dish.
Layer ingredients as listed.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: turkey noodle casserole for 50
directions: Cook noodles in water (slightly salted) until tender; drain. Saute onion in butter.
Add soup, milk and seasonings; stir until well blended.
Boil.
Arrange noodles, turkey and mushroom sauce in alternating layers in greased casserole.
Sprinkle almonds on the top.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Serving size is 3/4 cup.
Serves 50 people.

title: shrimp with chilies and garlic
directions: Wash shrimp, pat dry and set aside.
Cut chilies in half; remove seeds.
Place wok over high heat; add oil.
Heat for 10 seconds.
Add chili-garlic paste; stir-fry for 1 minute and oil turns slightly red.
Add shrimp; stir-fry 3 to 5 minutes until pink.
Stir in salt.
Serve at once with fresh bread to soak up chili mixture.

title: green chile enchiladas(stacked)
directions: Coat skillet with nonstick cooking spray. Cook onion and green chilies.
Heat enchilada sauce.
Add onion, green chilies, garlic powder and black pepper to sauce.
Heat tortillas.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover bottom of shallow baking dish with some of the sauce.
Dip tortillas, one at a time, in sauce.
Place 4 on bottom of dish.
Top each with cheese.
Continue to make 4 stacks. Top all stacks with rest of sauce and cheese.
Place in oven and bake until cheese is melted.
After removing from oven, may be topped with chopped lettuce and tomatoes for extra flavor.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in electric skillet on low temperature.
Add sauce, peppers, salt and onions.
Cook 15 minutes, low to medium temperature.
Then simmer on and on.
Serve on fresh buns.
Yields approximately 35 servings.

title: cornflake wreaths
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in saucepan.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and food coloring.
Add cornflakes; stir well.
Drop into wreaths on waxed paper.
Decorate with red hots.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: In a bowl stir together cream cheese, artichoke hearts, pimiento and oregano.
Spread cream cheese mixture onto tortillas. Divide remaining ingredients between the tortillas.
Roll up tortillas.	Cover and chill seam sides down for 2 to 24 hours. Cut roll-ups into one inch slices.

title: wine biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, oil, wine and sugar; let stand about 15 minutes.
Roll out about a tablespoon into a rope and twist like a knot.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush with egg white, beaten with a tablespoon of water.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: chicken divan
directions: Combine soup and mayonnaise. Cook broccoli until tender. Arrange in large baking pan. Place chicken on top. Pour soup mixture over chicken and sprinkle with cheese. Mix butter and crumbs and put on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: disappearing meat loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute onion in butter over low heat until tender.
Stir in flour.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add can of tomatoes with chilies. Stir.
Add cheese and jalapenos.
Cook over very low heat, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: new year's day crown roast of pork
directions: Mix together.
(Can be baked in casserole for 1 hour and served with other meats.)

title: wiener paprika-schnitzel
directions: Use meat mallet to pound veal on both sides until it is fairly thin.
Season it with salt, pepper and paprika.
Dust steaks lightly with flour.
Shake off excess flour.
Dip into combined egg and milk.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Press crumbs on firmly.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Skewer fresh fruit (such as apple slices, pineapple chunks, oranges, etc.) on wooden skewers or hors d'oeuvre picks. Arrange on attractive tray and serve with dip.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Shape into small, bite size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Recipe makes about 72 bite size balls.

title: boiled custard
directions: Scald the milk and butter in a double boiler over hot water. Beat eggs and sugar together until light.
Add milk to this mixture.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, salt and nutmeg.
Return to boiler.
Cook until custard coats the spoon, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Cool.
Put in dish and refrigerate.

title: mediterranean vegetables
directions: Put eggplant in a 2-quart microwave-safe dish.
Cover and microwave 6 minutes on High.
Put oil, onions and peppers in same dish.
Stir to mix; cover and microwave on High 4 or 5 minutes. Stir in eggplant and remaining ingredients, except Feta Cheese. Cover and microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: haystacks
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Blend in peanut butter.
Pour over corn flakes and stir. With teaspoon, spoon mixture on waxed paper in "little haystacks".

title: vegetable strudel(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Combine broccoli, cauliflower and carrots; steam until just tender.
Cool.
Cook onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons butter until soft.
Cool.
Combine eggs and seasonings and beat well. Add vegetables, onion mixture and cheese.
Oil a large baking sheet and set aside.
Keep phyllo dough sheets covered with a lightly dampened towel while you work.
Take the first sheet, brush with melted butter and continue to stack and butter each sheet, but the last.
Spread with vegetables, leaving a 3-inch border all around.
Fold short ends of dough in, then fold and overlap the long sides and seal with melted butter.
Put on oiled sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with Hollandaise Sauce.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine ingredients except paprika, in a buttered casserole. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until firm.
After baking, sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 12.

title: bean pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off grease.
Add all other ingredients (except biscuits) and bring to a boil.
Pour into a casserole dish. Cut can biscuits in half and put on top of mixture.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top of biscuits.
Bake until brown at 350°.

title: tomato ketchup
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until it boils down a bit, then mix in dry mustard, cloves, cinnamon, onion and peppers.
Stir constantly over heat until thick.
Bottle it and seal.

title: poppy seed salad dressing
directions: In a jar with a tight-fitting lid, combine the ingredients and shake until the sugar is completely dissolved.
Shake before each use.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute garlic, onion and celery in margarine.
Add soups, chicken broth and tomatoes.
Stir well.
Cube Velveeta and add, stirring until melted.
Combine cut up chicken, spaghetti and sauce in large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until golden.
Freezes well.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Mix together apples, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Spread mixture into a 9-inch pan.

title: country fried venison
directions: Dip cubed venison into buttermilk.
Salt and pepper, then batter in self-rising flour.
Deep fry at about 300° until brown. Serve with rice and gravy.

title: preacher's chocolate cake
directions: Position rack in lower third of oven; preheat to 325°.
Grease a 10 x 4-inch tube pan or a 12 cup Bundt pan; dust with flour.
In a medium bowl; stir together flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, using electric beaters, cream butter until light and smooth.
Add sugar in several additions, beating until light and fluffy.
Gradually add eggs, beating until mixture has the consistency of lightly whipped cream.
Beat in vanilla and melted chocolate.
Using a large rubber spatula, alternately stir in dry ingredients and sour cream, beginning and ending with dry ingredients and blending well after each addition.
Add the boiling water all at once, stirring until well blended.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugar and brown sugar until mixture is light. Add eggs, one at a time, then vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt.

Gradually add to creamed mixture. Stir in oatmeal, pecans and chocolate bits. Blend well. Drop by spoonfuls on well-greased cookie sheets. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: janice walker's banana nut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Sift flour, soda and salt and add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Add mashed bananas, vanilla and mix.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes in 3 (9-inch) layer pans or 9 x 13-inch loaf pan that has been greased and floured for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening together. Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.

title: dilled rolls
directions: Combine flour, mayonnaise and milk. Stir in dill seed and blend well. Drop into well-greased party size muffin tins.
Bake at 450° until lightly browned.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Cook chicken in margarine over medium heat, turning once, until light brown, about 10 minutes.
Mix wine, lemon juice,
salt and dill weed.
Pour over chicken.
Place lemon slices on chicken. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until chicken is done, 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove chicken; keep warm.
Heat wine mixture to boiling; cook until reduced by half, about 3 minutes. Pour over chicken; sprinkle with onions.

title: eagle brand pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each. Add flavoring and Eagle Brand milk. Add flour and beat well. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp and rice salad
directions: Boil shrimp in seasoning mix.
Cool and chop.
Mix all ingredients together.
Season to taste.

title: wanda's layered salad
directions: In large bowl layer in order the ingredients.
When you add the mayonnaise, make sure you spread to the end of bowl in all directions to seal. Layer the remaining ingredients, finishing with the tomatoes.

title: fish filets in almond butter(microwave)
directions: Combine almonds and butter.
Cook on High for 5 minutes, until golden brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Arrange fish filets in mixture, coating each piece.
Cook, covered, on High for 5 minutes.
(Fish is done when it flakes with a fork.)
Let stand, covered, for 2 minutes.

title: irish sweet bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Blend in butter or margarine to resemble corn meal.
Add raisins.
Mix beaten eggs and milk; add. Stir until blended.
Turn onto lightly floured board; knead for 2 minutes.
Pat to fit a 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Reduce oven to 350°; bake for 30 minutes.
Reserve 1 teaspoon of egg white; brush on top after you make the cross on top.
Good luck!

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute meat slightly.
Boil lasagna noodles slightly; set aside.
Put cottage cheese, mushrooms, spaghetti sauce, pepper, onion and slightly beaten egg whites in a medium size bowl along with sauteed meat.
Layer the lasagna noodles and meat mixture into a large lasagna pan or casserole dish and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: california cheese soup
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until all vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes.
Stir in soup and cheese.
Cook until soup is heated and cheese is melted.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: play dough
directions: For endless hours of fun for kids:
To boiling water add and stir remaining ingredients.
Add desired food coloring.
Keep different colors in separate airtight containers.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Spray 9x13 pan with vegetable spray.
Spread beans in pan. Brown meat and onions together, drain.
Season with salt to taste. Spread meat mixture over beans.
Cover with cheeses.
Pour taco sauce over top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: frozen marinated cucumbers
directions: Sprinkle salt over thin sliced cucumbers, onion and pepper in colander sitting in shallow dish in refrigerator.
Juice will be drawn from vegetables.
Let sit and drain for 2 hours.
Squeeze against colander and place in pint freezer containers.
While cucumbers are draining, mix sugar and vinegar.
Heat to boil.
Let cool.
Add celery seed.
Pour over vegetables and freeze.
Thaw in refrigerator overnight before use.

title: deviled mushrooms
directions: Rinse,	pat
dry
and remove stems from mushrooms.
Set caps aside.
Chop
enough stems to make 1/2 cup.
Reserve for later use.
In medium bowl combine cream cheese, deviled ham, 1/2
cup bread crumbs, reserved chopped mushroom stems, onion powder
and pepper.
In small saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of the
butter. Brush outside of caps with butter.	Mound stuffing	mixture
into each mushroom cap.	Melt remaining 1 tablespoon
of butter and stir in remaining bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over stuffed mushrooms. Place in shallow baking dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix and bake for 25 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: strombolis
directions: Stretch the bread loaf into a 12 x 8-inch rectangle pan.
Beat egg and oregano together.
Brush most of the mixture on the dough in the pan.
Layer half of the ingredients, then repeat.
Stretch second loaf and lay it on top of the meat mixture; pinch to seal. Brush with remaining egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Slice and dip in warmed pizza sauce if desired.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Make white sauce with melted margarine, flour, Pet milk and asparagus liquid.
Cook until thick and add cheese.
Put asparagus tips in casserole.
Cover with sliced eggs.
Repeat these two layers and pour white sauce over all.
Cover with cracker crumbs and bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven or until it is bubbly and cracker crumbs are browned.
This serves 3 to 4. I usually use 2 cans of asparagus.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine and mix eggs, sugar, oil and cream cheese.
Add dry ingredients and
vanilla.
Fold
in
zucchini, raisins and nuts. Grease 2 large or 3 small loaf pans. Bake at 350° about 55 minutes.

title: sausage milk gravy
directions: Heat grease in skillet.
Crumble the sausage into small pieces and add to hot grease.
Sprinkle flour into grease, stirring constantly, until all is combined.
Add milk until desired consistency; add salt and pepper to taste.

title: orange spinach salad
directions: Tear spinach and lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Add onion, green pepper, oranges and cucumber.
Toss with honey dill dressing. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: myriah's apricot cordial
directions: Place ingredients in 1/2 gallon flat topped glass jar (do not mix).
Turn jar upside down twice a day for half a day, for 8 days. Use same apricots again with same amount of sugar and vodka, only set for 12 to 14 days.

title: broccoli-orange salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl; set aside.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; add to broccoli mixture, stirring to coat.
Gently stir in mandarin oranges.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook the pasta, drain and rinse in cold water.
Combine with dressing and seasoning.
Tosss with an assortment of chopped vegetables.
Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: hot asparagus rolls
directions: Trim crust off bread; use a rolling pin to flatten.
Blend the 2 cheeses and the egg to a workable consistency; spread evenly on each slice of bread.
Roll 1 asparagus spear in each slice.
Add the Grand Marnier to the melted butter; dip each roll in the butter and coat thoroughly.
Place the rolls on a cookie sheet; freeze.
When frozen firmly, slice each roll into 3 sections. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
These can be made in advance and after the rolls are cut can be stored in the freezer, then defrosted and cooked when required.

title: african curried rice
directions: Saute in large pan until clear the oil, celery, onion and green pepper.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Serve over cooked rice with options of condiments.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix together and stir well.
Store in airtight container.
Use 3 to 4 tablespoons per cup of hot water.

title: marie's no-streak glass cleaner
directions: Pour the ammonia, alcohol and detergent into a one-gallon jug. Fill jug with water.

title: chocolate filled oatmeal bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Combine oatmeal, flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Spread 2/3 of mixture into greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Combine chocolate chips, condensed milk and margarine in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until melted and smooth.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Spread over oatmeal mixture in pan.
Spoon small drops of remaining oatmeal mixture on top.
Try to spread evenly a little.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter, then add peanut butter in boiler.
Bring to a boil.
Take off stove; add oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add chili powder.
Add red beans and taco sauce and heat thoroughly.
Chop lettuce and onions and mix together.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Crush chips and add to salad. Stir in French dressing and add to meat mixture.
Serve immediately.

title: tea doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt, nutmeg and shortening.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk. Drop by teaspoon into deep fat at 375° until outsides are golden brown, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: blueberry nut bread
directions: Mix sugar and melted shortening together.
Mix sour milk, beaten eggs, flour, soda and salt together.
Add nutmeats and blueberries to flour mixture.
Combine the flour and liquid mixtures.
Pour into 2 loaf pans that have been greased.
Let set 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: teriyaki meat loaf(good source of protein and niacin)
directions: Mix all ingredients except pineapple.
Spread beef mixture evenly in ungreased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Cook, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour; drain.
Spoon pineapple over meat loaf. Cook until meat loaf is done, about 30 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings, 335 calories per serving.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Thoroughly cream the margarine and sugar.
Add sweet potatoes and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg; gradually add to creamed mixture, beating well.
Blend in vanilla and orange extracts. Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Cool about 5 minutes and remove from pan.
While still hot, drizzle with glaze.

title: jessica's favorite pasta
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions.
Mix the cream cheese, milk, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper until smooth and creamy; set aside.
Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Drain linguine; toss with cream sauce and cooked vegetables.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired. Serve immediately.

title: hootin tootin cake
directions: Mix Cool Whip and powdered sugar together and refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: lobster supreme
directions: Drop frozen lobster tails into boiling salted water.
When water reboils, cook for 1 minute.
Drain immediately and drench with cold water.
Carefully remove meat from shells; reserve shells to refill.
Cut meat into bite size pieces.
Lobster will appear translucent, but completes cooking in sauce.
Mix the cream cheese and cream together until blended.
Melt butter; stir in flour.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly; cook until thickened.
Add salt, curry powder, paprika and cream cheese mixture, stirring until sauce is smooth.
Add lobster meat; simmer very gently until heated through.
Refill empty shells with mixture and serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: herb-roasted potatoes
directions: In 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish, add and mix all cut-up ingredients with Good Seasons garlic and herb salad dressing. Arrange in single layer.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until potatoes are golden brown, stirring occasionally. Uncover for last 15 minutes to brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: melting moments
directions: Stir together flour, cornstarch and sugar. In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine until smooth. Add flour mixture and vanilla. Beat until well blended. Refrigerate 1 hour. Shape into 1-inch balls. Place about 1 1/2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten. Bake in 350° oven 10 to 12 minutes. Don't overbake. Remove to rack to cool. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Saute beef in 9-inch frying pan.
Add cut up peppers and onions.
Add mushrooms and soup.
Let mixture cook for approximately 10 minutes.

title: cheese bread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Fold in grated cheese.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
(Suitable for freezing.)

title: pan-roasted chicken
directions: Heat the butter and oil
in
a
deep
skillet.
Add the garlic and
chicken
quarters,
skin
side
down.
Brown
the chicken on both sides and
add
the rosemary.
Add the pepper, the wine and a large pinch
of salt.
Lower the heat and cover the pan.
Cook slowly until
the
chicken
is
tender
at
the pricking of a fork.
Turn the chicken two or three times while cooking. Transfer the chicken
to
a warm platter and deglaze the pan. Pour the juices on the chicken and serve.

title: no roll pastry
directions: Mix in medium bowl with fork.
Stir flour and salt.
Add shortening and mix until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1 cup mixture.

Sprinkle 2 to 3 tablespoons cold water into flour mixture, a tablespoon at a time, mixing lightly with fork after each addition until pastry is moist enough to hold together. Press to bottom and sides of 8-inch or 9-inch pie plate; flute edges.
Fill crust with fruit, mincemeat or pumpkin filling; sprinkle reserved flour on top.

title: fresh vegetable salad
directions: Break cauliflower and broccoli apart.
Combine all ingredients.
Tastes best if refrigerated for a few hours.

title: veal rolls divan
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and reserve drippings.
Prepare stuffing mix per package directions, using bacon drippings and melted butter to make 1/4 cup.
Crumble bacon and stir into stuffing.
Place 1/3 cup stuffing onto each steak and roll each steak; secure.
Add 1 tablespoon salad oil to drippings in skillet. Brown veal rolls. Dissolve crushed bouillon cube into 1/2 cup boiling water.
Arrange broccoli spears in baking dish.
Place veal rolls over broccoli.
Pour bouillon mixture over veal. Cover dish with foil.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar with mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip and add remaining ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish or pan and freeze.

title: doctor bird cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; sift.
Dice bananas; add to dry ingredients along with oil, pineapple juice, vanilla and eggs. Stir to blend; do not beat.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes (top will spring back at your touch).
Cool in pan for 30 minutes, then turn onto plate. Sprinkle with powdered sugar when completely cool.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Open chicken breast to make a pocket.
Place 1 slice ham and 1 slice Swiss cheese in each pocket.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Melt margarine in a flat pan.
Mix crumbs and seasonings in a separate dish.
Roll chicken in margarine, then in crumbs.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Store in refrigerator for several hours.
Bake uncovered 40 minutes at 400°.

title: grilled asparagus with orange
directions: Combine orange rind and next six ingredients. Mix well. Take one third of mixture and cover asparagus. Chill 2 hours. Drain and grill asparagus 350°-400° 8-10 minutes. Cool. Toss remaining dressing with salad greens and serve asparagus over greens. Sprinkle with crumbled bacon just before serving.

title: rice and beans, spanish style
directions: Heat the oil in a large saucepan over moderate heat for 1 minute. Add the onion and green and red peppers and saut, stirring often for 1 minute. Add the salt and water; bring to a boil and stir in the rice. Remove from the heat; cover and let stand for 5 minutes. Stir the beans into the rice mixture; cover and warm over low heat for 2 minutes. Transfer to a serving dish; top with the chopped eggs and surround with the orange slices. Serves 4.

title: quick and easy dill veggie dip
directions: Mix well and use for dipping raw veggies! Can add onion flakes or powder if you like onion flavor.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Place 1 can rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix and beat well cream cheese, 2 egg yolks, vanilla and sugar.
Spread on rolls in pan. Press second can of rolls on top.
Beat egg whites until fluffy. Frost dough with mixture.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into crusts.
Chill.
Very easy, but very good.

title: corn meal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually and cream well.
Beat in eggs until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla. Sift together the remaining ingredients; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Roll on lightly floured board and cut with a 2-inch cookie cutter.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned and crispy (12 to 15 minutes).
Sprinkle with granulated sugar before baking.

title: oven-fried vegetables
directions: Spray a cold baking sheet with nonstick spray coating.
Set aside.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking soda.
Combine butter, sugar, vanilla and pudding.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake 2 inches apart on cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Drain liquor from oysters and reserve.
Mix crumbs and melted butter; toss until all crumbs are well buttered.
Grease casserole and line bottom with 1/3 of the crumbs.
Add half of the oysters. Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg and fresh ground pepper.
Repeat crumb and oyster layers; season.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Saute squash in butter; add onion.
Mix chiles and soup with squash and onion.
Put in casserole dish and top with cheese crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: linguini and clam sauce
directions: To make sauce, heat butter and oil; add garlic and simmer, 1 to 2 minutes, until golden but not brown.
Add parsley, oregano, basil and pepper.
Simmer.
Cook linguini al dente.
Drain.
Add clams to sauce; simmer 1 to 2 minutes, just to heat through.
Toss linguini with clam sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

In medium saucepan, melt butter; stir in flour, mustard and salt; gradually stir in milk and cook and stir until mixture thickens slightly (mixture should coat spoon). Remove from heat; add 1 1/2 cups of cheese and stir until melted. Stir in cooked macaroni.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°F.

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Melt margarine and mix with cracker crumbs.
Whip Dream Whip and cool milk together.
Add sugar, then cream cheese; beat well. Put half of crumbs in dish for crust, then half of cream mixture, then pie filling.
Put other half of cream mixture and remaining crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients with coffee. Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except French fried onions and put in casserole dish.
Cook for 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle Durkee French fried onions to cover top.
Bake additional 10 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots; drain and cool.
Cut onion and green pepper and mix with carrots.
Mix other ingredients and pour over the vegetables.
Cover closely.
Marinate in the refrigerator for 12 hours or more.
Keeps well in the fridge!
Makes a great condiment.

title: glazed or candied sweet potatoes
directions: Steam or boil potatoes in skins until tender; peel. Cut into halves lengthwise. Arrange in shallow pan. Mix sugar, water, butter or margarine and salt. Heat to boiling point. Pour over potatoes. Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Beat eggs at medium speed.
Gradually add sugar.
Add next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Add enough milk to fill freezer 3/4 full. Use electric or hand turned freezer.
Let ripen for 1 hour.
Yields 4 quarts.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Chop bananas and pour lemon juice over them.
Add all other ingredients except cream and sugar.
Add sugar to whipped cream and fold in.
Chill before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and broccoli in butter until golden brown. Mix soup with Cheez Whiz; heat until well mixed (this burns easily).
Combine all ingredients and place in casserole. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mixed fruit soup
directions: Simmer dried fruits with seasonings until tender.
Dissolve cornstarch in 2 tablespoons cold water.
Bring soup to boiling and stir in starch.
Cook, covered, until soup has thickened and is clear.
Cool with cover on.
To serve, pour over creamed rice or top with whipped cream.

title: baked chicken in one pan
directions: Cut broilers in half lengthwise.
Peel and cut potatoes in quarters.
Peel and cut carrots in 1/8-inch pieces.
Quarter onions.
Put vegetables in roasting pan.
Place chicken halves over vegetables.
Salt and pepper.
Pour cream over it.
Dot with squares of butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and place under broiler 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: easy jello dessert
directions: Drain fruit
cocktail and use this juice for the cup of cold water
when
mixing
Jell-O.
As Jell-O sets for a while, add the fruit and cream cheese.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Add other ingredients, except cinnamon. Pour into a greased dish; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: juicy baked chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken (do not cut up).
Stuff with 1/2 apple and 1/2 onion.
Season heavily with all the spices (just shake them on).
Place in roasting pan with sliced (thickly) onion and 1 cup water.
Roast at 500° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Roast at 425° for another 30 to 45 minutes.
Add more water if necessary as pan should have juice in it.
Baste with juice once or twice.
Cover with foil if skin gets too brown.
Slice and serve in own juice. Mmmmmm!

title: easy oven lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce.
In 2-quart baking dish layer sauce, uncooked lasagna, Ricotta and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: barb's summer salad
directions: Brown meat with minced garlic clove.
Drain can of kidney beans and stir into browned meat.
Heat thoroughly and set aside.

title: swiss asparagus
directions: Melt butter. Add salt, paprika and flour; cook and stir until smooth. You are making a white sauce. Stir in milk and continue cooking until sauce thickens. Add mushroom soup. Cut cheese in small bits. Add and stir until melted. Add celery, pimento and 2 eggs, chopped up. Add onions (you can saute in butter first if you have time). Place alternate layers of sauce and asparagus in
a casserole dish. Top with buttered crumbs. Cook at 400° until top looks good and crunchy.

title: chocolate fudge pie(it makes its own crust)
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in top of double boiler.
Mix sugar and flour.
Beat in eggs.
Add to the melted butter and chocolate. Add vanilla plus salt. Pour in a greased pie pan and bake in slow oven (300°) for about 20 minutes.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream and nuts or serve with ice cream.

title: baked oats
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together and all wet ingredients together, then mix all together and pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Serve with milk, hot applesauce or canned fruit.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing and melted butter/margarine.
Combine chicken, soup, milk, peas and onions in pan and bring to boil.
Put 3/4 of stuffing in bottom of baking dish.
Add chicken mixture and sprinkle remaining stuffing over mix.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.

title: ham with fettuccine
directions: Saute mushrooms in 1/4 cup butter over moderate heat for 2 minutes.
Add ham, zucchini, cream, 1/2 cup butter, salt and pepper.
Bring mixture to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes. Cook fettuccine until al dente:
drain.
Add ham and vegetable mixture, combining well.
Serve on heated platter, garnished with parsley and sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook broccoli until almost tender; place in an ungreased baking dish.
Cream soup and milk until smooth.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese over broccoli.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crushed wafers or crackers with 1 cube melted margarine. Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Using hands, mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Shape about a teaspoon of mixture around a green, pitted olive.
Repeat process until cheese mixture is gone.
Chill for at least 1 hour. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 18 minutes.
Should appear light golden around edges.

title: citrus cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sour cream.
Mix well and then mix in cream.
Pour in tube pan. Bake 45 to 55 minutes.
Take out of pan.
Spoon glaze on hot cake.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Beat egg and 1 tablespoon water.
Roll chicken in mixture and then in crumbs.
Brown in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Mix all other ingredients except cheese and pour over chicken.
Cover and cook in 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove cover; sprinkle with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Put back in oven until cheese melts.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut up fruit and place in large bowl.
Bring to boil the cornstarch, water and sugar until creamy.
Remove from heat and add strawberry jello.
Let cool and pour over fruit.
Place in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: barbecue potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease baking pan; set aside.
In small bowl, combine butter, ketchup, chili powder, brown sugar and red pepper.
Cut each potato lengthwise into 8 wedges.
Place in pan and brush with sauce.
Bake for 30 minutes, brushing occasionally, until tender.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Combine beef, salt, pepper, milk and oats in bowl; mix well. Shape mixture into meatballs.
Brown on all sides in butter in skillet.
Transfer meatballs to casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl; pour over meatballs.
Cover and bake.

title: salted nut roll bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, margarine and salt as if preparing pie crust.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes.
Cool.
Spread nuts on crust.
Combine syrup, chips and butter in double boiler until well blended.
Pour over crust and bake again for 10 minutes.
Serves 24.

title: skiers french toast
directions: In a small saucepan, combine syrup, butter and brown sugar. Simmer until syrupy. Pour over bottom of 9 X 13 pan. Slice bread into 12 to 16 slices and place over sugar-butter mixture. In a bowl, beat eggs, milk, vanilla and salt. Pour over bread. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Uncover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve hot or warm or it will harden in pan. This can be reheated. Serves 6 to 8.

title: feather rolls
directions: Combine 2 cups flour and yeast in mixer bowl; mix well. Combine potatoes, warm water, oil, sugar and salt in small bowl; mix well.
Add to flour mixture.
Beat at low speed for 1/2 minute.
Beat at high speed for 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining 3 cups flour by hand to form soft dough.
Place on lightly floured surface.
Let rest, covered, for 10 minutes.
Knead for 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, turning to coat surface.
Let rise, covered, in warm place until doubled in bulk.
Shape into rolls.
Place in greased baking dish.
Let rise, covered, until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: kifle
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar and Crisco like pie dough.
Dissolve yeast in warm milk, then mix egg yolks, yeast and vanilla in flour mixture with a little warm milk at a time.
Use more flour if needed.
Mix dough with hands until it doesn't stick.
Put in refrigerator for at least 3 hours.
Then roll out on pastry board a little at a time with flour and sugar on board.
Cut in small squares and fill with prune nut filling.
You can buy prune nut filling or you can make your own.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream first 2 ingredients slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Roll each ball in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: lemon luscious pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, lemon peel, butter, lemon juice, milk and egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat, cover and cool.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill for at least 1 hour.

title: low-fat peanut butter pie
directions: Whip the cheese at low speed until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly beat in milk.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into shell.
Freeze pie, covered.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: oriental marinated strips
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Put steaks in marinade.
Place in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove steaks from marinade and place on a preheated grill over medium heat for approximately 7 to 9 minutes for a rare-medium steak. Serves 2.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add milk and mix to desired thickness.
Drop by teaspoon in hot oil.

title: spinach hors d'oeuvre
directions: Thaw spinach; drain.
Beat eggs well.
Add all ingredients. Refrigerate several hours.
Form into bite size balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.
You can dip them in your favorite dip.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets; chill, peel and grate.
Melt margarine and cheese; add salt and milk.
Combine with potatoes. Add sour cream and onions; blend.
Pour into a greased 13x9-inch casserole.
Potatoes can be frozen or refrigerated at this point. Bake at 350 degrees about 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Drain berries and boil juice.
Add juice to Knox gelatine.
Let thicken.
Add Cool Whip.
Stir together and pour in container.
Let chill several hours before serving.

title: curry chicken and vegetable stir-fry(low calorie entree)
directions: Heat oil in wok or large skillet until hot.
Add chicken, onion and curry powder.
Stir-fry until chicken turns white, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Add vegetables, sugar and broth; continue cooking until vegetables are just tender, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve over rice.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Blend in eggs.
Mix in bananas.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Alternately add dry ingredients and milk to first mixture, mixing well. Add nuts. Mix.
Pour into prepared loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Empty beans into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add additional ingredients. Stir thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 1
hour uncovered.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients; add soda, baking powder, salt and flour.
Mix in 2 cups flour; add buttermilk and last 2 cups flour. Bake at 425° to 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cubed steak casserole
directions: Place steak in large glass dish. Layer onions, carrots and potatoes on top. Heat soup with margarine and pour over casserole. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cheese dumplings(recipe of croation origin)
directions: Place cheese in bowl.
Add egg and mix well.
Add flour and salt.
Knead lightly until smooth and your hands come clean.

title: chocolate fruit soup
directions: Place 1/2 cup chocolate chips in blender, process at high speed, about 15 seconds, or until reduced to fine particles. Remove from blender and set aside.
Over hot (not boiling) water, combine remaining chips and the milk.
Heat until chips melt and mixture is combined.
The chips and milk mixture will contain flecks of chocolate.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine filling ingredients and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Pour in pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: honey lime salad dressing
directions: Stir together mayonnaise, mustard and honey.
Add parsley, onions and lime juice.
Mix together well.
Add vinegar and oil. Salt to taste.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: All ingredients should be room temperature.

title: roast and gravy
directions: Place 3 feet
of
wide	aluminum
foil on cookie sheet. Put chuck roast on foil.
Spread soups (undiluted) over roast. Sprinkle one package
of
onion
soup
mix	over
roast.
Seal aluminum foil well.
Bake
in a 325° oven for 4 hours.
Do not open oven or foil
or
check on roast.
It will be done in the allotted time and you will have gravy.

title: pecan pie(here is another great tasting pecan pie recipe.)
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter in a saucepan and bring to a boil, then cool.
In a bowl, slightly beat eggs, and add cooled syrup mixture, stirring gently.
Gradually add salt, vanilla and pecans. Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: texas trash
directions: Combine oil, butter and spices and heat.
Mix all other ingredients and pour liquid over it.
Stir to coat well.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours, stirring every 20 to 30 minutes.
After mix is cool, store in an airtight container.

title: coffee sponge cake
directions: Combine boiling water and coffee.
Add cold water to make 1 cup.
Sift cake flour, baking powder and salt; set aside. Separate eggs.
Place whites in a deep bowl and add cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar in beaten egg whites.
Continue to beat until whites stand in peaks.
Place yolks in large bowl and beat gradually.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar and vanilla.
Beat until very thick.
Alternately with cooled coffee liquid, fold egg yolks and flour mixture, 1/4 at a time, into beaten whites.
Put in a 10-inch tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add melted butter, then buttermilk, beaten eggs, salt and vanilla.
Bake in uncooked pie shell until firm in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti with beef and mushroom stir-fry
directions: In medium bowl, combine soy sauce, 1 tablespoon oil, garlic and ginger.
Add beef strips; toss well to coat.
Cover; marinate 30 to 60 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: After cake is done, melt butter.
Add sugar and evaporated milk.
Pour on top of cake.

title: biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour and baking powder; add milk.
I mix with a spoon.
Turn onto a floured board and roll into 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut biscuits.
Place on cookie sheet.
Melt 1 teaspoon oleo and spread on top of each biscuit.
Cook about 10 to 12 minutes in 450° oven.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain clams, reserving juice; set clams aside.
Cook clam juice, potatoes, carrots, margarine, onion and water for 15 minutes or until veggies are tender.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer until heated through.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: pepper loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 400°.

title: salisbury steak and gravy
directions: Mix meat, eggs, bread and seasoning together.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in flour, mashing flat.
Fry.
Mix a full glass of water with gravy packet (onion gravy's great) and pour into a pot.
Put cooked patties in gravy, simmering while you finish frying rest of patties.
Pour off excess grease, but about 2 tablespoons.
Pour some of remaining flour in skillet; cook until brown.
Pour in water until thin enough to pour over meat.
Thin as needed.
Season gravy.

title: quick lasagne
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in dressing and Parmesan cheese.
Layer 1/2 of the noodles, meat mixture, spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Repeat layers.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking dish with butter.
Beat the eggs; add sugar and salt.
Stir in milk and corn.
Mix well. Bake 30 minutes.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Mix soup with melted butter and apple juice or vinegar.
Take 1 cup of the mixture and mix with rice in casserole.
Place chicken breasts over rice and pour rest of soup mixture over all. Sprinkle with paprika, almonds and cheese.
Bake at 275°, uncovered, for 2 hours.
(I use a cooking bag.)
(You don't have to use rice.)

title: bread or rolls
directions: Cook potatoes in water until done, soft. Drain, reserving one cup liquid from potatoes. Mash potatoes. Place 1/2 c. very warm, not hot, potato water in a bowl. Dissolve 1 tsp. sugar and the yeast in the water, let stand. Place sugar, salt, margarine and shortening in the hot mashed potatoes. Mix in well with mixer. Add the other 1/2 c. of potato water. Put this mixture in a very large bowl. Cool until very warm (not hot).

Mix in yeast then eggs. Add two cups of flour and beat with mixer. Add flour until you have a very nice soft dough, about 6 cups. Put the rest of the flour on dough board or counter. Place dough on the flour and knead until smooth and elastic. Grease a very large pan or bowl and put the dough into the bowl, turning over to grease the top. Cover with a light towel and let rise until double in bulk. Make into rolls or loaves of bread. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Butter tops of rolls or bread when removed from oven.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter. Mix with Rice Krispies. Add peanut butter and powdered sugar. Roll into balls. Refrigerate 5 to 10 minutes. Melt Hershey bar in double boiler. Stick toothpick in ball and dip in chocolate.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Either stew chicken breasts or cook in oven with 1/4 cup water for 45 minutes at 350°.
Pull meat from bones and dice.
Combine pineapple chunks with its juice, brown sugar, flour, vinegar, soy sauce and salt.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Pour over cooked meat and cook for 5 minutes at 350°.
Serve over rice.
(This recipe can easily be doubled for more servings or you can substitute pork.)

title: peach cobbler pie
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put peaches in pan.
Mix together flour and sugar.
Add milk and mix real good.
Then pour over peaches and bake at 350° until done or brown.

title: grandma's rhubarb pie
directions: Soak rhubarb in cold water 10 minutes; drain well.
Mix in flour, sugar, egg yolks and oleo. Beat egg whites until fluffy. Fold into rhubarb mixture.
Pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients for dressing.
Mix torn fresh spinach, peanuts, raisins, apples, sliced green onions and frozen peas.
Just before serving, add the chilled dressing.
