Also, the spinach should be cold.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch and an 8 x 8-inch pan. Sprinkle the coconut and pecans in the bottom of the pans.
Mix the cake mix according to package directions.
Pour on top of coconut and pecans.
Set aside.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in tightly covered jar. To serve, add 2 or 3 teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: mystery canapes
directions: Mix mayonnaise, catsup, curry powder and salt.
Add almonds, celery, onion and dates.
Mix well. At this point the mixture may be refrigerated, covered, for up to a week.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Spoon onto Triscuits and bake for 1 to 2 minutes.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add rest of ingredients.
Beat vigorously for 2 minutes.
Fold in 2 cups blueberries.
Turn into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Combine 1/2 cup of sugar with 3/4 teaspoon of nutmeg and sprinkle over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: brandy (or rum) balls
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan, combine evaporated milk and chocolate pieces.
Cook, stirring over medium heat until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add crushed wafers, sugar, 1/2 cup pecans and brandy or rum; mix well. Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes.
Shape into balls 1 inch in diameter.
Roll in remaining pecans.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm.

title: rice stuffing casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Stir before servings.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter blossom cookies
directions: Blend in dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and roll into balls. Roll into sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove and place a chocolate kiss on top until cookie cracks.
Return to oven and bake 2 to 5 minutes more.

title: smoke fish brine
directions: Stir well.
Put clean fish in brine 8 to 10 hours.
Rinse and dry.
Smoke for 8 hours.
Wrap in foil.
Cook 2 hours at 200°.

title: easy berry pie
directions: Combine water and gelatin in small saucepan.
Place over low heat and stir until dissolved and mixture is clear.
In a medium bowl, combine condensed milk and lemon juice.
Stir in gelatin mixture until well combined.
Fold in sour cream.
Mix in 1 1/4 cups blueberry filling.
Spread mixture evenly into crust.
Chill remaining filling.
Cover and refrigerate pie for 3 to 4 hours.

title: lemon honey turkey
directions: In a small bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients. Place tenderloins in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray. Brush with half the sauce. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until a meat thermometer reads 170°, basting occasionally with remaining sauce. Remove turkey to a plate and keep warm. Transfer drippings to a small saucepan. Combine cornstarch and water until smooth. Stir in drippings. Bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 1 to 2 minutes or until thickened. Stir in browning sauce, if desired. Serve sauce over turkey. Yield: 6 servings.

title: green beans almondine
directions: Simmer beans with water and soup mix for 20 minutes.
Drain. Turn into a serving dish.
Combine rest of ingredients and mix with beans.

title: very tender baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken thoroughly.
Salt lightly on both sides.
Roll in flour.
Place in lightly greased baking dish.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove cover.
Drain drippings from chicken; pour over top of chicken.
Put back in oven, uncovered, until brown.

title: plum cake
directions: Dump all of the ingredients together and mix with mixer.
Stir in 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour (approximately).

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss the first 6 ingredients in bowl and top with dressing made with other ingredients.
Toss and serve.
Store in refrigerator.

title: potato soup
directions: The amount of the ingredients you use depends on the amount you want as a finished product.
Saute onion in butter.
Add chopped potatoes, smoked sausage (cut into small rounds),
salt, pepper and parsley.
Don't quite cover with water and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add milk to make pot as full as you want. Stir over medium heat until heated through.
(If you want it thick, add Shaker Gravy Flour according to directions on box.)

title: never fail fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter, milk and Marshmallow Whip and bring to a boil.
Boil 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add chocolate bits and stir until dissolved.
Add nuts and pour into a buttered pan to cool.
Mark into squares.
Makes 2 1/4 pounds.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.
Put drained spaghetti in 9 x 9 pan, shredded cheese on top.
Mix egg and milk; pour over top.
Top with hamburg and sauce.

title: baked pizza pockets
directions: Cut a thin slice from top of each pouch bread.
Mix filling. Fill pouches carefully, then pat gently to distribute filling. Place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Brush tops lightly with oil.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
When lukewarm, cut into wedges with serrated knife.
Serves 6 or more.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, sugar, soda, salad dressing and vanilla. Slowly add water to batter and beat in well.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli in flowerets.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together.
Add broccoli and marinate overnight in refrigerator. Right before serving, add onion, bacon and raisins.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt; gradually add milk.
Cook in double boiler until thick, about 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Slowly add small amounts of hot mixture to egg yolks.
Stir, adding rest of hot mixture.
Cook 5 minutes; cool.
Add butter and vanilla.
Slice bananas into cooled, baked shell.
Whip 1/2 whipping cream and fold into cream filling.
Pour over bananas. Refrigerate.
Decorate with balance of whipped cream.

title: apple salad
directions: Boil together to thick: sugar, pineapple and flour and then add butter.
Cool.
Dice apples (peel if desired). Mix Cool Whip and nuts.
Add sauce and apples by folding them into mixture. Sprinkle a few chopped maraschino cherries on top.
Quick, easy and good!

title: ham tetrazzini
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion in margarine until tender.	Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Stir until smooth. Cook over medium heat stirring until thickened and smooth.	Stir in ham, soup, mushroom, garlic powder and cheeses.	Mix well. Stir until cheese melts.
Stir in cooked noodles.
Pour into lightly greased 9x13 pan.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° until heated.
(Note:
Chicken or turkey are also good to use and may be substituted for ham.)
Serves 6-8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Brown onions and celery in saucepan with margarine.
Combine all other ingredients except Cheddar cheese soup.
Mix well in casserole dish.
Heat Cheddar cheese soup in a saucepan and spread over mixture.
Cover and bake about 45 minutes or until brown around edges in preheated 350° oven.

title: blender bernaise sauce
directions: Leave hollandaise in the blender container.

In a small saucepan, combine wine, vinegar, tarragon, onion and pepper. Bring to a boil and cook until liquid is reduced to 2 tablespoons. Pour into the prepared hollandaise and blend on high speed a few seconds to blend.
Serve over asparagus, broccoli or grilled steak.

title: mamaw's chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, melted margarine and mix well.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake 35-40 minutes until firm in 350° oven.

title: vanilla frozen dessert(has 65 calories)
directions: Combine skim milk and evaporated milk in saucepan. Heat until scalded.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add sweetener and vanilla.
Blend into milk.
Pour into freezer tray.
Cool to room temperature.
Place in freezer until frozen around edges and thick in center.
Remove to chilled bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Combine dry milk and ice water.
Beat until consistency of whipped cream. Fold into gelatin mixture.
Pour into 2 freezer trays.
Freeze until firm.
Yields 8 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Combine all other ingredients.
Mix well and bake in 4 well-greased and floured coffee cans (1 pound size).
Fill cans 1/2 full and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pennsylvania cole slaw
directions: Adjust amount of sauce according to how much cabbage and carrots you use.
Heat vinegar; add sugar and oil, and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat and add salt, pepper and celery seed.
Pour sauce over slaw and seal tightly.
Let sit in the refrigerator for several hours or overnight.

title: italian cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: christmas scent
directions: Combine all ingredients in a kettle or saucepan.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer as long as needed.
Check often and add water, as needed.
Store in refrigerator and re-use.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Then add beaten eggs.
Sift soda with 2 cups flour.
Add butter mixture. Add more flour if necessary to make a drop batter.
Drop by spoonfuls and smash with fork.
Delicious cookies.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add all ingredients, except cheese.

title: hummus
directions: Mix all ingredients in a food processor or blender and refrigerate.
Serve with pita bread.

title: buttery almond cookies
directions: Beat sugar, butter and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add almond extract and egg; blend well.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
(Dough will be stiff.)
Divide dough into four equal parts.
On lightly floured surface form each part into a roll 6 inches long and 1 1/2 inches thick.
Wrap rolls in plastic wrap. Refrigerate at least 1 hour until firm.
Heat oven to 375°. Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Cut each roll into 12 (1/2-inch) slices.
Gently press 1 almond into center of cookie.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: banana crush
directions: Squeeze juice from oranges and lemons.
Prepare a syrup with sugar and water.
Mash bananas into citrus juices.
Add pineapple juice and sugar syrup.
Place in container and freeze.

title: jiffy raisin loaf
directions: Rinse raisins in hot water; drain. Combine with biscuit mix, sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Beat egg. Add milk. Stir into dry ingredients. Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool on rack.

title: banana milkshake
directions: Mash banana well.
Add milk and blend with beater or shake in jar.
Serve immediately or refrigerate and serve later.
Makes one serving, about 1 1/2 cups, with 187 calories.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine apples, cinnamon, margarine and sugar in dish that can be used as a serving dish.
Top with cake mix.
Melt margarine and pour over cake.
Mix.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes or until brown on top.

title: ice cream crunchies
directions: Mix ingredients (except ice cream) until Rice Krispies are well coated.
Press mixture into wax paper-lined 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan. Chill.
Remove from pan and cut into 12 (3-inch) squares.
Cut 2 pints of ice cream into slices and place between crunchie squares. Wrap and freeze.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Stir cream cheese until very soft; blend in 1/2 cup milk until smooth.
Add 1 1/2 cups milk and pudding mix.
Beat slowly for 1 minute.
Pour at once into 9-inch crumb crust.
Chill.

title: mexican chili
directions: Melt Crisco in large skillet.
Brown onion, green pepper and ground beef; add remaining ingredients.
Stir and cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Brown and dice bacon; drain.
Brown hamburger.
Add remaining ingredients including bacon.
Mix well and place in casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: date nut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time. Fold in flour and baking	powder;
add
extract.	Fold
in
pecans and dates. Bake at 350° about 2 1/2 hours.

title: stained-glass potato chips
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Brush each of 3 jelly roll pans with 1 tablespoon oil.
Slice potatoes paper thin with mandoline slicer or by hand; stack slices.
Sandwich 1 teaspoon herbs between 2 same size slices in prepared pan.
Repeat with remaining herbs and potatoes.
Brush tops with remaining 1 tablespoon oil; sprinkle lightly with salt.
Bake in batches until edges are golden and crisp, 7 to 11 minutes.
Drain chips on paper towels.
(Can be made ahead.
Reheat on cookie sheets in preheated 400° oven for 3 to 4 minutes.)
Makes 3 dozen chips.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 375° in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with cream cheese frosting or dust with powdered sugar.

title: pizza pie dough
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in water.
Beat in half flour; add salt, oil and remaining flour.
Mix well.
Knead until smooth. Let rise until double.
Spread over greased pizza pans and garnish with your favorite toppings.

title: frozen kahlua creme
directions: Beat cream until stiff peaks form.
Combine ice cream, cream, and Kahlua.
Pour into cupcake papers set into muffin tins. Sprinkle with almonds.
Freeze until firm.
To serve, prepare dessert plate with chocolate sauce drizzle or chocolate shavings. Remove Creme from cupcake paper and turn upside down on dessert plate.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Steam all vegetables until just cooked, about 8 minutes.
Place 1 cup rice pilaf on the bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Put all vegetables on the bed of rice and pour salsa over vegetables. Place thinly sliced cheeses on top to cover.
Sprinkle sunflower seeds on top of cheese.
Place in microwave for approximately 5 minutes, until cheese is melted.
For conventional oven, preheat to 375°.
Bake in oven until cheese is thoroughly melted.
This has been a favorite dish of restaurateur Bric Haley for many years!

title: ma bess' lemon bisque
directions: Thoroughly
chill
milk
or it will not whip.
Dissolve jello in	boiling
water.
Add
sugar,
salt, lemon juice and rind. When this has congealed, beat milk until stiff and whip jello mixture into it.
Spread half of vanilla wafer crumbs in large pan and pour lemon mixture over it.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Set in refrigerator to chill, about 3 hours.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season chops; dredge in flour, brown in oil and place in a greased casserole.
Place pepper and onion slices on each chop. Add spoonful of rice on each chop.
Pour tomato sauce and water on top.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for one hour.
Add more water, if necessary.
Serves 4.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and cook in a small amount of water until tender. Drain and mash.
Add other ingredients, except half of cheese and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs on top of casserole and bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dilly beans
directions: Scald pint jars and pack beans in jars vertically.
Put 1 head dill, 1 red pepper and 1 clove garlic in each jar.
Bring vinegar, water and salt to a boil.
Pour over beans to 1/2-inch in top of jar.
Adjust lids and process in water bath 5 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Prepare gelatin and set aside to cool.
Mix grated carrots, sugar and pineapple together.
When gelatin is cool, add carrot-pineapple mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch square dish and refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce, if desired.

title: chocolate peanut butter dessert
directions: Crush 32 Oreo cookies. Toss with melted butter. Press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix cream cheese, peanut butter and 2 cups powdered sugar; fold in 1 (16 ounce) carton of Cool Whip. Spread over crust. Sprinkle with chopped peanut butter cups. Mix pudding, milk and powdered sugar for 2 minutes. Fold in 1 (16 ounce) carton Cool Whip. Spread over the peanut butter cups. Crush remaining 8 Oreo cookies and sprinkle over top. Chill at least 3 hours.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss together the first 7 ingredients with the mayonnaise, lemon juice and soy sauce. Add apple slices and serve on lettuce.

title: custard rhubarb pie
directions: Put rhubarb in a dish; sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Melt butter.
Beat eggs.
Add remaining sugar and milk.
Arrange rhubarb on pie crust.
Dribble butter over rhubarb.
Add egg mixture.
Cover with lattice strips of crust.
Bake until knife test proves done, at 350°.

title: all-bran pull apart rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Knead lightly and place in lightly greased bowl; let rise.
Knead well. Pinch off rolls and let rise again in greased pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: dot's special biscuits
directions: Mix together into dough.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter or drop into skillet of hot oil and turn over, browning both sides.

title: ham and cheese party rolls
directions: Melt margarine; add poppy seed and Worcestershire.
Pour over rolls.
Bake in 350° oven approximately 5 to 10 minutes, until cheese begins to melt.

title: hostess twinkie cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed and cool.
Boil flour and milk.
Let cool.
Beat in margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and vanilla. Beat until thick and creamy.
Split cake and frost between layers.

title: grandmother's apple salad
directions: Mix sugar, water, butter, egg, flour and vinegar, stirring constantly. Cook until thickened. Cool and fold into fruits and nuts. Serves 12-14.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and egg.
Add soup, raisins, flour and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for almost an hour in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Test with toothpick.

title: marinara
directions: Cook onion, carrots, oil and garlic for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add red pepper, oregano and basil.
Cook for 15 seconds.
Add tomatoes and crab meat.
Put over cooked angel hair spaghetti.

title: apple crisp
directions: Coat bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread out pie filling to cover bottom about 1/2 to 3/4 inches thick.
Spread box of cake mix over pie filling.
Melt margarine/butter and drizzle over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour or until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: pumpkin nickel bread
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
In a separate bowl, mix the remaining ingredients.
Combine both mixtures until well moistened.
Spoon into a greased loaf pan and top with topping. Bake at 350° for 1 hours.
Cool on rack.
Freezes well.

title: carrot slaw
directions: In a bowl, combine carrots, mayonnaise, lemon juice, coconut, currants (if using) and sugar.
Add cinnamon and toss with fork. Refrigerate a few hours; toss and serve.

title: grilled jalapeno boats
directions: Cook and crumble bacon.
Slice peppers in half lengthwise and remove seeds.
Fill with cheese and garnish with crumbled bits of bacon.
Cook on grill away from flames until cheese melts.

title: original chex brand party mix
directions: Combine margarine, Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt. Mix well.
Pour cereal, nuts and pretzels into large resealable plastic bag.

title: congealed tomato salad
directions: Heat 1 cup tomato
juice.
Sprinkle gelatin over it and stir to soften, almost boiling.	Stir
in the other 2 1/2 cups juice, vinegar, lemon
juice,
Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder. Let begin to jell and add the rest of ingredients and let congeal.

title: beer batter for shrimp
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, beer, egg, baking powder and seafood seasoning.
Mix well.
Let sit for 10 minutes.
In skillet or deep fryer, heat oil to 350°.
Dip each shrimp in batter.
Roll in coconut, if desired.
Fry until golden brown, about 2 to 5 minutes.
(Do not burn coconut.)

title: vegetable lasagne
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan; add eggplant, onion and garlic; cook stirring 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, salt, sugar and basil. Bring to boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer until tender 20 minutes.
Combine spinach (thawed and drained) Ricotta, Mozzarella, egg and nutmeg in large bowl; spoon 1 1/4 cup eggplant sauce in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Layer with 3 lasagne noodles and half the spinach mixture, 3 more noodles and 1 3/4 cup sauce, then remaining spinach mixture and noodles.
Top with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; bake uncovered 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: everyday salad
directions: I don't always use that large a can of pineapple.

title: pizza sandwich
directions: Brown onion and ground beef.
Drain.
Mix in 1 can tomato sauce and oregano. Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.

title: mama's eggless cake
directions: Mix all and boil for 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix 1 tablespoon baking soda with a little cold water.
Add to cooled mixture.
Add enough flour for a thick dough (a little denser than a carrot cake batter).
Bake in greased and floured pans at 350° until tests done with toothpick (about 40 minutes).
Makes 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: monkey bread in a loaf pan
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Combine granulated sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag.
Drop biscuits in and shake.
Combine brown sugar and margarine.
Heat gently until melted.
Place biscuits in a greased 7 3/4 x 3 3/4-inch loaf pan.
Pour brown sugar and margarine mixture over biscuits.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
This is tasty when served warm. You don't slice it, just tear off pieces at the table.

title: golden glazed chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in single layer in baking pan.

In saucepan, melt butter; add remaining ingredients, stirring until smooth. Pour over chicken; bake, uncovered, in 550° oven about 45 minutes, basting occasionally with sauce, until tender and glazed.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix margarine, shortening, sugar and eggs.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Roll dough into teaspoon size balls.
Roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture (great for little hands!).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: microwave cashew or peanut brittle
directions: Combine peanuts (or cashews), corn syrup, sugar and salt in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Syrup must be added first or the sugar will not melt. Cook 8 minutes on High, stirring after 4 minutes. Add butter and vanilla. Cook 1 more minute at High. Add baking soda and stir until light and foamy. Immediately pour onto lightly buttered baking sheet and spread out thin. When cool, break into pieces. Store in airtight container. Do not double!

title: maple icing
directions: Add the brown sugar to the milk, then add the butter, melted. Add the confectioners sugar slowly and mix well, then spread on cake.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix ingredients.
Heat 2 sticks butter or margarine in skillet.
Drop by teaspoon into hot margarine.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels and serve at once.

title: cherry nut ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients except regular milk.
Pour into ice cream freezer containers.
Finish filling the containers to the fill line with the regular milk.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: baked ham with glaze sauce
directions: In a 5-quart cast-iron Dutch oven, melt the butter until it sizzles, but don't let it burn!
Then toss in the onions, green onions and mushrooms and quickly stir-fry them over high heat until the onions turn a rich caramel color (which should take about 10 minutes or so).
When they're done, remove the vegetables from the pot and set them aside in a baking pan.

title: homemade chili
directions: Mix tomato juice, beans, chili powder, flour, and sugar. Heat and simmer.
Brown beef and onion.
Drain fat and pour into tomato mixture.
Cook on low for 20-30 minutes.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add about 5 tablespoons to 1 cup of hot water.

title: moist and minty brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square pan.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a small saucepan, combine sugar, oleo and water.
Bring to just a boil; remove from heat.
Add 1 cup chocolate chips and vanilla, stirring until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Transfer to a larger bowl.
Add eggs, beating well after each.
Stir in flour mixture and remaining chocolate chips.
Spread into prepared pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, just until center is set.
Cool; cut into 2 1/4-inch squares.

title: turkey curry
directions: Brown turkey in a large skillet that has been sprayed with cooking spray, breaking meat into chunks and turning to brown evenly.
Drain and discard fat.

title: mommy's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix it all up and bring to a boil in a pan.
Line baking pan with foil and place chicken on top.
Seal, leaving space for steam.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pork chops with apples
directions: In a large skillet, brown pork chops in oil on each side. Season with salt and pepper.
Remove and keep warm.

title: wine punch
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and pour over a block of ice. Serves 12.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls and roll in sugar.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: no-bake coconut pie
directions: Mix all together. Pour into pie plate and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Makes its own crust.
Makes two pies.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion in margarine until transparent. Add mushrooms and cook slightly; stir in flour. Add broth and milk and bring to a gradual boil, stirring constantly. Add seasonings and pimento; blend together.
Combine with turkey.
Alternate layers of spaghetti and turkey, ending with layer of spaghetti. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Freezes well. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pizza fondue
directions: Brown together hamburger and onion.
Add other ingredients.

title: shorten bread
directions: Cream butter with 10-X sugar.
Gradually add flour.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet and roll in 10-X sugar or combination of 10-X sugar and coconut or ground nuts.
Double for a nice batch.

title: hamburger baked bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Crumble bacon on top.
Cover and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and cook for another 30 minutes.

title: braised lamb shanks(crockery cooking)
directions: Roll shanks in flour and brown in oil.
Place shanks in crock-pot.
Mix flour with 1/2 cup water; add to chicken broth water and rosemary, salt, pepper and cube.
Pour mixture over shanks and cook on high 1 hour.
Turn on low and cook 6 to 9 hours until done.
Serve with boiled potatoes, peas and mint jelly.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing.
Then add onions and crab meat or shrimp; mix well.

title: crab pate
directions: Heat soup in pan; remove from heat.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add to soup, stirring well.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into 4-cup mold.
Chill until firm (overnight). Serve with crackers.

title: zippy mushrooms
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Add onion slices. Cover and place in refrigerator for 24 hours. Black olives may also be added.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour, cream of tartar, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture, then add milk and orange juice.
Stir in flavoring and orange rind.
Pour in tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: salsa dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate before serving.
Great sauce for Mexican dishes or a favorite with chips.

title: fresh tomato soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add tomatoes and enough broth to cover.
Add herbs and simmer for 10 to 12 minutes.
Put mixture through coarse blender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 30 to 40 minutes.
Add salt to taste and teaspoon of sugar if desired.
Stir frequently.
Serves 8.
Okay to freeze. Lots of work, but worth it.

title: chocolate cherry pie
directions: Spread softened cream cheese evenly in bottom of baked pie shell.
Cook chocolate pudding according to package directions and pour on top of cream cheese.
Allow pudding to cool.
Completely top with cherry pie filling.
Garnish with Cool Whip.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fire and ice
directions: Boil all ingredients except tomatoes, pepper and onion hard for 1 minute.
Combine all ingredients and pour over tomatoes. Chill.
Good for summer picnics.

title: cream cheese roll
directions: Cream the cheese with the butter.
Add the onion juice and salt.
Roll in the ground nuts.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Stand roll in icebox.
Slice thin and serve with crackers.

title: ginger's hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all together.
Keep in a large container.
Mix several teaspoons with a cup of hot water.

title: cheese ball
directions: Use food processor to combine all ingredients.
Make a ball. Roll ball in paprika or chili powder or chopped pecans.

title: calico beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low heat setting for 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 hours.
Uncover and cook on high heat setting for 30 more minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: flour tortillas
directions: In mixing bowl stir together flour, salt and baking powder. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Add 1/2 cup warm water and mix until dough can be gathered into a ball (if needed, add more water, 1 tablespoon at a time).
Let dough rest 15 minutes.
Divide dough into 12 portions; shape into balls.
On a lightly floured surface, roll each ball to a 7-inch round.
Trim uneven edges to make round tortillas.
Cook in ungreased skillet over medium heat about 1 1/2 minutes per side or until lightly browned.
Makes 12 tortillas.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
Cream butter and other ingredients to squash.
Pour into casserole dish and add Pepperidge stuffing on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Cook onions until tender.
Add tomatoes, beans, corn, taco seasoning and 1 or 2 cups of water. Simmer.
Serve.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix everything except margarine.
Pour into casserole pan, then cut up margarine on top of mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until desired color of toasty brown.

title: burnt caramel pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Add other ingredients.
Top pie with meringue and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients, except fruit.
Add fruit and liquid; mix. Pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine fruit and nuts and dredge in 1 cup flour; mix well. Set aside.
Combine remaining 1 cup of flour with other dry ingredients; set aside.
Beat eggs; gradually add sugar.
Mix well. Add melted butter, honey and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture, blending well.
Line a 10-inch tube pan or 2 smaller ones or loaf pans with wax paper.
Grease and flour.

title: apricot brandy
directions: Place ingredients (do not mix) in 1/2 gallon flat topped glass jar.
Turn the jar twice a day.
Allowing the jar to sit on its top for half the day.
Do this for 8 days and your first batch is ready.
You may use the same apricots, more sugar and vodka to make another batch only let the second batch sit for 12 to 14 days.
The apricots can be used for bread after the brandy is finished.

title: german pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients except butter together.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan and pour mixture in.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. A delicious breakfast variation.

title: pawley's island ratatouille
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add all the remaining ingredients, putting tomatoes in last.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 10 to 15 minutes, allowing to cook down.

title: one step lasagne
directions: Brown beef and mix in sauce.
Mix water and sauce in large bowl.
Spread 1 1/2 cups sauce in lasagne dish.
Put noodles to cover sauce on top.
Spread 1/2 of cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese over this and 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Add another 1 1/2 cups sauce and repeat noodle layer and cheeses.
Put remaining sauce over this and be sure to cover noodles.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese over this.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms with damp paper towels.
Remove stems and use in another dish.
Marinate mushrooms in Italian dressing for 2 hours in refrigerator, then drain well.
Combine other ingredients and spoon into caps; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Saute beef with onion.
Add diluted soup and frozen mixed vegetables.
Pour into casserole.
Cover with Tater Tots and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Add yeast, milk and sugar to warm water in mixing bowl.
Stir to dissolve.
Add salt, eggs, shortening and half of flour.
For light, flakey buns, keep dough soft as possible, almost sticky, just so you are able to handle it.
Mix with wooden spoon until smooth.
Add enough remaining flour to handle easily.
Mix with hands.
Turn out on board and knead 5 minutes.
Round up in well-greased or oiled bowl.
Turn so greased side is up.
Cover with damp towel.
Let rise until almost double, 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and let rise again, 30 minutes.
Roll out dough a portion at a time 3/8-inch thick.
Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon/sugar mix.
Roll jelly roll fashion and slice.
Place in ungreased pans close together.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: batter fish
directions: Add enough 7-Up to pancake flour to make a thick batter.
Cut up fish into small pieces.
Pat dry.
Dip fish into batter and drop into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown on all sides.
Drain and serve hot or cold.
If batter gets too thick, add more 7-Up. Happy eating!

title: pickle relish
directions: Mix well the first 6 ingredients.
Let stand for 1/2 hour. Drain off salt and water.
Mix sugar, white vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Pour over chopped ingredients.
Refrigerate. Let stand 7 to 10 days before eating.
Keeps very well.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
After removing the crusts, use a rolling pin to flatten each slice of bread.
Combine cream cheese and bacon, stirring well.
Spread bread with cheese mixture, covering to edges.
Place 2 asparagus spears, in alternate directions, on each slice of bread; roll up and place seam side down on a greased baking sheet.
Brush each generously with butter and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Cut each roll in half.
Bake for 12 min.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend the 2 cheeses. Add pineapple, onion and sauce.
Chill. Form in ball and roll in nuts. Refrigerate.

title: pesto torte
directions: Combine cream cheese, butter and goat cheese.
Spread 1/3 of this mixture on a decorative plate.
Spread a layer of Pesto over the cheese layer.
Repeat these layers
and end with a cheese layer.
Dice sundried tomatoes and place on top.
Chill well, but serve at room temperature with Tuscany toast, Melba toast, bagel chips or crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup of cheese and 1/4 cup of crackers.
Combine all other ingredients in a casserole dish.
Top with reserved crackers and cheese.
Bake at 350° until top is bubbling.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Put
first
ingredients in blender.	When completely liquified, take out and add sugar and vinegar.
Cook at a hard boil for 5	minutes.
Skim	the
top.
Add	green
or red food coloring and 2 bottles of Certo.
Put into hot jars and store.

title: cacerola de posole(hominy casserole)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients, except the cheese, and spoon into a lightly greased 8 x 8-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese evenly on top. Cover with foil and bake for 20 minutes. Remove foil and bake an additional 10 minutes until golden and bubbly.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by heaping teaspoonful 2 inches apart.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven and test.
After done, place on rack to cool.
When cooled, use Marshmallow Fluff and put two together.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter, then stir in cocoa.
Remove from heat. Stir in sugar and eggs.
Mix well. Add flour, salt, nuts and vanilla. Mix well. Pour into greased pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Cover hot cake with marshmallows. Frost with favorite frosting.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Place Italian dressing over and bake 30 minutes.
Add rice, vegetables, bouillon cubes and water.
Bake another 30 minutes.
When done, can use the juices for gravy.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Remove from pan and saute onion, green pepper and garlic until just tender.
Grease baking dish; layer potatoes, vegetable mixture, salt and pepper and chops.
Pour mushroom soup, diluted with 1/2 can milk on top of chops.
Bake at 350°`, covered, for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and continue to bake until tender and golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: hot stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms. Remove stems and chop. Brush with melted butter. Saut stems and garlic in butter. Transfer to small bowl. Add lobster or crabmeat, Worcestershire sauce, egg, salt and pepper. Stir to combine. Fill caps with mixture. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Top with melted butter. Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes. Serve immediately. Can partially do ahead. Yield: 12. Preparing: 30 minutes. Baking: 15 minutes.

title: chocolate dream cookies
directions: Measure flour, salt and soda (sift).
Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Cream thoroughly.
Blend in egg and slightly cooled chocolate.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Add chips and mix well. Drop by teaspoons onto lightly greased baking sheet and bake in moderate oven (375°) for 10 minutes.
Serves 5 dozen.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt all ingredients, except powdered sugar, in large saucepan over low heat.
When melted, remove from heat and add the powdered sugar.
Pat into greased 9 x 9-inch glass pan.
Press napkins onto top.
Cool.
Remove napkins and cut.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and chili in bowl.
Warm in pan or microwave. Serve warm with taco chips.

title: welsh rarebit
directions: Heat the butter in a saucepan; stir in the flour and cook steadily for several minutes, then gradually add the cold milk. Bring to the boil and cook until smooth and thick.
Add the mustard, salt, pepper, most of the cheese and the beer.
Heat steadily without boiling too quickly until cheese has melted. Spread over the buttered toast.
Sprinkle with remainder of the cheese and brown under a hot grill.
Serve at once.

title: venison marinade
directions: For each pound of meat make solution of vinegar and water and marinate the meat in a glass bowl for several hours.

title: delicious salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Pull marshmallows apart and dissolve in Jell-O.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Put in refrigerator until starts to congeal.
Stir in whipped cream.
Put back in refrigerator.
Best to make night before.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine tuna, cooked rice and 1 to 2 tablespoons minced onion. Heat milk; add bread crumbs, then cool slightly.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add crumb mixture to tuna mixture and mix, then fold in egg whites and 1 cup cheese.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until center rises and knife comes out clean.

title: mushroom hors d'oeuvres
directions: Coarsely chop mushrooms in a food processor.
Remove and set aside.
Coarsely chop onion.
Remove and set aside.
Finely chop the parsley.
Melt butter over low heat in a frying pan.
Add reserved ingredients.
Cook slowly.
If it is too thick, add a little sour cream.
Serve on cocktail rye or crackers.
This is a favorite of ours!

title: pumpkin ice cream roll
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, pumpkin, pie spice, baking powder and salt.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes or until pale yellow.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin.
Fold in dry ingredients.

title: arizona barbecued ribs
directions: Have ribs cut into sections 2 or 3 inches long.
Brown in shortening.
Add minced onion and brown.
Add all remaining ingredients to short ribs.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° from 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.
May be cooked on stovetop if preferred.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: candy
directions: Melt chocolate bars. Remove from heat and beat until smooth. Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch buttered pan.
Cut into squares when cool.
Makes 18 ounces total.

title: christine's frozen fruit salad
directions: Fold together ingredients in order listed.
Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish with nonstick spray.
Pour in salad mixture and freeze.

title: oven-fried okra
directions: Wash okra and drain.
Remove tips and stem ends; cut okra crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Boil together first 7 ingredients for 1 hour.
Work through sieve.
Cream together and add butter and flour.
Add salt and sugar.
Boil together 10 minutes.
When thickened, put in cans and hot water bath 5 or 10 minutes rolling boil.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Stir in pie filling.
Turn into 9 x 9-inch cake dish.
Chill until set.
